name: Three Fingers
description: Three Fingers is an NPC in Elden Ring. Three Fingers is an integral part of The Lord of Frenzied Flame ending and can be found near the Cathedral of the Forsaken, below the Subterranean Shunning-Grounds. There they pass on the unspeakable message of the Frenzied Flame.
metadata: {"image": "https://eldenring.fanapis.com/images/npcs/17f6985df0bl0i2os10gas1pv9n5r.png", "quote": "???", "location": "Cathedral of, the Forsaken", "role": "???", "Location": "Cathedral of the Forsaken", "Role": "Quest NPC", "Voiced by": "N/A", "wiki_url": "https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/Three+Fingers"}

name: The Great-jar
description: The Great-Jar is an NPC in Elden Ring. The Great-Jar can be found in Northern Caelid, at the colosseum North of the Deep Siofra River Well Site of Grace.

name: Bridge Of Sacrifice
description: A busy bridge swarming with iron-clad foes. Be prepared to engage in an array of melee, ranged and artillery attacks or attempt to push past them

name: Church Of Elleh
description: Church of Elleh is a ruined building that hides a Site of Grace. The rooftop has caved in and offers no protection from the elements, and weeds are overtaking the walls, but this doesn't stop merchants from seeking what little shelter is on offer Church of Elleh is a Location in Elden Ring. The Church of Elleh is found in Western Limgrave. Players will find it by heading north from the first Site of Grace available. This is an important checkpoint for the player as it features a merchant and weapon upgrade table.

name: Deathtouched Catacombs
description: Catacombs filled with the stench of death, Skeletons dwell in the shadows Deathtouched Catacombs is a Location in Elden Ring. The Deathtouched Catacombs is found in Stormhill, Limgrave. It can be reached by heading west from Saintsbridge.

name: Church Of Dragon Communion
description: The dilapidated remains of the Church of Dragon Communion showcase the ruin that came to the land. But could a flame still linger at its altar??

name: Coastal Cave
description: Coastal Cave is a dark opening on the side of a cliff. Its mossy depths are overrun by hostile humanoid creatures, but those who brave it may find passage to new lands Coastal Cave is a Location in Elden Ring. The Coastal Cave is found in Western Limgrave, on the southern portion of the western beach. This cave leads to the Church of Dragon Communion location.

name: Dragon-burnt Ruins
description: Dragon-Burnt Ruins are what remains of the housing area among Agheel Lake, long lost to the deadly attacks of the fierce Agheel Dragon Dragon-Burnt Ruins is a Location in Elden Ring. The Dragon-Burnt Ruins is found in Limgrave, around the center area of Agheel Lake.

name: Forlorn Hound Evergaol
description: The southern Evergaol of Limgrave, before the entrance to Weeping Peninsula Forlorn Hound Evergaol is a Location in Elden Ring. The Forlorn Hound Evergaol is found in Limgrave. It can be found at the very south of Main Limgrave

name: Fringefolk Hero's Grave
description: Fingefolk Hero's Grave is a dark and secluded location within the Cave of Knowledge. The confused and aimless dwell within Fringefolk Hero's Grave is a Location in Elden Ring. The Fringefolk Hero's Grave is found in Limgrave behind a fog wall in Stranded Graveyard that requires two Stonesword Keys. It is a dungeon.

name: Fort Haight
description: The overrun fort of Kenneth Haith, the alleged next ruler of Limgrave

name: Divine Tower Of Limgrave
description: Closed with a giant set of doors. It looks like you need some pieces to interact with the tower.

name: Gatefront Ruins
description: Gatefront Ruins is what remains of the now destroyed barracks near the fortification. Despite its poor state, it is a heavily guarded location by those loyal to Stormveil

name: Limgrave Tunnels
description: Limgrave Tunnels are a mine harvested for Glimstone. Its zealous miners don't dare venture into its hidden chambers, for fear of the hoarder Troll within Limgrave Tunnels is a Location in Elden Ring. The Limgrave Tunnels is found in Limgrave, on the northern area of the Agheel Lake, just south from "Agheel Lake North" grace.

name: Groveside Cave
description: Groveside Cave is a small refuge for wildlife in Limgrave. Its proximity to water and ease of access make it a sought-after shelter against bad weather, but those who venture in don't seem to return Groveside Cave is a Location in Elden Ring. The Groveside Cave is found in Limgrave, just north from Church of Elleh.

name: Minor Erdtree (mistwood)
description: Easily distiguished from the rest of the trees in Mistwood Forest.

name: Highroad Cave
description: A cave that houses a tomb, deep within. It is situated at the northmost part of Limgrave. It has been inhabited by a pack of Wolves, Land Octopuses, and Giant Bats Highroad Cave is a Location in Elden Ring. The Highroad Cave is found in Stormhill, Limgrave. You can find the cave at the far northside of Limgrave [Map Coordinates Here]. The nearest site of grace to reach the entrance of the cave is the Saintsbridge site. Make sure to bring a Torch before entering this cave.

name: Mistwood
description: Mistwood is a Location in Elden Ring. The Mistwood region is located in the Eastern part of Limgrave. Tiered terrain, small beaches, and luscious forests occupied by Lesser Runebears are the defining features of this region.

name: Mistwood Ruins
description: Concealed by the thriving growth of vegetation, these ruins are kept out of sight by the veil of nature itself. But there's more to it than what you see

name: Murkwater Catacombs
description: An underground cemetery that is located at the north-east side of Agheel Lake in Limgrave. Once a place for peaceful rest for fallen heroes, it is now infested by goblins. Murkwater Catacombs is a Location in Elden Ring. The Murkwater Catacombs is found in the eastern portion of Western Limgrave, by following the water north-east from Agheel Lake.

name: Murkwater Cave
description: A dark cave halfway through the Murkwater River Murkwater Cave is a Location in Elden Ring. The Murkwater Cave is found in Limgrave. It can be found halfway through the Murkwater River, beware of Bloody Finger Nerijus' position.

name: Siofra River Well
description: A mystical underground region filled with its own set of skies and stars. Beware, it is teeming with creatures big and small alike

name: Smoldering Church
description: The Last Church in Limgrave before reaching Caelid

name: Stormgate
description: The Stormgate is a heavily guarded area that marks the border within Limgrave and Stormhill. Only the foolhardy would rush such against such odds

name: Stormfoot Catacombs
description: Stormfoot Catacombs were meant as a restful place for the deceased, but its now overrun by Goblins. Its deepest secrets are secured by the Guardian of the Burial Tree Stormfoot Catacombs is a Location in Elden Ring. The Stormfoot Catacombs is found in West Limgrave, due West and north from Church of Elleh.

name: Stormhill
description: Stormhill is a Location in Elden Ring. Stormhill is the upper half area of Limgrave, between its central river and Stormveil.

name: Stormhill Evergaol
description: The Brave and Foolish alike dare venture into the Stormhill Evergaol and face its relentless knight in battle Stormhill Evergaol is a Location in Elden Ring. The Stormhill Evergaol is found in Stormhill - Limgrave, by traveling to the western area and locating a mysterious circle summoning altar. The center of the circular platform can be examined which will prompt the choice to enter or not in Stormhill Evergaol, if you accept, you will enter to another dimension surrounded by an energy shield not allowing you to escape. Then you must defeat the Crucible Knight.

name: Stormhill Shack
description: The Stormhill Shack is a dilapidated shelter formerly used to house hunters in the area. A Site of Grace offers a needed moment of rest for those traveling nearby Stormhill Shack is a Location in Elden Ring. Stormhill Shack is found in Stormhill, shortly after clearing the Stormgate section. Players can find some respite at this location's Site of Grace before venturing forth into the storm.

name: Stranded Graveyard
description: Stranded Graveyard is a dark and secluded location within the Cave of Knowledge. The confused and aimless dwell within

name: Summonwater Village
description: D, Hunter of The Dead, warns you of this nearby village taken over by death, known as Summonwater Village Summonwater Village is a Location in Elden Ring. Summonwater Village is found in the northeast part of Limgrave, flooded and in ruins. The Summonwater Village is hinted at by D, Hunter of The Dead, who warns you that death has taken over the nearby village and its inhabitants.

name: Third Church Of Marika
description: The Ruins of an Old Church found in the Mistwood. The most prominent sight here is a statue of a lady with her arms outstretched

name: Warmaster's Shack
description: Small shack in a remote area near north-central Stormhill.

name: Waypoint Ruins
description: Waypoint Ruins consists of a group of broken buildings and abandoned campsites, now overrun with poisonous flowers and their crazed caretaker Waypoint Ruins is a Location in Elden Ring. The Waypoint Ruins is found in Western Limgrave. It can be reached by either going southeast from Agheel Lake North site of grace or going north from Agheel Lake South site of grace.

name: Ailing Village
description: A small, abandoned village nestled within a forested area north of the Castle Morne Rampart. This village is host to long-dilapidated dwellings, inhabited only by hostile Demi-humans.

name: Callu Baptismal Church
description: A dilapidated church, presumably frequented by the former residents of Ailing Village. Now it lies in ruin, its congregation replaced by a family of mutant vermin feasting on the remains of unfortunate travelers

name: Church Of Pilgrimage
description: The Church of Pilgrimage is a broken building situated at the top of the cliff in the north of the Weeping Peninsula. Even with the walls and roof destroyed pilgrims still make the journey to visit this church

name: Castle Morne
description: Remants of a chaos swept castle, teeming with iron-clad enemies -now engulfed with fire, piles of remains and ruin. Castle Morne is a Location in Elden Ring. It is found on the southernmost tip of the Weeping Peninsula. Players would find the castle hard to miss, as the road leads directly to it, and going for the Map (Weeping Peninsula) would bring them into its ruined outer bailey.

name: Demi-human Forest Ruins
description: Demi-Humans congregate here to worship their queen. Defeating her will reward players with the Demi-Human Queen's Staff, which is excellent for beginner mages.

name: Earthbore Cave
description: Earthbore Cave is a small dark cave on the side of the Cliffside between Limgrave and Weeping Peninsula. One might be able to hear the squeaks of rats and the snoring of a large beast deep within if you listen closely Earthbore Cave is a Location in Elden Ring. The Earthbore Cave is found in the north side of Weeping Peninsula, to the west and down the hill from the Lookout Tower. Looking outside the cave players can see the water separating the Weeping Peninsula from Limgrave.

name: Forest Lookout Tower
description: A run-down tower built on the edge of the cliffs of the Weeping Peninsula, located west of the Bridge of Sacrifice.

name: Impaler's Catacombs
description: The Impaler's Catacombs are found in the east side of the Weeping Peninsula. Once used to store the bodies of the dead, it is now crawling with Imps. Impaler's Catacombs is a Location in Elden Ring. The Impaler's Catacombs is found in the north eastern side of Weeping Peninsula. The entrance to the Impaler's Catacombs are a set of doors set against a very large cliff wall on the eastern side of the Weeping Peninsula, easily spotted by following the edge of the cliffs while looking inland.

name: Fourth Church Of Marika
description: The ruins of a lonely church, sitting atop a plateau west of the peninsula. Despite its current state, the altar remains intact and ghostly knights still roam the fields nearby, perhaps restless and duty-bound to safeguarding the area...

name: Minor Erdtree (weeping Peninsula)
description: One of the large Erdtree's found in the Weeping Peninsula. An Erdtree Avatar charges at those who approach

name: Isolated Merchant's Shack
description: Found at the western edge of the Weeping Peninsula, this lonesome hut is home to but a single person who has long adapted to a life of seclusion

name: Oridys's Rise
description: A lone observation tower atop a plateau in the east of the Weeping Peninsula. Long since abandoned, the entrance is barred by a seal, presenting travelers with a small challenge

name: Morne Tunnel
description: A dark and hidden tunnel that is inhabited by Misbegottens and Miners. Morne Tunnel is a Location in Elden Ring. The Morne Tunnel can be found in Weeping Peninsula. To reach it start from the South of the Tower grace in Weeping Peninsula then head West and finally South around the mountain. Go past the Poisonous Flowers to get to the tunnel entrance. Map Link

name: Tombsward Cave
description: Hidden cave in the forest teeming with poison-filled creatures. Tombsward Cave is a Location in Elden Ring. The Tombsward Cave is found in the Weeping Peninsula, just to the south of the Weeping Evergaol. It is hidden among a densely forested area of the cliff face. The cave features a large area with poisonous swamps.

name: Tombsward Ruins
description: The ruins of a former burial ground. Next to nothing remains here, yet squires still roam the dark tunnels beneath. Perhaps protecting the graves of their former noble masters..

name: Tombsward Catacombs
description: The Tombsward Catacombs are hidden inside the mountain near the Minor Erdtree in the Weeping Peninsula. Once filled with the bodies of the dead, armed skeletons now rise to chase away those that wish to explore its depths. Tombsward Catacombs is a Location in Elden Ring. The Tombsward Catacombs is found in Weeping Peninsula. The entrance to the Tombsward Catacombs can be found by moving directly south from the Church of Pilgrimage, towards the Minor Erdtree. Look for the set of doors leading into the mountain, hidden behind a stone pillar.

name: Tower Of Return
description: A dilapidated tower guarded by foot soldiers and mounted cavalry. Makeshift wooden platforms and ladders line the inside of the tower, allowing it to retain some function as a lookout point and a mount for ballistae

name: Weeping Evergaol
description: An evergaol located on the western landmass of the Weeping Peninsula. A formidable opponent is imprisoned within Weeping Evergaol is a Location in Elden Ring. The Weeping Evergaol is found at the Weeping Peninsula far to the northwest. This location is highly accessible on foot or on horseback as it is out in the open field. The gaol's distinct circular construction is easily visible from far away.

name: Witchbane Ruins
description: A set of ruins found in western Weeping Peninsula. Overgrown with thick shrubs and poisonous flowers, this decrepit landmark invites only misery and dread.

name: Academy Crystal Cave
description: The depths of the Raya Lucaria Academy are rich in rose-tinted crystals, imbued with the natural magic of the area Academy Crystal Cave is a Location in Elden Ring. The Academy Crystal Cave is found in Liurnia of the Lakes. The entrance is found west of the Raya Lucaria Academy.

name: Academy Gate Town
description: The sunken remains of the academy town

name: Ainsel River Well
description: A small structure housing a lift that takes you down to the Ainsel River.

name: Artist's Shack
description: A small cabin at North Liurnia of The Lakes. Its strongly perceived tranquility seems overshadowed by oblivion.

name: Bellum Church
description: Located past the ruins and the forested area guarded by Mounted Knights.

name: Bellum Highway
description: Outside the East Raya Lucaria Gate

name: Black Knife Catacombs
description: Black Knife Catacombs homes many skeletons and crabs within its depths, find and defeat the Black Knife Assassin within to obtain their dagger.

name: Caria Manor
description: A large estate situated far to the north of Liurnia. Caria Manor is a Location in Elden Ring. The Caria Manor is a large estate found in Liurnia of the Lakes, far to the north. Players can get to the manor by following the main road on the western landmass heading north. Caria Manor is a major dungeon that is heavily guarded and contains many things of note. Defeating the boss and completing this dungeon is required in order to access the northeast sub-region of Three Sisters behind the estate.

name: Boilprawn Shack
description: Small cozy shack where Blackguard Big Boggart resides.

name: Carian Study Hall
description: A large library-like location full of spectres Carian Study Hall is a Location in Elden Ring. The Carian Study Hall is found in the Liurnia of the Lakes region. Take the Elevator up from the Study Hall Entrance Sites of Grace. Although you will be able to access this area immediately, using the Carian Inverted Statue (obtained through Ranni the Witch's quest) on the pedestal near the beginning of the map will unlock an alternative version of this map.

name: Chapel Of Anticipation
description: A small starting building with trail leading to an area occupied by a gnarly Grafted Scion Chapel of Anticipation is a Location in Stormveil Castle, Limgrave in Elden Ring. The Chapel of Anticipation is the starting building players are placed in after the game introduction. Players find themselves in a destroyed chapel, and will soon find themselves attacked by a grotesque Scion.

name: Chelona's Rise
description: A tower overlooking the southern-most tip of Liurnia of the lakes

name: Church Of Inhibition
description: The remnants of an old church in the north of Liurnia, just before the Altus Plateau.

name: Cathedral Of Manus Celes
description: A large church atop the southern plateau of Liurnia. Cathedral of Manus Celes is a Location in Elden Ring. The Cathedral of Manus Celes is found at the Moonlight Altar plateau, high above in the southwest Liurnia of the Lakes. The Moonlight Altar is accessible only after making significant progress in Ranni's questline, including defeating Astel, Naturalborn of the Void in the Grand Cloister and gaining access to the lift in the Deep Ainsel Well, which leads up to the plateau. Players can reach the Cathedral of Manus Celes by heading northeast from the Moonlight Altar site of grace.

name: Church Of Irith
metadata: {"image": "https://eldenring.fanapis.com/images/locations/17f69eb0b5al0i2mfvs8tpdxql60r.png", "region": "Limgrave", "Liurnia of the Lakes": "A peaceful church at the back of Stormveil Castle."}

name: Church Of Vows
description: It is here, at the Church of Vows, that the great houses of the Erdtree and the Moon were joined by the matrimonial bond between red-haired Radagon and Rennala of the Full Moon. That is why it holds in view the monuments of both houses, the Erdtree of the Capital and the Academy of Raya Lucaria. Church of Vows is a Location in Elden Ring. The Church of Vows is found in Liurnia of the Lakes, atop a plateau on the eastern landmass. It can be accessed by following the roads heading north along the eastern landmass. An alternate route is available by way of a Waygate from Raya Lucaria Academy. The Church of Vows is home to Miriel, Pastor of Vows, a giant amicable turtle that can speak.

name: Converted Fringe Tower
description: A tower found on the fringe in the northeastern tip of Liurnia.

name: Converted Tower
description: An abandoned tower

name: Cuckoo's Evergaol
description: Evergaol located on the western landmass of Liurnia. A powerful force stirs within. Cuckoo's Evergaol is a Location in Elden Ring. The Cuckoo's Evergaol is found in western Liurnia of the Lakes. Players can reach this location by following the northern main road from the Minor Erdtree.

name: Deep Ainsel Well
description: A deep well leading to the Moonlight Altar from the underground Grand Cloister.

name: Divine Tower Of Liurnia
description: Divine Tower of Liurnia is a Location in Elden Ring. The Divine Tower of Liurnia is found in Liurnia of the Lakes and is reached by taking the lift down at the secret area of Carian Study Hall.

name: Frenzied Flame Village
description: A village in Liurnia gripped in the madness of Three Fingers. Its denizens know nothing but the fiery frenzy burning within them

name: Grand Lift Of Dectus
description: A massive lift platform found between Liurnia and the Altus Plateau. The mechanism that operates the lift is barred by four Guardian Statues, requiring the brandishing of a special artifact for them to release their hold

name: Highway Lookout Tower
description: A lone tower overlooking the Liurnia main road on the eastern landmass

name: Jarburg
description: Jarburg was a peaceful village, but the effects of the Shattering affected even the otherwise amicable Living Jar Jarburg is a Location in Elden Ring. Jarburg is found in Liurnia of the Lakes. To reach this area, go to the Artist's Shack and head to the cliff just south of Carian Study Hall. There's no direct path, you need to jump from the cliff down the stone platforms to get there.

name: Kingsrealm Ruins
description: A ruined area, only seemingly bare. Kingsrealm Ruins is a Location in Elden Ring. The Kingsrealm Ruins is found in the northwest of Liurnia of the Lakes. The area is easily accessible on foot or on horseback by following the main road along the western landmass.

name: Lakeside Crystal Cave
description: Hidden on the southwestern cliffs of Liurnia of the Lakes, a winding cave carved by large crystals Lakeside Crystal Cave is a Location in Elden Ring. The Lakeside Crystal Cave is found within the southern region of Liurnia of the Lakes, directly south from the Scenic Isle Site of Grace.

name: Laskyar Ruins
description: Ruins of a sunken structure beset by fog, found amidst the marshes of south Liurnia.

name: Lunar Estate Ruins
description: The ruins of a large estate found atop the southwestern plateau of Liurnia.

name: Malefactor's Evergaol
description: An evergaol overlooking the vast lakes. An ever burning flame resides within Malefactor's Evergaol is a Location in Elden Ring. The Malefactor's Evergaol is found in Liurnia of the Lakes, on the long stretch of land in the southern landmass. To get to this location, players can take a spirit spring a bit west of the Liurnia Lake Shore Site of Grace. You can also approach the southern landmass from the southwestern side of the marshes and then travel east.

name: Minor Erdtree (liurnia Southwest)
metadata: {"image": "https://eldenring.fanapis.com/images/locations/17f69f56f55l0i2mhypmucze7mfrzc.png", "region": "Limgrave", "Liurnia of the Lakes": "This ancient Erdtree overlooks the lakes from the southwest"}

name: Moonfolk Ruins
description: Ruins found in the southwest of the Liurnia of the Lakes region

name: Purified Ruins
description: The holy remains now lie in ruin

name: Ranni's Rise
description: A tower beset by large chunks of glintstone emerging from the ground and penetrating its interiors. Home to a mysterious figure observing The Lands Between Ranni's Rise is a Location in Elden Ring. Ranni's Rise is one of three towers found in the Three Sisters sub-region of Liurnia of the Lakes. The tower is found in the western section of Three Sisters. When first visiting the area, this is the only tower that is initially accessible.

name: Raya Lucaria Crystal Tunnel
description: One of the vast networks of tunnels used prominently for the academy's crystal mining operation.

name: Renna's Rise
description: A Tower of the Three Sisters, belonging to Renna. It houses Ranni's Snow Witch Armor Set

name: Revenger's Shack
description: An isolated shack north of the Minor Erdtree. Bodies litter the ground inside the shack, possibly belonging to those one has taken revenge upon

name: Ringleader's Evergaol
description: An evergaol where a nortorious assassin is incarcerated

name: Road's End Catacombs
description: Catacombs at the end of the world.. Road's End Catacombs is a Location in Elden Ring. The Road's End Catacombs is found in Liurnia of the Lakes. South of Revenger's Shack, take a pathway past the Ghost Jellyfishes, keep going until the end and you will reach a door that leads to the Road's End Catacombs.

name: Rose Church
description: The ruins of a former church aptly named Rose Church, for its walls are now festering with scarlet rot and overgrown with bloodroses.

name: Royal Grave Evergaol
description: An evergaol constructed for the Carian Royal family in the plains east of the royal estate Royal Grave Evergaol is a Location in Elden Ring. The Royal Grave Evergaol is found in Liurnia of the Lakes, to the east of Caria Manor. This area becomes accessible only after completing the manor and defeating Royal Knight Loretta. The Onyx Lord is imprisoned within.

name: Ruin-strewn Precipice
description: A steep precipice with abundant caves in the insides all the way through Ruin-Strewn Precipice is a Location in Elden Ring. The Ruin-Strewn Precipice is found in Liurnia of The Lakes. It is an alternative way to the Altus Plateau instead of the Grand Lift of Dectus. Its entrance is through the Miners' caves, accessed through the various stairs and platforms above Ravine-Vailed Village. It is full of Giant Bats and Vulgar Militiamen, with Miners in the inside of the caves and Land Octopuses towards the top.

name: Seluvis's Rise
description: A tower bequeathed unto Preceptor Seluvis. Serves as his personal study as he delves into the sorcerous arts. Seluvis's Rise is a Location in Elden Ring. Seluvis's Rise is one of three towers found in the Three Sisters sub-region of Liurnia of the Lakes. This tower is found in the southwest section of Three Sisters. The entrance is initially blocked until you speak to Ranni at Ranni's Rise for the first time.

name: Slumbering Wolf's Shack
description: A small shack nestled at the side of a cliff, only accessible through a long winding cave system. A woman and her wolf companion rest here.

name: Stillwater Cave
description: A dark and murky cave beset by a poisonous miasma. Home to servants of rot, relishing in the presence of the giant poisonblooms endemic to the cave Stillwater Cave is a Location in Elden Ring. The Stillwater Cave is found in Liurnia of the Lakes. Players can find the cave entrance by descending down the southern plateau from the Stormveil Castle passage that leads to the lake-facing cliffs of Liurnia. Look for 2 Spirit Jellyfish around the jagged, craggy hills to find the cave below the cliffs.

name: Temple Quarter
description: Ruined by the breaking, the Temple Quarter is now overrun with dangerous creatures, ready to attack any who come near

name: Testu's Rise
description: An observation tower found in the middle of a lone isle in Liurnia. The entrance is sealed by impish magic and presents a challenge to would-be visitors

name: The Four Belfries
description: As its name suggests, The Four Belfries is a hill with four large bell towers overlooking Liurnia from the west. Each belfry hosts a waygate that transports travelers to various locations

name: Village Of The Albinaurics
description: The cursemongers have destroyed the Village of the Albinaurics, but perhaps their hope to reach the promised city is not yet lost Village of the Albinaurics is a Location in Elden Ring. The Village of the Albinaurics is found in Liurnia of the Lakes, by exploring the swamp area on the south-western shores. There is a slope (just SSW of the "Folly on the Lake" Site of Grace) heading to the village that is now adorned with corpses and carcasses, as the cursemongers have taken over the location.

name: Abandoned Cave
description: Long time abandoned cave. Abandoned Cave is a Location in Elden Ring. Abandoned Cave is located in Dragonbarrow, Caelid, east of Smoldering Wall Grace on the eastern wall of the canyon, and slightly northwest of the Sellia Evergaol. The location is only reachable by approaching from the west and crossing the canyon using a tree.

name: Caelem Ruins
description: A set of perpetually burning ruins in western Caelid. The Caelid Highway cuts through these ruins which are heavily guarded by mobile flamethrowers and swarming with burning reanimated corpses

name: Caelid Catacombs
description: A labyrinth of Scarlet Rot-soaked floors and tunnels.

name: Caelid Waypoint Ruins
description: A set of ruins found in southwest Caelid, along the highway. Long abandoned, the ruins have become home to all manner of creatures that revel in the decay and putrefaction brought on by the scarlet rot

name: Aeonia Swamp
description: The Swamp of Aeonia is nestled in the center of the Caelid region. What were once flourishing plains filled with rich flora and fauna are now reduced to a cesspool of death and decay. A high concentration of the dreaded scarlet rot has mutated the very earth itself, twisting the creatures and plant life that once called this home.

name: Cathedral Of Dragon Communion (caelid)
description: The Cathedral of Dragon Communion has long been destroyed, but those who seek to commune with draconic power may yet access its power

name: Church Of The Plague
description: A dilapidated church found in the cliffs east of Sellia, Town of Sorcery

name: Fort Gael
description: A ruined fort in a ruined land, Fort Gael is a Location in Elden Ring. The Fort Gael is found in Caelid, due south of Rotview balcony. It is a heavily guarded Fort, protected by knights and soldiers of Redmane, as well as magical beings. Some treasures can be found within the fort.

name: Gael Tunnel
description: A set of tunnels found on the western edge of Caelid, along the border to Limgrave Gael Tunnel is a Location in Elden Ring. The Gael Tunnel is found in Caelid. Located in the border between Limgrave and Caelid.

name: Forsaken Ruins
description: The Forsaken Ruins consists of a group of broken buildings and abandoned campsites. It is located in Caelid and is gaurded by a Giant Crow

name: Gaol Cave
description: Found at the west of Caelid. Gaol Cave is a Location in Elden Ring. The Gaol Cave is found in Caelid. It can be found in the scarlet lake East of Fort Gael. It can only be accessed using two Stonesword Keys to break an Imp Statue seal.

name: Gowry's Shack
description: A lone shack found below the eastern hills near Sellia, Town of Sorcery.

name: Minor Erdtree Catacombs
description: Minor Erdtree Catacombs is a Location in Elden Ring. The Minor Erdtree Catacombs is found in Caelid, beneath the Minor Erdtree. Players can reach this location by traveling east from where the region meets with Limgrave and then looking for the entrance behind the tree, in the north.

name: Redmane Castle
description: A small castle that is heavily guarded at the castle's outskirts by Radahn Knights and Soldiers. The Redmane Castle serves as the gathering point for warriors alike who are wanting to participate in the Radahn Festival Redmane Castle is a Location in Elden Ring. The Redmane Castle is found in Caelid. It can be reached by crossing the bridge in-front of the "Impassable Greatbridge" site of grace. Follow the path upwards to the castle gate. Circle behind the castle using the path on the right hand side. After disposing of some enemies, there is a gap that you must jump across, it is recommended to use your mount for this section. There will be a small series of stairs leading to a shortcut, a door that can be opened only from the other side. To access the castle itself, you must climb up the ladder near said shortcut.

name: Minor Erdtree (caelid)
description: The Minor Erdtree of Caelid, found in the northwest near the border to Limgrave.

name: Sellia Crystal Tunnel
description: The crystal mining operation of Sellia is overseen by greedy and aggressive insectoids Sellia Crystal Tunnel is a Location in Elden Ring. The Sellia Crystal Tunnel is found in Caelid. You can reach this location (and by extension Caelid) early by opening the chest [Elden Ring Map Link] in Dragon-Burnt Ruins. It will envelop you in smoke and transport you to the mine.

name: Sellia Evergaol
description: Outside of Sellia Evergaol Sellia Evergaol is a Location in Elden Ring. The Sellia Evergaol is found in Dragonbarrow.

name: Sellia Gateway
description: The gateway leading to Sellia, Town of Socrcery

name: Sellia, Town Of Sorcery
description: A once-great town renowned for its study of the sorcerous arts. Now lying in ruin, the ghosts of its former scholars still roam the streets. Sellia, Town of Sorcery is a Location in Elden Ring. The Sellia, Town of Sorcery is found in eastern Caelid. Players can reach this location by following the Caelid Highway to the east and then heading north.

name: Shack Of The Rotting
description: An old worn-down shack overlooking a long stretch of cliffs in western Caelid.

name: Street Of Sages Ruins
description: The sages of Caelid are no more, and their former district is now the dwelling of perfumers and their poisonous flowers

name: War-dead Catacombs
description: Catacombs for those who have died a glorious battle death

name: Capital Outskirts
description: Capital Outskirts is a Location in Elden Ring. The Capital Outskirts sub-region lies in the Eastern area of the Altus Plateau and is the region just outside Leyndell, Royal Capital but still within the capital's outer walls. Beware of Skeletons rising from their graves and rocks flying out of the capital toward the battlegrounds when exploring the area. Capital Outskirts is a Location in Elden Ring. The Capital Outskirts sub-region lies in the Eastern area of the Altus Plateau and is the region just outside Leyndell, Royal Capital but still within the capital's outer walls. It also covers the bridges located between the lift southeast of East Capital Rampart and Forbidden Lands (this part of Capital Outskirts is initially sealed by Morgott, the Omen King and will be unlocked after defeating him).

name: Altus Tunnel
description: The Altus tunnels were once used to supply the lands with quality crystals

name: Dominula, Windmill Village
description: Dominula, Windmill Village is a Location in Elden Ring. The Dominula, Windmill Village is found in Altus Plateau. East of the "Road of iniquity Side Path"sight of grace. Follow the main path southeast then bend east.

name: East Windmill Pasture
description: East Pasture Outskirsts of Windmill Village. True to its name, it can be identified by the still-working windmill placed in the center of the pasture.

name: Golden Lineage Evergaol
description: An evergaol located on within the Altus Plateau. Golden Lineage Evergaol is a Location in Elden Ring. The Golden Lineage Evergaol is found in Altus Plateau. It is in the far southwest of the region, right by Grand Lift of Dectus. It is in an area the requires you to follow a specific pathway to access, while jumping down the cliffside will usually result in death. You must spend one Stonesword Key to unlock it.

name: Hermit Merchant's Shack
description: Nestled on a cliff within the confines of the Royal Capital, this shack is home to a humble merchant, who has chosen a life of seclusion

name: Leyndell, Royal Capital
description: Leyndell, Royal Capital is a Location in Elden Ring. The Leyndell, Royal Capital region is only accessible to players who have gathered two Great Runes or by following Ranni the Witch quest line and defeating Fia's Champions near the Great Waterfall Crest Site of Grace in the Deeproot Depths, and has content for highly leveled gameplay. For a detailed walkthrough, please visit the walkthrough page for Leyndell, Royal Capital Legacy Dungeon here.

name: Lux Ruins
description: Long forgotten ruins among golden trees, swarmed with demi-humans protecting the undergound chamber. Lux Ruins is a Location in Elden Ring. The Lux Ruins can be reached by exploring the western cliffs of Altus Plateau.

name: Old Altus Tunnel
description: An old mining site, still active to this day. Its tunnels echo with the grunts and groans of the commoners, tirelessly slaving away, grinding at the rich reservoir of crystals deep within

name: Minor Erdtree Church
description: What's left of the Church of the Minor Erdtree

name: Sealed Tunnel
description: Not as small or abandoned as it looks. Sealed Tunnel is a Location in Elden Ring. The Sealed Tunnel is found in Capital Outskirts. Down at south of the lake right next to the (closed) west gate to Leyndell Royal Capital. Jump down the bridge of land that separates the two lakes and continue south to access.

name: Stormcaller Church
description: A lonely church on a steppe

name: The Shaded Castle
description: An abandoned and Decrepit castle found in the northern region between the Mt. Gelmir and the Altus Plateau regions. The castle is half sunken into a poisonous bog, with the air tinged yellow by the fumes. The Shaded Castle is a Location in Elden Ring. The Shaded Castle is found in Altus Plateau. A castle found in the northern region of the Altus Plateau. Head north through the valley between the Mt. Gelmir and Altus Plateau regions, heading north from the Altus Tunnel to find your way to the Castle.

name: Woodfolk Ruins
description: Woodfolk Ruins, guarded by Limgrave's creatures, can be found near the Minor Erdtree within Altus Plateau.

name: Corpse-stench Shack
description: A run-down shack amidst burning corpses past the site of a recent battle.

name: Writheblood Ruins
description: Writheblood ruins, with nearest minor erdtree in background Writheblood Ruins is a Location in Elden Ring. The Writheblood Ruins is found in Altus Plateau. Two sequential jumping platforms are found just north of Mirage Rise, take these and head briefly eastward to arrive at Writheblood Ruins; or follow the path east from the Bridge of Iniquity site of grace.

name: Craftsman's Shack
description: A series of long-abandoned huts found directly south of the volcano

name: Gelmir Hero's Grave
description: Large Catacombs housing an ancient hero of Mt. Gelmir. Gelmir Hero's Grave is a Location in Elden Ring. The Gelmir Hero's Grave is found in Mt. Gelmir, high above the center of the region. Players can get to the entrance of these catacombs by heading northwest from the Bridge of Iniquity site of grace, climbing up the rope ladder to the First Mt. Gelmir Campsite site of grace and heading around west. Alternatively, you can reach the catacombs by walking along the long jagged rock extending from the north of Hermit Village over the chasm (use the Primeval Sorcerer Azur Site of Grace).

name: Hermit's Shack
description: An abandoned shack along the western edge of Mt. Gelmir

name: Fort Laiedd
description: Fort Laiedd is found on the western edge of Mt. Gelmir. A fort left broken, still occupied by those who won the battle Fort Laiedd is a Location in Elden Ring. Fort Laiedd is found on the western edge of Mt. Gelmir. This location can be reached by jumping into the ravine west of Wyndham Ruins and following it around the base of the mountain all the way to the northwest. Once you reach the Seethewater Terminus Site of Grace, the fort is just a straight shot west from there.

name: Perfumer's Ruins
description: A set of ruins found in Altus Plateau, far to the west and below Mt. Gelmir.

name: Hermit Village
description: A dilapidated village southeast of Mt. Gelmir. Now home to Demi-Humans. Hermit Village is a Location in Elden Ring. The Hermit Village is found in Mt. Gelmir, southeast of the volcano. Players can reach this location by first traveling around the volcano starting from the ravine west of Wyndham Ruins, following it all the way around to the Seethewater Terminus site of grace in the northwest. From here, head south past the lake of magma until you reach the Craftsman's Shack. The village is just up the hill east of the shack.

name: Sage's Cave
description: Sage's Cave is a dark opening in the side of a mountain. Its dark depths are overrun by hostile undead, but those who brave it may find treasures beyond compare Sage's Cave is a Location in Elden Ring. The Sage's Cave is found in Altus Plateau, west of Wyndham Ruins, under the cliffs. The cave's entrance can easily be reached by heading northeast from the Abandoned Coffin site of grace, past a large cluster of Poison Flowers.

name: Second Church Of Marika
description: Second of the four Churches of Marika where players can gather a Sacred Tear for their flask.

name: Unsightly Catacombs
description: A burial grounds crawling with Misbegotten creatures found deep beneath the Perfumer's Ruins. Despite its decrepit state, the catacombs give off a trace of fragrant aromas juxtaposed by the scent of the ancient dead Unsightly Catacombs is a Location in Elden Ring. The Unsightly Catacombs is found in Altus Plateau. Players can reach this location by first traveling to the Perfumer's Ruins by heading west from the Abandoned Coffin site of grace. The entrance to the catacombs is found below the ruins, with the door attached to the cliff face in the southwest.

name: Seethewater Cave
description: A cave found along the Seethewater Ravine. Seethewater Cave is a Location in Elden Ring. The Seethewater Cave is found in Mt. Gelmir. You can reach it by heading north through the ravine west of Wyndham Ruins. Be careful of the fire geysers as you make your way there. You'll need two Stonesword Keys to unlock the entrance of the cave.

name: Wyndham Catacombs
description: Burial grounds located beneath Wyndham Ruins. Wyndham Catacombs is a Location in Elden Ring. The Wyndham Catacombs is found in Altus Plateau, at the south of the jagged rocky mountains leading up to Mt. Gelmir. The entrance to the catacombs can be found at the very top of Wyndham Ruins, pressed against the side of a cliff.

name: Volcano Cave
description: A cave system at the highest point of Mt. Gelmir, made into a home by a family of Demi-Humans hiding their maddened Queen. Volcano Cave is a Location in Elden Ring. The Volcano Cave is found in Mt. Gelmir, in the north. Players can reach this location by travelling to the Ninth Mt. Gelmir Campsite Site of Grace and passing the nearby bridge, then hugging the cliff as you travel along the pass north, passing some soldiers and some demi-humans. The cave will be in the cliff on your left.

name: Wyndham Ruins
description: A large set of ruins atop a burial grounds. The reanimated dead still roam the area

name: Bestial Sanctum
description: The Beastial Sanctum is a refuge for those who feed on the dead. Beastly and deformed, the clergyman here will teach the ways of the beast to those who feed it

name: Dragonbarrow Cave
description: A small dungeon found beneath the Minor Erdtree in Dragonbarrow

name: Divine Tower Of Caelid
description: A massive tower found in central Dragonbarrow, north of Caelid. The sides of the tower are crumbling from the massive overgrowth protruding from the plateau

name: Deep Siofra Well
description: A second lift to the Siofra River.

name: Fort Faroth
description: Fort Faroth used to house the guardians of Caelid, but its defenders have long fallen, now bound to earth as hostile spirits

name: Lenne's Rise
description: An observation tower in the northeast of Dragonbarrow, off the path to the Bestial Sanctum

name: Isolated Merchant's Shack (dragonbarrow)
description: A lonesome hut found atop a plateau in western Dragonbarrow. Home to a hermit looking to part with various odds and ends... for a price

name: Castle Sol
description: A castle found in the northeast of the Mountaintops of the Giants. Stronghold of Commander Niall and his spectral knights Castle Sol is a Location in Elden Ring. The Castle Sol is found in Mountaintops of the Giants in the northeast. Players can reach this location by crossing the northern bridge from Stargazer's Ruins or from the Minor Erdtree (Mountaintops East).

name: Church Of Repose
description: A small crumbled church high on the mountains

name: Forge Of The Giants
description: The giant's forge could contain a volcano.

name: Grand Lift Of Rold
description: The impressive Lift of Rold transports those who wield the right key. But could there be more than one destination??

name: Guardians' Garrison
description: Guardian's Garrison is staffed by Fire Priests, who zealously watch the road leading to the Giant's Forge

name: Giant-conquering Hero's Grave
description: A complex dungeon filled with invulnerable enemies and strange golden floor seals.

name: Shack Of The Lofty
description: A lone shack found in the Mountaintops of the Giants. This shack was once visited by a traveling maiden, but she had long since perished under the elements

name: Spiritcaller's Cave
description: A cave found by the Freezing Lake, heavily battered by the elements

name: Stargazer's Ruins
description: A set of ruins found in central Mountaintops of the Giants. The plateau it is sitting on is located between two bridges. Stargazers' Ruins is a Location in Elden Ring. The Stargazers' Ruins is found in Mountaintops of the Giants. Players can reach this location by traversing the central Mountaintops either from the south or north. There are bridges to the plateau in directions.

name: Zamor Ruins
description: The ancient Town of Zamor, now fallen to ruin. Its anzient order of knights still roam the snow-capped streets

name: Consecrated Snowfield Catacombs
description: The Catacombs of the fields leading to Miquella's Haligtree hide powerful secrets, but are zealously guarded Consecrated Snowfield Catacombs is a Location in Elden Ring. The Consecrated Snowfield Catacombs is found among the eastern cliffs of the Consecrated Snowfields, by exploring the eastern area of the sub-region.

name: Apostate Derelict
description: A ruined church lying in the frozen north-west of the Consecrated Grounds

name: Heretical Rise
description: The secrets of Heretical Rise are closely guarded by hidden magic, but the tower is overrun with hostile Avionette Soldiers

name: Hidden Path To The Haligtree
description: The secret passage leading to Miquella's Haligtree has been polluted by Those Who Live in Dead Hidden Path to the Haligtree is a Location in Elden Ring. The Hidden Path to the Haligtree is found in the Forbidden Lands. This location is accessed by activating the Grand Lift of Rold with both the Haligtree Secret Medallion (Left) and Haligtree Secret Medallion (Right).

name: Yelough Anix Ruins
description: A set of ruins found in the northwest of the Consecrated Snowfield

name: Ordina, Liturgical Town
description: Ghost town inhabitated in the evergaol

name: Yelough Anix Tunnel
description: An icy tunnel on the southern edge of the Yelough Anix Ruins Yelough Anix Tunnel is a Location in Elden Ring. The Yelough Anix Tunnel is found in the west of the Consecrated Snowfield. The entrance can be found on the cliff face to the south of the Yelough Anix Ruins.

name: Abductor Virgins
description: Deadly mechanical constructs who wield massive blades. Abductor Virgins is a Field Boss in Elden Ring. These two deadly constructs are found beneath Volcano Manor. This is an optional boss as players do not have to defeat it to advance in Elden Ring. Abductor Virgin is the normal enemy version of this boss.

description: Remarkably agile and aggressive warrior. Dangerous even for those with shield coverage... Alecto, Black Knife Ringleader is a Boss in Elden Ring. She is the ringleader of the Black Knives Plot, imprisoned within Ringleader's Evergaol. On the Night of the Black Knives, Alecto and the Black Knife Assassins assassinated Godwyn the Golden using daggers imbued with a fragment of Destined Death stolen from its caretaker, Maliketh. During their escape from Leyndell, Alecto's daughter, Tiche, perished protecting her.

description: Remarkably agile and aggressive warrior. Dangerous even for those with shield coverage...

name: Alabaster Lord
description: An Evergaol prisoner wielding a vicious sword and the void with murderous intent.
metadata: {"image": "https://eldenring.fanapis.com/images/bosses/17f69b85929l0i1ukc4l2up7yp9v0i.png", "region": "Liurnia of the Lakes", "location": "Royal Grave Evergaol, Liurnia of the Lakes", "drops": ["3.600 Runes", "Meteorite"], "healthPoints": "???"}

name: Adan, Thief Of Fire
description: An evergaol prisoner and former battle mage, Adan wields a spiked flail and uses stolen knowledge of fire magic to great effect. Adan, Thief of Fire is a Field Boss in Elden Ring. Adan, Thief of Fire is an evergaol prisoner found in the Malefactor's Evergaol in southern Liurnia of the Lakes. Adan is a stout battle mage wielding a spiked flail and utilizes fire magic. This is an optional boss as players are not required to defeat it to advance in Elden Ring.

name: Ancient Dragon Lansseax
description: Lansseax was the sister of Fortissax. It is said that she took the from of a human to commune with the knights as a priestess of the ancient dragon cult. Ancient Dragon Lansseax is a Great Enemy Boss in Elden Ring. This ancient, four-winged ancient dragon is the sister of Fortissax and had connections to the people of the Golden Order as her brother did. This is an optional boss, as players don't need to defeat it in order to advance in Elden Ring.

name: Ancestor Spirit
description: A glowing spirit that takes the form of a large deer, making it a menacing threat when charging at targets. Ancestor Spirit is a Great Enemy Boss in Elden Ring. This animated carcass of a deer-like creature is encountered in the Hallowhorn Grounds found in Siofra River. This is an optional boss, as players don't need to defeat it in order to advance in Elden Ring.

description: Noticeably agile, frost-made creature suceptible to magic attacks. Ancient Hero of Zamor is a Field Boss in Elden Ring. Ancient Hero of Zamor is an agile swordwielder that uses frost magic and is found in multiple locations. This is an optional boss, as players don't have to defeat it to advance to the Legacy Dungeon.

name: Beast Clergyman
description: Temporarily overtaken by their bestial rage, the Beast Clergyman attacks ferociously, throwing rocks and themselves at their foes. Calm their aggression and return them to their senses. Beast Clergyman is a Boss in Elden Ring. He is the boss form of Gurranq Beast Clergyman. This Elden Ring Beast Clergyman Guide features boss locations, tips, strategies and videos on how to defeat the Beast Clergyman easily, as well as boss stats and lore for the Beast Clergyman.

name: Astel, Stars Of Darkness
description: A hostile, massive Dragon-Fly creature. Menacing and extremely powerful. Astel, Stars of Darkness is a Field Boss in Elden Ring. This giant insectoid creature is found in Yelough Anix Tunnel in the Consecrated Snowfield. This is an optional boss, as players don't need to defeat it in order to advance in Elden Ring. Astel, Naturalborn of the Void is the weaker variant of this boss.

name: Beast Of Farum Azula
description: Underground-living creature found at Groveside Cave

name: Beastman Of Farum Azula
description: The beasts of Groveside Cave rally around the prowess of the Beastman of Farum Azula Beastman of Farum Azula is a Boss in Elden Ring. The Beastmen are said to have come from a doomed city in the sky, and attack with the ferocity of a wild beast on the hunt. These are optional bosses, as players are not required to defeat them to advance in Elden Ring.

description: Menacing and slow-paced, it wields a large, red-glowing sword and a shield combined with a full body armor and a chilling cape. Bell Bearing Hunter is a recurring Field Boss in Elden Ring. He is a hunter of shopkeepers who only appears at night and features long-distance melee attacks. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat it to advance in Elden Ring.

This is an optional boss, as players don't need to defeat it in order to advance in Elden Ring. However, doing so yields useful Items and Runes.

description: The merciless bloodhounds attack with grace and agility, never backing down or giving a moment's rest. Bloodhound Knight Darriwil is a Boss in Elden Ring. description: A large feline-hound looking guardian that serves as a "Watchdog"for the Burial Tree of the Stormfoot Catacombs.

name: Cleanrot Knight
description: Powerful, dexterous Knight capable of distanced, very rapid attacks. Its spear and sword are a threat to any light-armored fighter. Cleanrot Knights are Field Bosses in Elden Ring. These tall warriors are clad in golden armor with distinct tufts of decorative crimson fur. They wield a thrusting sword, alongside a spear or a scythe and are found as bosses in various locations, often in those with Poison or Rot. They are optional bosses, as players don't need to defeat it in order to advance. However, defeating them yields useful Items and Runes.

name: Commander Niall
description: Commander Niall is a tall and built knight with a peg leg, clad in heavy armor, wielding a halberd that doubles as a battle standard. He is accompanied by two Spectral Banished Knights, one equipped with dual swords and the other equipped with a sword and shield. Commander Niall is a Great Enemy Boss in Elden Ring. Commander Niall is found in Castle Sol in Mountaintops of the Giants. This is an optional boss, as players don't need to defeat it in order to advance in Elden Ring. However, he must be defeated before entering Consecrated Snowfield.

name: Commander O'neil
description: A large and imposing human commander who wields a halberd that doubles as a battle standard, rousing his spirit minions to battle with unquenchable fervor. Commander O'Neil is a Great Enemy Boss in Elden Ring. Commander O'Neil is a human who wields a halberd with a battle standard and summons aid from ghostly warriors. These imposing knights ride atop dark steeds and appear only at night, wielding large flails and halberds. There are several Night's Cavalry that roam the Lands Between. These are optional bosses, as players don't need to defeat them in order to advance in Elden Ring.

name: Putrid Tree Spirit
description: A blood-rotted tree that has found life despite the death that consumes it. Putrid Tree Spirit is a Field Boss in Elden Ring. This rotten tree root creature is found buried in dark places throughout the Lands Between. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat it to advance in Elden Ring. The one in Elphael, Brace of the Haligtree is necessary to complete Millicent's questline.

name: Radagon Of The Golden Order
description: Lord Radagon was a great champion, possessed of flowing red locks. He came to these lands at the head of a great golden host, when he met Lady Rennala in battle. He soon repented his territorial transgressions though, and became husband to the Carian Queen. However. When Godfrey, first Elden Lord, was hounded from the Lands Between, Radagon left Rennala to return to the Erdtree Capital, becoming Queen Marika's second husband and King Consort. Taking the title... of second Elden Lord. Radagon of the Golden Order is a Boss in Elden Ring. Radagon is a tall, fractured god wielding the hammer that shattered the Elden Ring, and is found in the heart of the Erdtree. He was previously married to Rennala, but became Queen Marika's consort after Godfrey was exiled from the Lands Between. Completing Brother Corhyn & Goldmask's quest to a certain point reveals that he is the "other half" of Queen Marika. Despite being of one body, the two do not share the same will, as evident from Radagon attempting to repair the Elden Ring after Marika had shattered it. This boss is NOT optional as players must defeat him to reach the end of Elden Ring's story.

This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat it to advance in Elden Ring, though they do need to defeat it to advance further in Raya Lucaria Academy and to achieve a certain ending.

name: Royal Knight Loretta
description: The eternal guardian of Caria Manor fervently defends her domain atop the Royal Moongazing Grounds. Loretta uses her greatbow to rain destruction on all who would dare approach the estate grounds. Royal Knight Loretta is a Greater Foe Boss in Elden Ring. Royal Knight Loretta is the spirit of a knight riding atop her steed. She wields a polearm and utilizes powerful glintstone sorceries to punish would-be trespassers to her domain, the Caria Manor in northern Liurnia of the Lakes. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat her to advance in Elden Ring, though they do need to defeat her to reach the Three Sisters and achieve a certain ending.

name: Royal Revenant
description: An obscene and disturbing abomination, blend of a spider-like creature and human limbs resulting in a quite resourceful fighter at close range. Royal Revenant is a Field Boss in Elden Ring. Royal Revenant is a grotesque amalgamation of humanoid and arachnid, with its many grafted limbs. The Revenant is extremely aggressive and quick, utilizing its poison attacks to weaken prey. This is an optional boss, as players don't need to defeat it in order to advance in Elden Ring. However, doing so yields useful Items and Runes.

name: Starscourge Radahn
description: General Radahn is cursed ever to wander. Eaten from the inside, by Malenia's scarlet rot, his Wits are long gone. Now he gathers the corpses of former friends and foes alike, gorging on them, like a dog. Starscourge Radahn is a Legend Boss in Elden Ring. Starscourge Radahn is heralded as one of the mightiest living demigods, having fought Malenia the Severed to a standstill during the Shattering. However, his resulting affliction with the Scarlet Rot caused him to be driven to insanity, crippling him and reducing him to a state of feral rage. He is located in Caelid, where he can be accessed from Redmane Castle after activating the Radahn Festival by progressing far enough in Ranni's questline, or activating any site of grace in Altus Plateau.

name: Tree Sentinel
description: The heavily armored and highly decorated sentinel protects the tree. Who would dare oppose him? Tree Sentinels are Field Bosses in Elden Ring. These heavily armored knights ride large steeds and carry powerful halberds. Although players are likely to encounter one in their first steps out into the Lands Between, it's wise to leave it be at first and return stronger and more experienced. description: Lighter version of the Astrologer Robe

name: Beast Champion Armor
description: Silver armor engraved with tiny beasts. Worn by Bernahl the Recusant. Beasts are drawn to champions, and to lords. And this armor befits a champion worthy of becoming a lord. And that is what Bernahl was. Until his maiden threw herself into the fire.

name: Black Knife Armor
description: Scale armor used by the Black Knife Assassins, forged to make no sound. Traces of power yet remain in its concealing veil, which muffles the sound of footsteps. The assassins that carried out the deeds of the Night of the Black Knives were all women, and rumored to be Numen who had close ties with Marika herself.

name: Beast Champion Armor (altered)
description: Lighter version of the Best Champion Armor

name: Banished Knight Armor
description: Thick, full set of armor covering the entire body. This armor was worn by knights who, whether by misfortune or misdeed, were forced to abandon their homes. These fierce warriors were each and all accomplished. Perhaps that is why, despite their territorial losses, they were still named knights.

name: Black Knife Armor (altered)
description: Lighter version of the Black Knife Armor

name: Bloodsoaked Tabard
description: Padded cloth armor with indelible bloodstains around the neck. Worn by headless foot soldiers who endlessly guard the Wandering Mausoleum.

name: Bloodhound Knight Armor (altered)
description: Lighter version of the Bloodhound Knight Armor

name: Blaidd's Armor (altered)
description: Lighter version of the Blaidd's Armor

name: Bloodhound Knight Armor
description: Metal armor with a jutting breastplate. Worn by the Bloodhound Knights.

name: Blackflame Monk Armor
description: Black iron armor adorned with ashen cloth.

name: Blaidd's Armor
description: Well-worn black armor of the man-wolf Blaidd

name: Blue Silver Mail Armor (altered)
description: Lighter version of the Blue Silver Mail Armor

name: Blue Festive Garb
description: Ceremonial garb worn by dancers at the festivities in Dominula, the village of windmills. Use of this garb, dyed in a stunning blue, is only permitted for the young maids who play the central role in the festival.

name: Blue Cloth Vest
description: Vest of a nomadic warrior. The blue color of its fabric symbolizes brisk waters, as fluid and flowing as the sword in the hand of its wearer. Just as still waters turn foul, stagnation leads to decay. Warriors must remain ever drifting.

name: Blue Silver Mail Armor
description: Chainmail armor crafted with blue silver. Worn by the wolf-riding Albinauric archers. Blue silver is a metal born from the same mother as the archers themselves, and provides protection from magic and frost.

name: Brave's Battlewear
description: Battlewear fashioned from leather armor adorned with a large sheet of cloth. Garb worn by warriors of the frigid uplands The red cloth signifies participation in the Long March long, long ago and this ceremonial garb beseeches the favor of the Warrior King who led them.

name: Briar Armor (altered)
description: Lighter version of the Briar Armor

name: Carian Knight Armor
description: Armor of the enchanted knights that once served the Carian royal family. The enchanted knights, anointed by the Lunar Queen, were heroes of the highest honors, but fell into disarray with the decline of the royal family.

name: Briar Armor
description: Battered iron armor from a foreign land. Worn by Elemer of the Briar.

name: Carian Knight Armor (altered)
description: Lighter version of the Carian Knight Armor

name: Brave's Battlewear (altered)
description: Lighter version of the Brave's Battlewear

name: Chain Armor
description: Armor made of woven chain. Standard issue for ordinary soldiers. Though plain in appearance, it offers dependable protection.

name: Champion Pauldron
description: Pauldron reserved for the badlands' bravest. Proof that the wearer has slaughtered countless foes. Following the example of their chieftain Hoarah Loux, the brave warriors of the badlands shun excess adornment.

name: Bull-goat Armor
description: Great Horned Tragoth's armor. Covers its wearer with a pair of giant horns, providing staunch poise.

name: Chain-draped Tabard
description: Padded cloth armor with a chainmail shawl draped over the shoulders. Widely issued to foot soldiers in a lord's army.

name: Cloth Garb
description: Clothing made of coarse material, commonly worn in the Lands Between.

name: Cleanrot Armor (altered)
description: Lighter version of the Cleanrot Armor

name: Commoner's Garb (altered)
description: Lighter version of the Commoner's Garb

name: Cleanrot Armor
description: Armor of the Cleanrot Knights, celebrated for their undefeated campaign in the Shattering. The Cleanrot Knights vowed to fight alongside Malenia, despite the inevitable, if gradual, putrefaction of their flesh. Their acceptance of their fate made these battles fiercest of all.

name: Commoner's Garb
description: Garb with a thick embroidered cape attached. Standard wear for commoners of the Lands Between.

name: Confessor Armor (altered)
description: Lighter version of the Confessor Armor

name: Confessor Armor
description: Black leather armor for blending in with the darkness. Worn by church confessors. The churches outside the Lands Between, dedicated to the teachings of the Two Fingers, send confessors out to follow the guidance of grace. The confessors are loyal servants to the Two Fingers, ready to hunt down and quietly dispose of their enemies.

name: Commoner's Simple Garb
description: Garb with a modest cloth cape attached. Standard wear for commoners of the Lands Between. The board hung from the neck depicts a sprawling tree, its roots and branches forming two holes. This is a self-imposed shackle, a voluntary display of allegiance to the Erdtree that increases faith.

name: Commoner's Simple Garb (altered)
description: Lighter version of the Commoner's Simple Garb

name: Consort's Robe
description: Fine robe of white silk worn by Tanith, Lady of the Volcano Manor.

name: Crucible Axe Armor
description: Armor of the Crucible Knights who served Godfrey, the first Elden Lord. Worn by the knight Ordovis and his men. Holds the power of the crucible of life, the primordial form of the Erdtree. Strengthens Aspects of the Crucible incantations. Crucible Axe Armor is a Chest Armor in Elden Ring. Crucible Axe Armor is an armor piece worn over or around the player's torso to obtain an increase of defense and resistance. It also changes the appearance as well when it is equipped. Some armor pieces may be available to both genders but may be slightly different for male and female characters.

name: Corhyn's Robe
description: Robe of Corhyn the cleric. Even after exile, Corhyn refused to recant his prophecies. And for this, he was blessed with the guidance of grace. Since then, the cart wheel draped on his neck has served as a reminder. That true guidance awaits those with iron wills. Those with unwavering faith.

name: Crucible Tree Armor
description: Armor of the Crucible Knights who served Godfrey, the first Elden Lord. Worn by the knight Siluria and her men. Holds the power of the crucible of life, the primordial form of the Erdtree. Strengthens Aspects of the Crucible incantations.

name: Crucible Axe Armor (altered)
description: Lighter version of the Crucible Axe Armor

name: Crucible Tree Armor (altered)
description: Lighter version of the Crucible Tree Armor

name: Cuckoo Surcoat
description: Armor worn by Raya Lucaria Academy soldiers. The surcoat depicts twinned cuckoos peering into a flourishing mass of glintstone. To a glintstone sorcerer, the body is a transient thing. The Cuckoo alone knows its insignificance, yet watches over it all the same.

name: Cuckoo Knight Armor
description: Armor worn by Raya Lucaria Academy knights.

name: Cuckoo Knight Armor (altered)
description: Lighter version of the Cuckoo Knight Armor

name: Deathbed Dress
description: Extremely thin and sheer white dress worn by the Deathbed Companion as she embraces the dead. Slowly replenishes the HP of nearby allies, but not that of the wearer. The touch of the fabric is exceedingly soft, so as not to harm even the most withered corpse, while still sharing her warmth.

name: Depraved Perfumer Robe
description: Robe worn by depraved perfumers. The embroidery on the apron is itself a curse upon the Erdtree. These heresy-inclined perfumers imbibe their own spices to alter body and mind. Their slow descent into self-destruction is what earned them their name.

name: Drake Knight Armor
description: Black iron armor worn by drake knights. Features the spoils of a dragon catch as an emblem of pride as both dragon hunter and partake of communion. The cape is crafted with dragon wing membrane.

name: Drake Knight Armor (altered)
description: Lighter version of the Drake Knight Armor

name: Depraved Perfumer Robe (altered)
description: Lighter version of the Depraved Perfumer Robe

name: Elden Lord Armor (altered)
description: Lighter version of the Elden Lord Armor

name: Elden Lord Armor
description: Armor of Godfrey the first Elden Lord. The age of the Erdtree began amongst conflict, when Godfrey was lord of the battlefield. He led the War against the Giants. Faced the Storm Lord, alone. And then, there came a moment. When his last worthy enemy fell. And it was then, as the story is told, that the hue of Lord Godfrey's eyes faded.

name: Dirty Chainmail
description: Chainmail worn by young Albinaurics. The appearance of a protruding belly provides no benefits worthy of note.

name: Errant Sorcerer Robe
description: Commonplace robe made of thick cloth. Worn by the Errant Sorcerer Wilhelm, one of the first Tarnished to visit Roundtable Hold. A silent seeker of sorcery, who had gone so far as to make contact with the primeval current, Wilhelm was led by guidance into confrontation with his friend Vargram, and it is said that he was then taken prisoner in Roundtable Hold.

name: Erdtree Surcoat
description: Armor worn by soldiers sworn to defend the royal capital of Leyndell. The surcoat bears a majestic likeness of the Erdtree. Its golden backing is an honor bestowed on no other soldiers.

name: Eccentric's Armor
description: Unusually colorful armor. Worn by the knight Jerren. Jerren preferred a nomadic existence, but after spending time as guest of the Carian royals, he became a guest commander for General Radahn. And for the first time, the restless tumbleweed would be bound by honorable oath

name: Eye Surcoat
description: Brown surcoat draped over chainmail.

name: Festive Garb
description: Ceremonial garb worn by dancers at the festivities in Dominula, the village of windmills. Faintly bloodstained.

name: Errant Sorcerer Robe (altered)
description: Lighter version of the Errant Sorcerer Robe.

name: Festive Garb (altered)
description: Lighter version of the Festive Garb.

name: Fia's Robe
description: Robe of black cloth that covers the entire body. Worn by Fia, the Deathbed Companion, on her journey after being exiled from her home.

name: Fell Omen Cloak
description: "A cloak of ragged fur worn about the exposed body of Margit, the Fell Omen.

name: Exile Armor
description: Damaged armor draped with a large deep-red cloth. Worn by soldiers sent to the penal colonies.

name: Finger Maiden Robe (altered)
description: Lighter version of the Finger Maiden Robe.

name: Finger Maiden Robe
description: Robe worn by maidens who serve the Two Fingers. The maidens live to serve a chosen Tarnished, sharing their guidance and the wisdom of the Two Fingers.

name: Fingerprint Armor
description: Iron armor singed and blistered by fingers. Worn by Vyke, knight of the Roundtable Hold. No other Tarnished was closer to the throne of the Elden Lord than Vyke. But without announcement, Vyke traveled far below the capital, and was scorched by the flame of frenzy. Did he make his choice for his maiden, or did some other force lure him with suggestion?

name: Fingerprint Armor (altered)
description: Lighter version of the Fingerprint Armor.

name: Fur Raiment
description: Raiment fashioned from a bristly pelt. Worn by ancestral follower warriors. The ancestral followers keep their distance from the Erdtree, awaiting new buds. They are certain to sprout from their very flesh, and indeed, their souls.

name: Gelmir Knight Armor
description: Armor worn by knights once royal to Praector Rykard.

name: Gelmir Knight Armor (altered)
description: Lighter version of the Gelmir Knight Armor.

name: Fire Prelate Armor
description: Black iron armor adorned with a red cloth. Attire of the Fire Prelates, commanders of the Fire Monks.

name: Godrick Knight Armor
description: Armor worn by knights loyal to Godrick The Grafted.

name: Godksin Noble Robe
description: Robe made by sewing together patches of smooth skin. Subcutaneous fat makes it plump and soft. Worn by Godskin Nobles known for their seven-face aprons. Strengthens the Noble Presence incantation. Nobles are the most ancient apostles who are said to have assimilated inhuman physiology. Not unlike the crucible, the Erdtree in its primordial form.

name: Fire Prelate Armor (altered)
description: Lighter version of the Fire Prelate Armor.

name: Foot Soldier Tabard
description: Padded cloth armor with more than a few stains. Widely issued to foot soldiers in a lord's army.

name: Fire Monk Armor
description: Black iron armor adorned with a red cloth. Attire of the Fire Monks.

name: Godrick Knight Armor (altered)
description: Lighter version of the Godric Knight Armor.

name: Goldmask's Rags
description: Worn rags that just barely cover the body. Lord Goldmask felt no draw to the vain excess of clothing; what use is finery to one who seeks greater brilliance?

name: Gravekeeper Cloak
description: Defensive wear encircled by bronze snakes. Worn by gladiators who were driven from the colosseum. The wearer becomes a slightly easier target for foes. The snake is viewed as a traitor to the Erdtree, and the audience delighted in seeing these bronze effigies beaten and battered.

name: Godskin Apostle Robe
description: Robe made by sewing together patches of smooth skin.

name: Haligtree Crest Surcoat
description: Armor worn by soldiers sworn to the Haligtree. The surcoat bears the crest of the Haligtree. Though watered with Miquella's own blood since it was a sapling, the Haligtree ultimately failed to grow into an Erdtree.

name: Gravekeeper Cloak (altered)
description: Lighter version of the Gravekeeper Cloak.

name: Guardian Garb
description: Engraved golden garb. Worn by guardians of the Minor Erdtree.

name: Haligtree Knight Armor
description: Armor worn by knights sworn the Haligtree.

name: Guardian Garb (full Bloom)
description: Engraved golden garb. Worn by the guardians of the Minor Erdtrees. Raises the HP recovery effects of the Flask of Crimson Tears, but greatly lowers fire damage negation. It is said that the blood-red flowers blooming on their backs mark the senescence of their ancient pact. Perhaps the guardians are part tree already

name: Haligtree Knight Armor (altered)
description: Lighter version of the Haligtree Knight Armor.

name: High Page Clothes
description: Clothes of a page selected for special privileges by the noble they serve.

name: Highwayman Cloth Armor
description: Hideously stained and ragged cloth armor. Worn by former foot soldiers who have turned to banditry.

name: High Page Clothes (altered)
description: Lighter version of the High Page Clothes.

name: Hoslow's Armor
description: Garish silver armor decorated with red embellishments. Passed down through the Hoslow family. When Juno Hoslow received an invitation to the Volcano Manor, he discreetly refused. "I have already walked many a road drenched in blood, yet never would I consider myself a champion."

name: Ivory-draped Tabard
description: Padded cloth armor with a shawl in the color of ivory draped over the shoulders. Worn by foot soldiers sworn to the Haligtree.

name: Knight Armor
description: Iron armor of an unknown knight. It is made of thin iron plate. Such metal armor is heavy, but provides considerable damage negation.

name: Juvenile Scholar Robe
description: Robe worn by young academy scholars, the juveniles birthed anew by the amber egg of Queen Rennala, the head of Raya Lucaria Academy. Yet their rebirth is not without imperfections, and thus do they repeat the process, eventually becoming utterly dependent upon it. Rebirth is as sleep to them, and with each awakening, memory fades into oblivion.

name: Kaiden Armor
description: Armor worn by Kaiden sellswords.

name: Land Of Reeds Armor
description: Armor made from strips of iron fastened together. Worn by warriors of the Land of Reeds. The Land of Reeds has long been locked in a miserable civil war, during which time it has remained alienated from the cultures of its neighbors. Little wonder that the entire nation has succumbed to blood-soaked madness, or so it is said.

name: Hoslow's Armor (altered)
description: Lighter version of the Hoslow's Armor.

name: Lazuli Robe
description: Robe worn by scholars of the Lazuli Conspectus, singular among the greater Raya Lucaria Academy. These scholars, who sought to master Carian sorcery, instead learned to see the moon as equal to the stars. This robe, in the hue of the full moon, signifies their heresy.

name: Leather Armor
description: Lightweight and battle-proven leather armor worn by a savvy soldier. Leather Armor is a Chest Armor in Elden Ring. Leather Armor is part of the Leather Set Armor Set, and is a Light Weight armor that provides some Immunity Resistance. Leather Armor is an armor piece worn over or around the player's torso to obtain an increase of defense and resistance. It also changes the appearance as well when it is equipped. Some armor pieces may be available to both genders but may be slightly different for male and female characters.
