name: Leather Trousers
description: Well-made leather trousers. The lower legs are each bound in cord for ease of movement.

name: Leyndell Knight Greaves
description: Greaves worn by knights sworn to defend the royal capital of Leyndell. Time has yet to dull their luster.

name: Leyndell Soldier Greaves
description: Greaves worn by soldiers sworn to defend the royal capital of Leyndell. Rust-worn and stained through unending conflict.

name: Lionel's Greaves
description: Rounded iron greaves. Worn by Lionel the Lionhearted.

name: Malformed Dragon Greaves
description: Malformed golden greaves.

name: Malenia's Greaves
description: Greaves made of unalloyed gold. Worn by Malenia, Blade of Miquella. Malenia awaited Miquella at the foot of the husk. "My brother will keep his promise. He possesses the wisdom, the allure, of a godhe is the most fearsome Empyrean of all."

name: Maliketh's Greaves
description: Beast's greaves made of black iron and decorated with gold. Worn by Maliketh the Black Blade. Maliketh, Queen Marika's loyal half-brother, bore a blade imbued with Destined Death, and there was not one demigod who did not fear him. Champions knew what was at stake. Indeed, that is what made them champions.

name: Mausoleum Greaves
description: Greaves worn by headless soldiers who endlessly guard the Wandering Museum. Rust-worn and stained through unending conflict.

name: Mausoleum Knight Greaves
description: Greaves worn by headless knights who endlessly guard the Wandering Mausoleum. Time has yet to dull their luster.

name: Old Sorcerer Legwraps
description: Ragged waistcloth that extends to the thighs. Common amongst old-fashioned sorcerers.

name: Nox Monk Greaves
description: Greaves worn by the monks of the Eternal City. Long ago, the Nox invoked the ire of the Greater Will, and were banished deep underground. Now they live under a false night sky, in eternal anticipation of their liege. Of the coming age of the stars. And their Lord of Night.

name: Omenkiller Boots
description: Long, stiff leather gloves worn by the Omenkillers.

name: Nomadic Merchant's Trousers
description: Trousers of the nomadic merchants. These merchants once thrived as the Great Caravan, but after being accused of heretical beliefs, their entire clan was rounded up and buried alive far underground. Then, they chanted a curse of despair, and summoned the flame of frenzy.

name: Page Trousers
description: Trousers worn by pages who serve nobility and are mindful to keep them out of harm's way.

name: Night's Cavalry Greaves
description: Pitch-black greaves thinly painted with dried blood. Worn by the Night's Cavalry who ride funeral steeds.

name: Mushroom Legs
description: Mushrooms found growing all over the body. These overgrown mushroom have colonized the Legs. To those enraptured by the scarlet rot, they are holy vestments that root one to the earth.

name: Omen Greaves
description: Malformed greaves resembling an Omen with its horns cut off.

name: Old Aristocrat Shoes
description: Hard-wearing shoes made of leather. Travel attire worn by nobles in the capital. Garb favored by the aged.

name: Noble's Trousers
description: White trousers of superior craftsmanship. Worn by expatriated royalty. A gift of such rare beauty, a royal wouldn't disgrace their illustrious heritage even if found dead, in a ditch, in the middle of nowhere, while wearing such splendid raiment.

name: Ragged Loincloth
description: Greaves pieced together from scavenged metal.

name: Perfumer Sarong
description: Sarong of an Erdtree Capital perfumer.

name: Preceptor's Trousers
description: Trousers of the magic preceptors who serve the Carian royals. Black and perfectly discreet.

name: Prophet Trousers
description: Trousers of the exiled prophets who foresaw that their faith would end in flames  and were persecuted and driven from their homes as a result. Its fabric scrapes against their skin like a file, and the rickety cart wheel around the neck warns passers-by not to lend an ear to their meandering sermons.

name: Queen's Leggings
description: Leggings indicating the highest order of sorcerer. Worn by Rennala, Queen of the Full Moon. When Rennala, head of both the Academy of Raya Lucaria and the Carian royal family, lost her husband Radagon, her heart went along with him. And then, those at the academy realized. That Rennala was no champion, after all.

name: Raya Lucarian Greaves
description: Greaves worn by Raya Lucaria Academy soldiers. Rust-worn and stained through unending conflict.

name: Prisoner Trousers
description: Tattered trousers. Worn by a prisoner convicted of an appalling crime. Never once washed, every fiber is filthy. The smell is beyond belief.

name: Redmane Knight Greaves
description: Black iron greaves worn by knights who fought by General Radahn's side. Time has yet to dull their luster.

name: Radahn's Greaves
description: Greaves depicting the golden lion. Worn by General Radahn.

name: Radahn Soldier Greaves
description: Greaves worn by soldiers who fought by General Radahn's side. Rust-worn and stained through unending conflict.

name: Royal Knight Greaves
description: Silver greaves of Loretta, a knight who served Miquella's Haligtree. Loretta, once a royal Carian knight, went on a journey in search of a haven for Albinaurics, and determined that the Haligtree was their best chance for eventual salvation.

name: Ronin's Greaves
description: Greaves of the man who calls himself Shabriri. Highly functional and heavily worn.

name: Royal Remains Greaves
description: Greaves graced with gold human bones. Worn by the unspeaking adherent of Sir Gideon the All-Knowing.

name: Sage Trousers
description: Thick burgundy trousers. Attire of the wise sages who were deemed heretical. Evidence that the wearer was driven from town.

name: Shaman Leggings
description: Leggings fashioned from bristly pelts. Worn by ancestral follower shamans.

name: Snow Witch Skirt
description: Witch's skirt in the color of snow. Once worn by the snowy crone who the young Ranni encountered deep in the woods. She was a witch, and well versed in cold sorceries. It is said that the doll that houses Ranni's soul was modeled after her. That old witch was Ranni's secret mentor.

name: Scaled Greaves
description: Gauntlets worn by Old Knight Istvan. The corroded metal is reinforced with rock-hard scales, making it high effective against non-physical attacks. Istvan is one of a few wizened Tarnished who survived to this day.

name: Rotten Duelist Greaves
description: Greaves wrapped with bronze snakes, eaten through by scarlet rot. Worn by gladiators who were driven from the colosseum. The wearer becomes a slightly easier target for foes.

name: Spellblade's Trousers
description: Glintstone sorcerer Rogier's traveling attire, graced with an intricate, aristocratic decoration. Strengthens glintstone sorcery skills.

name: Sorcerer Leggings
description: Leggings worn by Raya Lucaria's magic scholars. Made by wrapping a simple cloth around the legs.

name: Traveler's Slops
description: Slops of a traveling perfumer of no renown.

name: Veteran's Greaves
description: An old greaves that has seen many battles.Worn by Niall, the great veteran general of Sol.

name: Traveler's Boots
description: Light yet sturdy leather boots.

name: Traveling Maiden Boots
description: Boots worn by traveling maidens.

name: Twinned Greaves
description: Greaves depicting entwined twins of gold and silver.

name: Tree Sentinel Greaves
description: Golden greaves of the heavy cavalry Tree Sentinels who serve the Erdtree.

name: War Surgeon Trousers
description: Bloodstained trousers of the war surgeons who were effectively mercy killers. Of the surgeons that were abducted by the Lord of Blood none were able to tame the accursed blood. None but Varr, that is; though he was an exception

name: Vulgar Militia Greaves
description: Greaves worn by lean, mean, and filthy militiamen.

name: Warrior Greaves
description: Greaves of a nomadic warrior. Crafted from sturdy leather.

name: Vagabond Knight Greaves
description: Greaves of a knight banished from their motherland. Dirty and battered after enduring a lengthy vagabond journey.

name: White Reed Greaves
description: Greaves of the White Reeds, fashioned from banded iron plates. Worn by the Inabam head disciples of the great swordsman Okina. The Inaba traveled in pursuit of not only the master who abandoned them, but also proper deaths, won honorably through hard-fought combat. To be a White Reed is to seek death; fitting for the Inaba, who desired nothingmore than to die by the sword.

name: Zamor Legwraps
description: Legwraps worn by knights of Zamor, hailed as heroes in the War against the Giants. These long-lived warriors, clad in biting, freezing winds, are said to have been the mortal enemies of the Fire Giants since time immemorial.

name: Arrow's Sting Talisman
description: A talisman depicting three iron arrows. Carried by soldiers long ago.

name: Arsenal Charm
description: An iron charm that resembles a mass of weaponry. Boosts maximum equipment load. This talisman was derived from an unusual greatsword, once wielded by a hero hungry for vengeance.

name: Assassin's Cerulean Dagger
description: An assassin's dagger, misshapen and stained in cerulean. Critical hits restore FP.

name: Assassin's Crimson Dagger
description: An assassin's dagger, misshapen and stained in crimson. Critical hits restore HP. Assassin's Crimson Dagger is a Talisman in Elden Ring. Assassin's Crimson Dagger causes critical attacks to restore 10% +85 HP. Players can use Talismans in Elden Ring to boost a variety of Stats.

name: Arrow's Reach Talisman
description: A talisman depicting three arrows. Carried by hunters of beasts.

name: Axe Talisman
description: A talisman depicting an axe and a warrior. Enhances charge attacks.

name: Boltdrake Talisman
description: Talisman depicting a yellow ancient dragon. Boosts lightning damage negation.

name: Blue Dancer Charm
description: A cloth doll depicting a dancer garbed in blue. An ancient heirloom of some sort. Blue Dancer Charm is a Talisman in Elden Ring. Blue Dancer Charm raises Physical Damage with lower Equip Load. Players can use Talismans in Elden Ring to boost a variety of Stats.

name: Blessed Dew Talisman
description: Talisman depicting a drop of the Erdtree's sap, a blessed boon.

name: Bull-goat's Talisman
description: A talisman depicting the horns of a bull-goat. Raises poise.

name: Cerulean Amber Medallion
description: A medallion with cerulean amber inlaid. Boosts maximum FP. Cerulean Amber Medallion is a Talisman in Elden Ring. Cerulean Amber Medallion raises maximum FP by 7%. Players can use talismans in Elden Ring to boost a variety of Stats.

name: Carian Filigreed Crest
description: A talisman adorned with the royal crest.

name: Cerulean Seed Talisman
description: A cerulean-colored talisman patterned after an Erdtree seed. Boosts FP restoration from the Flask of Cerulean Tears.

name: Clarifying Horn Charm
description: An accoutrement worn by the ancestral followers. Raises focus. (Focus governs resistance to sleep and madness.)

name: Claw Talisman
description: A talisman depicting a claw and an assassin. Enhances jump attacks.

name: Crucible Knot Talisman
description: A talisman fashioned from a bony knot that embodies that aspects of various creatures. Said to have grown on the human body long ago. Crucible Knot Talisman is a Talisman in Elden Ring. Crucible Knot Talisman can be used to reduce the damage from the impact of headshots taken. Players can use Talismans in Elden Ring to boost a variety of Stats.

name: Crimson Amber Medallion
description: A medallion with Crimson amber inlaid. Boosts maximum HP. The Erdtree's old sap becomes amber, treasured as the most precious of jewels in the age of Godfrey, the first Elden Lord. A primordial life energy resides inside Crimson Amber Medallion is a Talisman and optional Keepsake in Elden Ring. Crimson Amber Medallion raises maximum HP by 6%. Players can use Talismans in Elden Ring to boost a variety of Stats.

name: Crucible Scale Talisman
description: A talisman fashioned from a scale that embodies the aspects of various creatures. Said to have grown on the human body long ago.

name: Crepus's Vial
description: Small mysterious bottle with a dark mist sealed within.

name: Curved Sword Talisman
description: A talisman depicting a curved sword and a swordsman. Enhances guard counters.

name: Dragoncrest Shield Talisman
description: Wrought iron talisman depicting a trio of ancient dragons. Boosts physical damage negation.

name: Flamedrake Talisman
description: Talisman depicting a red ancient dragon. Boosts fire damage negation. Flamedrake Talisman is a Talisman in Elden Ring. Flamedrake Talisman reduces Fire Damage taken by 13% (the effect is reduced to 4% in PvP). Players can use talismans in Elden Ring to boost a variety of Stats.

name: Fire Scorpion Charm
description: A talisman carried by assassins who strike unseen. Patterned on a scorpion freshly shed of its exoskeleton, its claws seizing a heart that burns with fire.

name: Godskin Swaddling Cloth
description: Sacred cloth of the Godskin Apostles, made from supple skin sewn together. Godskin Swaddling Cloth is a Talisman in Elden Ring. Godskin Swaddling Cloth causes successive attacks to restore HP. Players can use talismans in Elden Ring to boost a variety of Stats.

name: Faithful's Canvas Talisman
description: A talisman bearing an icon that depicts a group of masked figures. Raises potency of incantations.

name: Great-jar's Arsenal
description: A charm that resembles a great jar overflowing with weaponry. Vastly boosts maximum equipment load.

name: Haligdrake Talisman
description: Talisman depicting a golden ancient dragon. Boosts holy damage negation.

name: Green Turtle Talisman
description: A talisman in the shape of a green turtle. Raises stamina recovery speed.

name: Hammer Talisman
description: A talisman depicting a hammer and a knight. Enhances stamina-reducing attacks against a blocking opponent.

name: Immunizing Horn Charm
description: An accountrement worn by the ancestral followers. Raises immunity. (Immunity governs resistance to poison and rot.) Immunizing Horn Charm is a Talisman in Elden Ring. Immunizing Horn Charm raises Immunity by 90, improving resistance to Poison and Scarlet Rot. Players can use talismans in Elden Ring to boost a variety of Stats.

name: Kindred Of Rot's Exultation
description: A talisman depicting the exultation of pests. Kindred of Rot's Exultation is a Talisman in Elden Ring. Kindred of Rot's Exultation raises attack power by 20% for 20 seconds when Poisoning or Rot occurs in the vicinity. Players can use Talismans in Elden Ring to boost a variety of Stats.

name: Lightning Scorpion Charm
description: A talisman carried by assassins who strike unseen. Patterned on a scorpion freshly shed of its exoskeleton, its claws seizing a heart that sparks with lightning.

name: Longtail Cat Talisman
description: A brooch depicting Lacrima, the long-tailed cat.

name: Marika's Scarseal
description: An eye engraved with an Elden Rune. Said to be the seal of Queen Marika.

name: Lord Of Blood's Exultation
description: A talisman depicting the exultation of the Lord of Blood. Lord of Blood's Exultation is a Talisman in Elden Ring. Lord of Blood's Exultation raises attack power by 20% for 20 seconds when Blood Loss occurs in the vicinity. Players can use Talismans in Elden Ring to boost a variety of Stats.

name: Mottled Necklace
description: A vividly-colored accoutrement precious to the ancestral followers.

name: Moon Of Nokstella
description: This legendary talisman is a treasure of Nokstella, the Eternal City.

name: Old Lord's Talisman
description: A legendary talisman depicting the ancient king whose seat lies at the heart of the storm beyond time.

name: Pearldrake Talisman
description: Talisman depicting a pearlescent ancient dragon. Boosts non-physical damage negation.

name: Primal Glintstone Blade
description: An old glintstone blade that has been stained with blood.

name: Prince Of Death's Pustule
description: A fetid pustule taken from facial flesh. Raises vitality. (Vitality governs resistance to the effects of Death.)

name: Radagon Icon
description: A legendary talisman depicting the Elden Lord Radagon. Shortens the casting time of sorceries and incantations.

name: Radagon's Scarseal
description: An eye engraved with an Elden Rune. Said to be the seal of King Consort Radagon. Radagon's Scarseal is a Talisman in Elden Ring. Radagon's Scarseal raises Vigor, Endurance, Strength, and Dexterity by 3 each, but increases damage taken by 10%. Easily confused with the separate talisman: Radagon's Soreseal. Players can use talismans in Elden Ring to boost a variety of Stats.

name: Radagon's Soreseal
description: This legendary talisman is an eye engraved with an Elden Rune, said to be the seal of King Consort Radagon.

name: Sacred Scorpion Charm
description: A talisman carried by assassins who strike unseen. Patterned on a scorpion freshly shed of its exoskeleton, its claws seizing a heart with a blessed glow.

name: Sacrificial Twig
description: A talisman fashioned from a dried twig, so slender that it might snap at the slightest touch.

name: Shabriri's Woe
description: Disturbing likeness of a man whose eyes have been gouged out. The corners of his mouth are upturned in an almost flirtatious manner.

name: Spelldrake Talisman
description: Talisman depicting a blue ancient dragon. Boosts magic damage negation. Spelldrake Talisman is a Talisman in Elden Ring. Spelldrake Talisman reduces Magic Damage taken by 13% in PvE and 4% in PvP. Players can use Talismans Elden Ring to boost a variety of Stats.

name: Stargazer Heirloom
description: A talisman engraved with the legend of a queen. Raises intelligence.

name: Twinblade Talisman
description: A talisman depicting a twinblade and a confessor. Enhances the final hit ending a chain of attacks.

name: Taker's Cameo
description: A talisman engraved with a stern likeness of Praetor Rykard, master of Volcano Manor.

name: Starscourge Heirloom
description: A talisman engraved with a scene from a heroic tale. Raises strength.

name: Viridian Amber Medallion
description: A medallion with viridian amber inlaid. Boosts maximum stamina. The Erdtree's old sap becomes amber, treasured as the most precious of jewels in the age of Godfrey, the first Elden Lord. A primordial life energy resides inside Viridian Amber Medallion is a Talisman in Elden Ring. Viridian Amber Medallion raises maximum Stamina by 11%. Players can use talismans in Elden Ring to boost a variety of Stats.

name: Two Fingers Heirloom
description: A talisman engraved with the legend of the Two Fingers. Raises faith.

name: Winged Sword Insignia
description: A talisman depicting a raised prosthetic blade. An honor bestowed upon the knights who fought alongside Malenia the Severed. Winged Sword Insignia is a Talisman in Elden Ring. Winged Sword Insignia increases attack power with each successive attack. Players can use talismans in Elden Ring to boost a variety of Stats.

name: Erdtree's Favor
description: A talisman depicting a special blessing of the Erdtree. Slightly raises maximum HP, stamina, and equip load.

name: Crimson Seed Talisman
description: A crimson-colored talisman patterned after an Erdtree seed. Boosts HP restoration from the Flask of Crimson Tears.

name: Graven-school Talisman
description: A talisman depicting a school of graven mages, the nightmare of the academy.

name: Godfrey Icon
description: A legendary talisman depicting the Elden Lord Godfrey. Raises charge attack power of sorceries, incantations, and skills. Godfrey Icon is a Talisman in Elden Ring. Godfrey Icon raises attack power of charged Spells and Skills by 15%. Players can use talismans in Elden Ring to boost a variety of Stats.

name: Lance Talisman
description: A talisman depicting a lance and a knight. Enhances attacks while on horseback.

name: Graven-mass Talisman
description: A talisman depicting the first school of graven mages  a nightmare that would continue to haunt the academy. Greatly raises potency of sorceries. The primeval current is a forbidden tradition of glintstone sorcery. To those who cleave to its teachings, the act of collecting sorcerers to fashion them into the seeds of stars is but another path of scientific inquiry.

name: Ancestral Spirit's Horn
description: Item cut from the horns of the Regal Ancestor Spirit.

name: Stalwart Horn Charm
description: An accoutrement worn by the ancestral followers. Greatly raises robustness. (Robustness governs resistance to blood loss and frost.) Said to be a budding horn. The ancestral followers believe that the horns of a long-lived beast continue to bud like antlers, over and over again, until the beast one day becomes an ancestral spirit.

name: Dragoncrest Greatshield Talisman
description: Legendary talisman of wrought iron depicting a massive ancient dragon. Enormously boosts physical damage negation.

name: Marika's Soreseal
description: This legendary talisman is an eye engraved with an Elden Rune, said to be the seal of Queen Marika.

name: Gold Scarab
description: A talisman facsimile of a scarab, the carrier of treasures and precious things.

name: Ritual Sword Talisman
description: A talisman patterned after swords used in ritual combat held to honor the Erdtree. Ritual Sword Talisman is a Talisman in Elden Ring. Ritual Sword Talisman raises attack power by 10% when HP is at maximum. Players can use Talismans in Elden Ring to boost a variety of Stats.

name: Ritual Shield Talisman
description: A talisman patterned after shields used in ritual combat held to honor the Erdtree.

name: Perfumer's Talisman
description: A talisman depicting a set of perfume bottles. Raises potency of perfume items.

name: Blue-feathered Branchsword
description: A talisman adorned with blue feathers, once used in ancient death rituals. Blue-Feathered Branchsword is a Talisman in Elden Ring. Blue-Feathered Branchsword reduces damage taken by 50% when HP is below 20%. Players can use Talismans in Elden Ring to boost a variety of Stats.

name: Magic Scorpion Charm
description: A talisman carried by assassins who strike unseen. Patterned on a scorpion freshly shed of its exoskeleton, its claws seizing a heart that shimmers with magic.

name: Prince Of Death's Cyst
description: A fetid, overgrown cyst taken from facial flesh. Greatly raises vitality. (Vitality governs resistance to the effects of Death.)

name: Warrior Jar Shard
description: Shard of a shattered warrior jar.

name: Shard Of Alexander
description: Shard of the late Alexander, a shattered warrior jar.

name: Greatshield Talisman
description: Talisman depicting a knight holding a greatshield. Boosts guarding ability.

name: Millicent's Prosthesis
description: Part of the golden prosthesis used by Millicent. The hand is locked into a fist that once raised a sword aloft.

name: Spear Talisman
description: A talisman depicting a spear and a soldier. Enhances the counterattacks that are unique to thrusting weapons.

name: Dagger Talisman
description: A talisman depicting a dagger and a surgeon. Enhances critical hits.

name: Red-feathered Branchsword
description: A talisman adorned with red feathers, once used in ancient death rituals. Red-Feathered Branchsword is a Talisman in Elden Ring. Red-Feathered Branchsword raises attack power by 20% when HP is below 20%. Players can use Talismans in Elden Ring to boost a variety of Stats.

name: Companion Jar
description: A talisman given by the jars to their friends. Raises potency of thrown jars.

name: Flock's Canvas Talisman
description: A talisman bearing an icon that depicts a mass of masked figures. Greatly raises potency of incantations.

name: Concealing Veil
description: Talisman put together from dark cloth with a lustrous sheen

name: Crucible Feather Talisman
description: A talisman fashioned from feathers that embody the aspects of various creatures. Said to have grown on the human body long ago.

name: Daedicar's Woe
description: Disturbing likeness of a woman whose skin was flayed. She smiles with a serene tenderness.

name: Entwining Umbilical Cord
description: Mysterious circular object that's oddly warped. Changes the demeanour of the wearer's actions.

name: Flame Of The Fell God
description: This legendary incantation is one of several that draws directly from the power of the Fire Giants. Releases a ball of raging fire said to be inhabited by a fell god. The fireball floats toward enemies and explodes, setting the area ablaze. Arghanthy, the chief guardian of the Flame, had kept this incantation a well-kept secret until it was stolen by Adan. The fell god still lurks within the Fire Giants. Flame of the Fell God is an Incantation in Elden Ring. Flame of the Fell God spell fires a ball of fire that explodes on contact leaving a patch of fire. Updated to Patch 1.07.

description: Incantation that channels the power of the Dragonkin Soldiers. Creates a spear of ice lightning and stabs it into the ground from above. On impact, the spear will burst into trails of lightning advancing forwards. The Dragonkin were born in the Eternal City, where they knew no true sky, nor true lightning. Instead, ice lightning was their weapon. Frozen Lightning Spear is an Incantation in Elden Ring. Frozen Lightning Spear spell conjures a spear from above that moves forward dealing damage and leaving a trail of lightning. Updated to Patch 1.07.

The role of the hunters is to stamp out defiled reason - all for the perfection of the Golden Order.

name: Magic Fortification
description: Incantation of the Two Fingers' faithful. Increases magic damage negation. This incantation can be cast while in motion. Follow the path that has been set for you, and you will make enemies of all others: the monks, the sorcerers, the ancient dragon knights, and the scions of gold. Heed me  the Lands Between offers no welcome to the Tarnished.

name: Altered Armor
description: Altered Armor in Elden Ring are individual pieces of armor that have been visually modified to look different from the original armor. Not only does altering armor change its appearance, but it also makes minor adjustments to the armor piece's statistics such as its weight and damage negation. Altering armor is usually done not for the minor stats change, but for how it looks, allowing players match their armor to other pieces in the game. Since there are no additional buffs when wearing armor pieces of the same set, players have more options for choosing visually appealing armor that will suit their needs.

name: Ansbach's Set
description: Ansbach's Set is an Armor Set in Elden Ring. It is an Armor Set introduced in the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. Sets of Armor in Elden Ring are composed of four armor pieces which are Helms, Chest Armor, Gauntlets, and Leg Armor. This armor set offers very high overall stats, ideal for lightweight builds.

name: Abyssal Woods
description: Abyssal Woods is a Location in Elden Ring, added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Abyss region can be found east of the Gravesite Plain, south of the Scadu Altus, and can be accessed through Darklight Catacombs at the end of the Recluses' River.

name: Adula's Moonblade
description: Adula's Moonblade is a Sorcery in Elden Ring. Adula's Moonblade creates a cold magic greatsword to slice enemies sideways while launching ranged slash frost projectiles. Updated to Patch 1.07.

name: Ainsel River
description: Ainsel River is a Location in Elden Ring. The Ainsel River region features a sprawling cave system with large open caverns housing ruins and waterfalls. You can access the southern part of the region by taking the lift down at Ainsel River Well. The northern part, Ainsel River Main, is accessed by a waygate at the top of Renna's Rise after giving Ranni the Fingerslayer Blade or by taking a coffin in Deeproot Depths (see it on the Elden Ring Map here). This river can also be accessed by a coffin from The Nameless Eternal City Grace Site, from Great Waterfall Basin coffin ride after defeating the two Gargoyles at Siofra Aqueduct.

description: Ancestral Follower Ashes is a Spirit and Summon in Elden Ring. Ancestral Follower Ashes summons an ancestral follower who wields a heavy bow.

name: Ancient Dragon Senessax
description: Ancient Dragon Senessax is a Great Enemy Boss in Elden Ring. Senessax is an ancient dragon that guards the path to the summit. They are found in Jagged Peak, West side which is also near Bayle the Dread. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat it to advance in Shadow of the Erdtree.

name: Ancient Dragon-Man
description: Ancient Dragon-Man is a Boss in Elden Ring. Ancient Dragon-Man carries a katana and moves quickly in between attacks, and is found in Dragon's Pit, he drops the Dragon-Hunter's Great Katana once defeated. This is an optional boss as players will not need to defeat him to advance in Elden Ring.

name: Ancient Ruins of Rauh
description: Ancient Ruins of Rauh (Rauh Ruins) is a Location in Elden Ring. The Ancient Ruins of Rauh region are added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC, located north of Gravesite Plain, west of Scadu Atlus. [See Shadow of the Erdtree Map] It can only be accessed to its entirely by traveling through the Shadow Keep.

name: Armor
description: In Elden Ring, Armor are protective items worn by the player's character which grant protections, resistances, and various bonus effects against damage and status effects, as well as influencing statistics such as carry load and poise. In Elden Ring, armor is divided into categories such as Helms, Chest Armor, Gauntlets, and Leg Armor. Players can adorn a full set of the same armor, or wear different pieces from different sets, with no additional buff if all pieces are from the same set. This means that the player can freely customise their armor to their needs without worrying about set bonuses.

name: Astel Naturalborn of the Void
description: Astel, Naturalborn of the Void is a Legend Boss in Elden Ring. This strange alien lifeform is comprised of many-colored star debris which landed in the Lands Between long ago, and is found in the Grand Cloister. Astel destroyed one of the Eternal Cities and wiped out their sky. This is an optional boss, as players don't need to defeat it in order to advance in Elden Ring. However, it must be defeated to achieve a certain ending.
metadata: {"Location": "Grand Cloister", "HP": "11,170", "Stronger VS Magic Fire Lightning Holy Immune to Frostbite": "Weaker to Standard Slash Strike Pierce", "wiki_url": "https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/Astel,+Naturalborn+of+the+Void"}

name: Auriza Hero's Grave
description: Auriza Hero's Grave is a Location in Elden Ring. The Auriza Hero's Grave is found in the eastern section of the Capital Outskirts. Players can reach this location by following the main path within the outskirt walls, all the way to the east.

name: Auriza Side Tomb
description: Auriza Side Tomb is a Location in Elden Ring. The Auriza Side Tomb is found in the Capital Outskirts in the Altus Plateau. Can be accessed by dropping to a spiritspring below Capital Rampart site of grace and then going northeast or simply going northeast from Auriza Heros Grave entrance.

name: Banished Knight Engvall Ashes
description: Banished Knight Engvall Ashes is a Spirit and Summon in Elden Ring. Banished Knight Engvall Ashes summon the spirit of a Banished Knight. Engvall is the counterpart to Banished Knight Oleg, together they are known as the Wings of the Storm.

name: Banished Knight Oleg Ashes
description: Banished Knight Oleg Ashes is a Spirit and Summon in Elden Ring. Banished Knight Oleg Ashes summons the spirit of a Banished Knight. Oleg is the counterpart to Banished Knight Engvall, together they are known as the Wings of the Storm.

name: Barbed Staff-Spear
description: Barbed Staff-Spear is a Great Spear in Elden Ring. It is a brand-new Great Spear in the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Barbed Staff-Spear scales primarily with Strength, Dexterity and Faith and is a good Weapon for Faith players. This has the Jori's Inquisition skill that lets you summon golden arcs towards foes.

name: Messmer the Impaler
description: Messmer the Impaler is a Demigod Boss in Shadow of the Erdtree. He is the leader of the crusade against the Hornsent people, killing their Divine Beasts and burning the Tower Settlement. He is revealed to be Queen Marika's son, secreted away and abandoned in the Land of Shadow. In combat, he utilizes Fire-based Spells and a Greatspear. This is not an optional boss as players need to defeat him to advance in Shadow of the Erdtree.
metadata: {"Location": "Shadow Keep, Specimen Storehouse", "Drops": "400,000Remembrance of the ImpalerMessmer's Kindling", "HP": "38,981", "Strong VS Fire": "Weak to Slash Holy (phase 2) Frostbite", "wiki_url": "https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/Messmer+the+Impaler"}

name: Battlemage Hugues
description: Battlemage Hugues is a Boss in Elden Ring. Battlemage Hugues is a Haima Battlemage and is found in Sellia Evergaol, in central Caelid north from Sellia. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat it to advance in Elden Ring.
metadata: {"Location": "Sellia Evergaol", "Drops": "7,800Battlemage Hugues Ashes", "HP": "4,095", "Stronger VS Magic": "Weaker to Standard Slash Pierce Holy Poison Scarlet Rot"}

name: Battlemage Hugues Ashes
description: Battlemage Hugues Ashes is a Spirit and Summon in Elden Ring. Battlemage Hugues Ashes are used to summon the spirit of Battlemage Hugues.

name: Bayle The Dread
description: Bayle the Dread is a Legend Boss in Elden Ring. Bayle is the forefather of the drakes, a sworn enemy of the ancient dragons, and the target of Igon's vengeance. He is found at the summit of the Jagged Peak. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat it to advance in Shadow of the Erdtree.
metadata: {"Location": "Jagged Peak", "Drops": "490000Heart of Bayle", "HP": "41,612", "Stronger VS All Elements": "Weaker to Pierce"}

name: Belurat Gaol
description: Belurat Gaol is a Location in Elden Ring. The Belurat Gaol is found in the Gravesite Plain. The Belurat Gaol is an underground prison area situated northwest of the map. The entrance can be located around an area on the map that is surrounded by water and prison cages. This location is exclusive to the Shadow of the Erdtree expansion.

name: Belurat Tower Settlement
description: Belurat Tower Settlement is a Legacy Dungeon in Elden Ring. It is exclusive to the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The tower was said to be a place where practitioners and experts would practice the ancient form of hexing arts. It was also a place where individuals who have caught the "fly sickness" have succumbed to death or the disease that transformed them into hostile flesh-eating creatures. And since unimaginable actions and magic were practiced, those who have met their demise now roam the tower as lost Revered Spirits, waiting to kill anything or anyone who explores the area. [See Shadow of the Erdtree Map]

name: Black Knife Tiche Ashes
description: Black Knife Tiche is a Spirit and Summon in Elden Ring. Black Knife Tiche Ash summons an assassin that attacks enemies with her Black Knife imbued with the Rune of Death.

name: Black Knight Edredd
description: Black Knight Edredd is a Field Boss in Elden Ring. Black Knight Edredd is a winged knight armed with a double-ended sword and is found in Fort of Reprimand. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat it to advance in Shadow of the Erdtree.
metadata: {"Location": "Fort of Reprimand", "Drops": "80,000 (400,000 with Golden Eyes)Ash of War: Aspects of the Crucible: Wings", "HP": "19,584", "Strong VS Slash": "Weak to Lightning Poison Scarlet Rot Sleep"}

name: Black Knight Garrew
description: Black Knight Garrew is an Enemy Boss in Elden Ring. Black Knight Garrew is a big human knight that's equipped with a large mace and a large shield and is found in Fog Rift Fort. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat it to advance in Elden Ring.
metadata: {"Location": "Fog Rift Fort", "Drops": "80,000Black Steel Greatshield", "HP": "19,584", "Stronger VS Slash": "Weaker to Lightning Poison Scarlet Rot Sleep"}

name: Black Steel Greatshield
description: Black Steel Greatshield is a Greatshield in Elden Ring. It is a brand new Greatshield in the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Black Steel Greatshield is a Shield that scales primarily with Strength. Greatshields weigh a decent amount and provide the best protection in the game. Greatshields provide a greater value of blocking and protecting oneself from enemy and boss attacks but greatly increases the weight and reduces the player's mobility. This type of shield works best at reducing damage or guarding instead of parrying.

name: Blackflame Monk Amon Ashes
description: Blackflame Monk Amon Ashes is a Spirit and Summon in Elden Ring. Blackflame Monk Amon Ashes are used to summon the spirit of Amon, the Blackflame Monk.

name: Blackgaol Knight
description: Knight of the Solitary Gaol is an Enemy Boss in Elden Ring. The Knight of the Solitary Gaol switches weapons between a Greatsword and a Crossbow, and is found in the Western Nameless Mausoleum. The Knight of the Solitary Gaol drops the Greatsword of Solitude and his Solitude Set upon death. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat it to advance in Shadow of the Erdtree.
metadata: {"Location": "Western Nameless Mausoleum", "Drops": "70,000 Greatsword of SolitudeSolitude Set", "HP": "14,129", "Stronger VS Sleep Madness": "Weaker to Lightning"}

name: Blessing of Marika
description: Blessing of Marika is a Consumable Item in Elden Ring. It was added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. Most Consumables grant various effects such as restorative properties for recovering HP, removing certain negative status effects or applying temporary buffs and debuffs, while others can be thrown at enemies to deal damage.
metadata: {"Effect Completely restores HP and heals all ailments": "Scaling -", "FP Cost": "-"}

name: Bloodfiend Hexer's Ashes
description: Bloodfiend Hexer's Ashes is a Spirit and Summon in Elden Ring. It is a brand-new Spirit in the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. Bloodfiend Hexer's Ashes uses a spear that enables it to cast bloodflame hexes.

name: Bloodhound Knight
description: Bloodhound Knight is a Field Boss in Elden Ring. Bloodhound Knight is a humanoid crawling on all fours, wielding a large curved sword, and is found in Lakeside Crystal Cave. This is an optional boss.
metadata: {"Location": "Lakeside Crystal Cave", "Drops": "2,700Cerulean Amber Medallion", "HP": "1,985", "Strong VS Standard Slash Strike": "Weak to Lightning"}

name: Bloodhound Knight Floh
description: Bloodhound Knight Floh is a Spirit and Summon in Elden Ring. Bloodhound Knight Floh is an aggressive melee spirit with attacks similar to that of the Bloodhound bosses.

name: Bols Carian Knight
description: Bols, Carian Knight is a Field Boss in Elden Ring. Bols is a hulking Troll Knight clad in heavy armor and wielding a massive greatsword. He is imprisoned within the Cuckoo's Evergaol in western Liurnia of the Lakes. This is an optional boss as players are not required to defeat it to advance in Elden Ring.
metadata: {"Location": "Cuckoo's Evergaol, Liurnia of the Lakes", "Drops": "4,600, Greatblade Phalanx", "HP": "5,109", "Strong VS Magic Frostbite": "Weak to Phy (Sla) Poison Scarlet Rot Hemorrhage", "wiki_url": "https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/Bols,+Carian+Knight"}

name: Bone Peddler's Bell Bearing
description: Bone Peddler's Bell Bearing is a Key Item in Elden Ring. Bone Peddler's Bell Bearing allows you to buy items from the Two Maiden Husks in Roundtable Hold. Key Items in Elden Ring include a wide variety of items found in specific locations or are given by a related NPCs which are used to unlock areas, quests, and to further progress the game's story.

name: Bonny Gaol
description: Bonny Gaol is a Location in Elden Ring. The Bonny Gaol is found across a wooden bridge, directly south of Bonny Village in southern Scadu Altus.

name: Bosses
description: Bosses in Elden Ring are powerful enemies that add challenging experiences to the game. Bosses are encountered throughout the game in both the overworld and inside traditional dungeon-style levels. While some must be fought to progress through the story, most are optional. Each boss features a unique set of moves, gear, and various weaknesses and resistances to different damage types and styles of play. Successfully defeating a boss grants the player more Runes than traditional enemies drop in their respective areas, and many offer rare and/or unique armaments, armor, magic, and other items. This page contains a list of all the bosses encountered in the game.

Greatshields weigh a lot but provide the best protection in the game. Greatshields provide a greater value of blocking and protecting oneself from enemy and boss attacks, but greatly increases the weight and reduces the player's mobility. This type of shield works best at reducing damage or guarding instead of parrying.

name: Caelid
description: Caelid is a Location and Region in Elden Ring. The Caelid region is located east of Limgrave. It's mainly defined by its red, corrupt environment and a great amount of undead roaming the open fields.

name: Castle Ensis
description: Castle Ensis is a Minor Legacy Dungeon in Elden Ring. Castle Ensis is a dungeon exclusive to the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. Castle Ensis can be located north-northeast of the Three Path Cross checkpoint (site of grace). Castle Ensis is a small castle where players can encounter scholars of magic, deadly hounds, noblemen capable of using magical attacks, and soldiers of Messmer.

name: Cathedral of Dragon Communion
description: Cathedral of Dragon Communion is a Location for Dragon Communion in Elden Ring. The Cathedral of Dragon Communion is found in Caelid, by following the road South and then venturing further south as it turns east. It is a separate location from Limgrave's Church of Dragon Communion.

name: Cave of the Forlorn
description: Cave of the Forlorn is a Location in Elden Ring. It can be found in the ravine south of the Minor Erdtree in the Consecrated Snowfield. The entrance is guarded by a Giant Land Octopus. In order to enter the cave, players need to use two Stonesword Keys.

name: Cerulean Coast
description: Cerulean Coast (Southern Shore) is a Location in Elden Ring. The Cerulean Coast region can be found south of the Gravesite Plain. [See Shadow of the Erdtree Map]

name: Charo's Hidden Grave
description: Charo's Hidden Grave is a Region/Location in Elden Ring, added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Charo's Hidden Grave is found in the south of Gravesite Plain, near Cerulean Coast. [See Shadow of the Erdtree Map]

name: Chief Bloodfiend
description: Chief Bloodfiend is a Great Enemy Boss in Elden Ring. Chief Bloodfiend is a large boss that is armed with a club and is found in Rivermouth Cave. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat it to advance in Elden Ring.
metadata: {"Location": "Rivermouth Cave", "Drops": "80,000Bloodfiend Hexer's Ashes", "HP": "21,948", "Stronger VS Fire Hemorrhage": "Weaker to Slash Poison Scarlet Rot Frostbite", "wiki_url": "https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/Chief+Bloodfiend"}

name: Commander Gaius
description: Commander Gaius is a Legend Boss in Elden Ring. Commander Gaius rides a boar into battle and uses several magic attacks and is found at the back of the Shadow Keep Legacy Dungeon. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat it to advance in Shadow of the Erdtree.
metadata: {"Location": "Scaduview", "Drops": "230,000Remembrance of the Wild Boar Rider", "HP": "33,871", "Strong VS Slash Hemorrhage Frostbite": "Weak to Holy"}

name: Consecrated Snowfield
description: Consecrated Snowfield is a Location in Elden Ring. The Consecrated Snowfield region is a secret area on the lower plains of the Mountaintops of the Giants, that can only be accessed by those that collect both parts of the Haligtree Secret Medallion. Haligtree Secret Medallion (Right) is found in Liurnia of the Lakes. Haligtree Secret Medallion (Left) is found in Mountaintops of the Giants. Once you have both pieces of the medallion, go to the Grand Lift of Rold and select "Hoist secret medallion" (make sure your action is "Hoist secret medallion" and not "Hoist medallion") to brandish your secret one.

name: Count Ymir Mother of Fingers
description: Count Ymir, Mother of Fingers is a Boss in Elden Ring. Count Ymir, Mother of Fingers is the High Priest who has taken power from Metyr, Mother of Fingers, and is found in the Cathedral of Manus Metyr. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat it to advance in Elden Ring.
metadata: {"Location": "Cathedral of Manus Metyr", "Drops": "210,000 Ymir's Bell BearingMaternal StaffHigh Priest Set", "HP": "16,673", "Stronger VS Magic Holy Sleep Immune to Scarlet Rot": "Weaker to Physical"}

name: Creatures and Enemies
description: Creatures and Enemies in Elden Ring are the wildlife and foes inhabiting the Lands Between. These hostile monsters, animals, and NPCs are fought in order to progress through the game, or to obtain different types of items and resources, like Runes, Spells, and Equipment. This page contains a list of all Elden Ring Enemies, each with their individual page containing specific information, such as stats, locations, drops, and resistances. Enemies in Elden Ring retain the dark, brooding style that FromSoftware is known for. Grotesque and imposing figures, as well as traps like fire contraptions and ballistae, will attempt to stop the player from completing the journey for the elusive Elden Ring.

name: Crucible Knight Siluria
description: Crucible Knight Siluria is a Greater Foe Boss in Elden Ring. Crucible Knight Siluria is one of the very few normal sized Bosses, they perform quick heavy attacks but they have not too much Health. It is found in Deeproot Depths. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat it to advance in Elden Ring.
metadata: {"Location": "Deeproot Depths", "Drops": "25,000Siluria's Tree", "HP": "4,606", "Stronger VS All status effects Immune to Hemorrhage": "Weaker to Fire Lightning"}

name: Crucible Knight and Misbegotten Warrior
description: Crucible Knight and Misbegotten Warrior is a Field Boss in Elden Ring. A fearsome Misbegotten and a stoic knight have come to Redmane Castle to test their strength. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat it to advance.

name: Crumbling Farum Azula
description: Crumbling Farum Azula is a Legacy Dungeon in Elden Ring. Crumbling Farum Azula may also be considered a very small region, which can be reached through the Site of Grace at the Forge of the Giants in Mountaintops of the Giants, either by talking to Melina or listening to the flame, depending on your prior decisions in the game.

name: Crystal Release
description: Crystal Release is a Sorcery in Elden Ring. Crystal Release spell bombards a large area with projectiles. Updated to Patch 1.07.

name: Crystal Tears
description: Crystal Tears in Elden Ring are Key Items that can be mixed in the Flask of Wondrous Physick for various special effects and buffs. This page covers their names, effects, durations, and Locations. These for the most part stack with additional buffs that can be applied to your character, and you are limited to only two Crystal Tears that can be put in your flask.

name: Curseblade Labirith
description: Curseblade Labirith is a Field Boss in Elden Ring. Curseblade Labirith can turn invisible during combat and is found in the depths of Bonny Gaol. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat it to advance in Elden Ring: Shadow of the Erdtree.
metadata: {"Location": "Bonny Gaol", "Drops": "100,000 Curseblade Meera", "HP": "8,426", "Stronger VS None": "Weaker to Slash Sleep"}

name: Curseblade Meera
description: Curseblade Meera is a Spirit and Summon in Elden Ring. It is a brand-new Spirit in the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. Curseblade Meera summons an agile and powerful Curseblade. It is dropped by defeating Curseblade Labirith, at Bonny Gaol.

name: Damage Types
description: Damage Type in Elden Ring is an important mechanic pertaining to Combat. Damage is divided into two major groups: Physical and Elemental. Damage Type is affected by many factors, including your equipment, skills and temporary buffs. Players and enemies can also inflict abnormal status effects which can deal or modify damage.

name: Dancer of Ranah
description: Dancer of Ranah is a Boss in Elden Ring Shadow of the Erdtree. Dancer of Ranah is an agile fighter with a unique attack style and is found in Southern Nameless Mausoleum in an island west from the Cerulean Coast. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat it to advance in Elden Ring.
metadata: {"Location": "Southern Nameless Mausoleum", "Drops": "80,000 Dancing Blade of RanahDancer's Set", "HP": "15,025", "Stronger VS Fire": "Weaker to Strike Pierce"}

name: Dancing Blade of Ranah
description: Dancing Blade of Ranah is a paired Curved Sword in Elden Ring. It is a brand new Curved Sword in the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Dancing Blade of Ranah scales primarily with Dexterity and is a good Weapon for Dexterity Builds that attack rapidly. This weapon comes with the Unending Dance Skill which lets you slash repeatedly until you drain your stamina.

name: Dane's Hat
description: Dane's Hat is a Helm in Elden Ring. It is a brand new Helm in the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. Dane's Hat is part of the Dane's Set, and is the hat of Dryleaf Dane. Dane's Hat protect the player's head by applying various defensive properties, it also changes the appearance as well when it is equipped. Some armor pieces may be available to both genders but may be slightly different for male and female characters.

name: Death Blight
description: Death Blight is a Status Effect in Elden Ring. Status Effects are various buffs or ailments that apply either a beneficial or detrimental effect to the target. Status Effects can typically be applied to both enemies and players alike, however Death Blight only affects other Tarnished. Status Effects are triggered after a buildup meter is filled by repeated application of attacks that cause the effect. Both players and enemies can have varying resistances to a given Status Effect.

name: Death Knight
description: Death Knight is a Field Boss in Elden Ring. Death Knight is a repeat boss that wields various weapons that can conjure lightning and is found standing guard in the catacombs. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat it to advance in Shadow of the Erdtree.
metadata: {"Stronger VS None Immune to Hemorrhage": "Weaker to Holy"}

name: Death Knight's Longhaft Axe
description: Death Knight's Longhaft Axe is a Greataxe in Elden Ring. It is a brand new Greataxe in the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Death Knight's Longhaft Axe scales primarily with Strength, Dexterity and Faith and is a good Weapon for faith players looking for a great axe. This weapon deals both physical and lightning damage and comes with the Blinkbolt: Long-hafted Axe skill that transforms you into a bolt of lightning that rushes down to enemies and follows up with a heavy attack.

name: Death Knight's Twin Axes
description: Death Knight's Twin Axes is an Axe in Elden Ring. It was added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Death Knight's Twin Axes scales primarily with Strength, Dexterity and Faith and is a good Weapon for faith builds. This comes with the Blinkbolt: Twinaxe skill, which transforms you into a bolt of lightning.

name: Deeproot Depths
description: Deeproot Depths is a Location in Elden Ring. The Deeproot Depths region is found underground and is accessed by resting in a coffin after defeating the Valiant Gargoyle in Siofra Aqueduct, or alternatively, through a hidden passage near the Frenzied Flame Proscription [Map] grace in the Subterranean Shunning-Grounds. From the Cathedral of the Forsaken grace (after defeating Mohg, the Omen), head through the hidden passage behind the chest and make your way to the Frenzied Flame Proscription grace at the very bottom. Roll into the southeastern wall to reveal a hidden passage with a chest and roll into the wall behind the chest to reveal yet another hidden passage and the Root-Facing Cliffs grace.

name: Demi-Human Queen Gilika
description: Demi-Human Queen Gilika is a Field Boss in Elden Ring. Demi-Human Queen Gilika is a large Demi-Human that wields a magical staff and is found in Altus Plateau. This is an optional boss, as players don't need to defeat it to advance in Elden Ring.

name: Demi-Human Queen Marigga
description: Demi-Human Queen Marigga is a Field Boss in Elden Ring. Demi-Human Queen Marigga has the appearance of a humanoid jackal and carries a staff. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat it to advance in Shadow of the Erdtree.
metadata: {"Location": "Cerulean Coast", "Drops": "100,000Star-Lined Sword", "HP": "9,793", "Stronger VS None": "Weaker to Fire Poison Scarlet Rot"}

name: Demi-Human Swordmaster Onze
description: Demi-Human Swordmaster Onze is a Great Enemy Boss in Elden Ring. Onze is a demi-human that, despite his appearance, skillfully wields a magic katana and is found at the bottom of the Belurat Gaol. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat it to advance in Shadow of the Erdtree.
metadata: {"Location": "Belurat Gaol", "Drops": "80,000 RunesDemi-Human Swordsman Yosh", "HP": "14,883", "Stronger VS None": "Weak to Slash Fire Poison Scarlet Rot"}

name: Demi-Human Swordsman Yosh
description: Demi-Human Swordsman Yosh is a Spirit and Summon in Elden Ring. It is a Spirit Ash in the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. Demi-Human Swordsman Yosh is a nimble and agile swordsman.

name: Demigods
description: Demigods are beings of incredible power in Elden Ring and comprise the royalty of those in the Lands Between. These deific figures descend from either Queen Marika the Eternal or her second Lord consort Radagon of the Golden Order. In the base game most of the Demigods go on to claim Great Runes of the shattered Elden Ring and vie for power in a struggle known as the Shattering. The first of the Demigods would be the Golden Linage descending from Queen Marika and Godfrey, First Elden Lord. Radagon would first wed Rennala, Queen of the Full Moon and together they have Demigod children who became prominent members of the Carian Royal Family. This family would become fractured when Radagon leaves Rennala to become the second Elden Lord after Godfrey is divested of Grace. Radagon and Marika have Demigod children together who would also gain the title of Empyreans.
metadata: {"Godfrey, First Elden Lord": "The first demigods were the Elden Lord Godfrey and his offspring, the golden lineage. Godfrey was a ferocious warrior. When he vowed to become a lord, he took the Beast Regent Serosh upon on his back to suppress the ceaseless lust for battle that raged within. The age of the Erdtree had begun amongst conflict, when Godfrey was known as the lord of the battlefield. He led the War against the Giants. Faced the Storm Lord, alone. And then, there came a moment. When his last worthy enemy fell. And it was then, as the story is told, that the hue of Lord Godfrey's eyes had faded. Godfrey was divested of his grace, becoming Tarnished, he then took his kinfolk and left the Lands Between. After the Long March of the Tarnished came to an end, Godfrey divested himself of kingship, becoming a simple warrior once more.", "Godwyn the Golden": "Godwyn the Golden was the son of Queen Marika and Lord Godfrey, and an important figure of the Golden Linage. His victorious role in the Ancient Dragon War earned him much acclaim as when the conflict concluded he had also earned the friendship of the ancient dragon Fortissax. He would come to wield the dragon's lightning as his own. On the Night of the Black Knives, Godwyn would be assassinated in soul and his body left to fester. Being the first of the Demigods to die after the Rune of Death had been sealed away, his passing was greatly mourned and attempts to bring him a true death did not succeed. Buried beneath Leyndell at the Erdtree's roots, deathroot emerged and spread across the land through the underground root system. Godwyn had become the Prince of Death, whose vile visage takes form in pustules and cysts.", "Godrick the Grafted": "Godrick the Grafted is the last descendant of the Golden Linage and bears a Great Rune. Declared weak by many, Godrick has been pushed out of his ancestral home and now resides in Stormveil Castle, using his army to capture prospective tarnished for the sake of grafting them onto himself in the belief that he will become stronger. Other victims of his include the Warhawks around the castle and innocents including Roderika's traveling party who left her a single memento. Godrick was likely responsible for attacking Leyndell in the First Defense of Leyndell, resulting in Godefroy's capture and he and his men having to flee from the capital. Still he hopes one day they'll return together to their home, bathed in rays of gold.", "Morgott, the Omen King": "Morgott, the Omen King is Mohg's twin, the discarded son of Queen Marika and Lord Godfrey, and bears a Great Rune. Together they were chained in Leyndell's sewers before eventually breaking free. Condoning his treatment and holding his curse in contempt, Morgott went under a disguised alias as Margit, the Fell Omen and defended Leyndell during the Second Defense of Leyndell. During the opening cinematic, Radahn is depicted as the aggressor of this conflict. Morgott rules Leyndell in the absence of his mother and viciously hunts down tarnished that seek the Elden Ring.", "Mohg, Lord of Blood": "Mohg, Lord of Blood is Morgott's twin, the discarded son of Queen Marika and Lord Godfrey, and bears a Great Rune. Together they were chained in Leyndell's sewers before eventually breaking free. Condoning his curse and holding his treatment in contempt, Mohg sought the blessing of an Outer God and to replace his mother's order with his own. Hoping to create his own dynasty, Mohg searched for other Great Runes and snuck into the Haligtree. Bewitched by Miquella, Mohg would regularly offer spoils of blood to the Empyrean's cocoon.", "Rykard, Lord of Blasphemy": "Praetor Rykard is the son of Radagon and Rennala and a member of the Carian Royals. He also bears a Great Rune. He came to inhabit Mt. Gelmir along with his inquisitors and committed numerous atrocities so that he could wage war with Leyndell. At some point he met Lady Tanith, who became his consort at Volcano Manor. In an effort to gain power, he let himself be devoured by an ancient serpent. Tarnished can join the Volcano Manor as recusants who hunt down their fellows, and those who excelled are allowed an audience with Rykard to become part of his family.", "Starscourge Radahn": "General Radahn is the son of Radagon and Rennala and a member of the Carian Royals. He also bears a Great Rune. General Radahn modeled himself after heroes of the battlefield such as Godfrey, Serosh, and his father, and he learned powerful gravity sorcery from an Alabaster Lord in Sellia. With this magic he was able to still ride his cherished horse even after he grew in size. Waging war even against the stars, Radahn held them in place and earned the Starscourge moniker. He took part in many conflicts during the Shattering and engaged Malenia in one final confrontation in Caelid. Now mindless from scarlet rot, he still roams the battlefield.", "Lunar Princess Ranni": "Ranni is the self-described daughter of Radagon and Rennala and a member of the Carian Royals. Though she came to bear a Great Rune, she cast it aside unlike the rest of her kin. She learned incredible sorceries from Rennala and a mysterious snow witch, and came to despise her eventual fate. As an Empyrean, she was chosen by the Two Fingers as a successor to Queen Marika. She is behind the plot of the Night of the Black Knives, resulting in Godwyn's demise and the discarding of her flesh. During the Shattering she returned to Carian Manor and operates with discretion along with her comrades to further change her fate.", "Miquella the Kind": "Kindly Miquella is one of the Twin Prodigies sired by Radagon and Queen Marika, and bore a Great Rune. Miquella was an Empyrean, and so a potential candidate to surpass his mother. Due to an affliction he was born with, this was unlikely to happen. Born to be forever young, Miquella sought out a way to cure his sister, bring a true death to Godwyn, and bring amnesty to those shunned by the Golden Order. Miquella's other half, St. Trina, could grant even the most tortured souls rest. With his ability to charm others Miquella wished to create a new order with his Haligtree which would allow him to grow into a god. All of his efforts failed and his body lies inert inside its cocoon. It seems without the strength of a Lord, Miquella could never bring an age of compassion.", "Malenia, Blade of Miquella": "Malenia is one of the Twin Prodigies sired by Radagon and Queen Marika, and bears a Great Rune. Malenia was an Empyrean, and so a potential candidate to surpass her mother. Due to an affliction she was born with, this was unlikely to happen. An Outer God chose Malenia as its vessel and only through teachings from the one who sealed it away could she manage to withhold her condition. Swearing to be her brother's protector, Malenia fought in numerous battles in his name and fought General Radahn to a standstill in Caelid, ultimately blooming into a Scarlet Aeonia that ravaged the land. Escorted back to the Haligtree by a heroic knight, she waits for her brother's return.", "Melina the Kindling Maiden": "Melina is heavily hinted to be the daughter of Queen Marika and so a demigod like the rest of her kin. She behaves much like a spirit, \"burned and bodiless\". By her own admission she was born at the foot of the Erdtree, and she can recall Spoken Echoes of Queen Marika at select locations. From within the Erdtree \"her mother\" tasked her with an important mission, and so she has searched the Lands Between for a worthy tarnished who will pursue the Elden Ring and to make an accord with them. She is likely the younger sister mentioned by Messmer's Kindling, the one who \"bore a vision of fire\".", "Messmer the Impaler": "Messmer the Impaler is the son of Queen Marika and leader of the crusade against the hornsent. Born with the curse of the abyssal serpent, Marika sealed away his power beneath his eye. Messmer was tasked by Queen Marika along with his Fire Knights and other forces of the Erdtree to crush the people of the Belurat Tower and was later ensnared in the land of shadow and removed from the Lands Between. He will carry out his mother's wishes until his last breath."}

name: Divine Beast Dancing Lion
description: Divine Beast Dancing Lion is a Legend Boss in Elden Ring. Divine Beast Dancing Lion is a powerful and fast boss that uses diverse elemental attacks and is found in Belurat, the Tower Settlement. This is an optional boss, as players do not need to defeat it to advance in Shadow of the Erdtree.

name: Divine Beast Head
description: Divine Beast Head is a Helm in Elden Ring. It is a brand-new Helm in the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. Divine Beast Head is not part of a set, and is literally the head of the Divine Beast Dancing Lion. Divine Beast Head protect the player's head by applying various defensive properties, it also changes the appearance as well when it is equipped. Some armor pieces may be available to both body types but may be slightly different depending on body type.

name: Divine Beast Tornado
description: Divine Beast Tornado is an Incantation in Elden Ring. It was added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. Divine Beast Tornado conjures a whirlwind and then launches a tornado forward.

name: Golem
description: Golems are a type of Giant Humanoid Enemy in Elden Ring. They are massive humanoid constructs created to protect and guard against intruders, wielding their massive weapons. Though large, their weakness is their low mobility and their ankles, which will topple them with ease.
metadata: {"Location": "StormhillCastle MorneAinsel River WellLeyndell, Royal Capital Mountaintops of the GiantsScadu AltusGravesite PlainRauh BaseAncient Ruins of Rauh", "Drops": "844 - 3927 Runes Golem's Halberd Golem Greatbow Great Arrow Golem's Great Arrow Golem's Magic Arrow Smithing Stones"}

name: Dragon's Pit
description: Dragon's Pit is a Location in Elden Ring, added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. It is found by following the path southwest of the Pillar Path Waypoint Site of Grace in Gravesite Plain.

name: Dragon-Hunter's Great Katana
description: Dragon-Hunter's Great Katana is a Great Katana in Elden Ring. It was added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Dragon-Hunter's Great Katana scales primarily with Strength and Dexterity and is a potent Weapon to oppose dragon-like creatures.
metadata: {"Attack Phy 152 Mag 0 Fire 0 Ligt 0 Holy 0 Crit 100": "Guard Phy 69 Mag 32 Fire 32 Ligt 32 Holy 32 Boost 37", "Scaling Str D Dex D": "Requires Str 15 Dex 20", "Great Katana": "Slash/Pierce", "Dragonwound Slash": "FP 18", "Wgt. 10.5": "Passive (55)", "wiki_url": "https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/Dragon-Hunter's+Great+Katana"}

name: Dragonbarrow
description: Greyoll's Dragonbarrow is a Location in Elden Ring. The Dragonbarrow region is the stretch of plateaus and hills located directly north of Caelid. Players can get to Dragonbarrow by heading up the hills east of Caelem Ruins and jumping over the chasm with Torrent. Alternatively, players can take the sending gate northeast of the Third Church of Marika in Limgrave which leads to the Bestial Sanctum in the northeastern tip of this sub-region.

name: Dragonclaw Shield
description: Dragonclaw Shield is a Greatshield in Elden Ring. The Dragonclaw Shield is a Shield that scales primarily with Strength and Dexterity. Greatshields weigh a decent amount and provide the best protection in the game. Greatshields provide a greater value of blocking and protecting oneself from enemy and boss attacks, but greatly increases the weight and reduces the player's mobility. This type of shield works best at reducing damage or guarding instead of parrying.

name: Dragonscale Flesh
description: Dragonscale Flesh is a Consumable Item in Elden Ring. It is a brand new Consumable Item in the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. Most Consumables grant various effects such as restorative properties for recovering HP, removing certain negative status effects or applying temporary buffs and debuffs, while others can be thrown at enemies to deal damage.
metadata: {"Effect Boosts vigor, stamina, strength, and dexterity at the cost of gradual HP loss": "Scaling -", "FP Cost": "-"}

name: Dryleaf Arts
description: Dryleaf Arts is a Hand-to-Hand Art in Elden Ring. It is an armament introduced in the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Dryleaf Arts scales primarily with Strength and Dexterity and is a good Weapon for those looking for rapid attacks with long combos.

name: Dryleaf Dane (Boss)
description: Dryleaf Dane is a Field Boss in Elden Ring. Dryleaf Dane is originally a friendly NPC, but can trigger a boss fight after acquiring the Monk's Missive note. He can be found in Moorth Ruins. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat it to advance in Shadow of the Erdtree.
metadata: {"Location": "Moorth Ruins", "Drops": "0Dane's HatDryleaf Arts", "HP": "18,321", "Stronger VS Magic Holy Sleep Madness": "Weaker to Standard Slash Pierce"}

name: Eastern Nameless Mausoleum
description: Eastern Nameless Mausoleum is a Location in Elden Ring, added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Eastern Nameless Mausoleum is found in the depths section of the Scadu Altus region, southeast of the Ruins of Unte. [See Shadow of the Erdtree Map]

name: Elden Throne
description: Elden Throne is a Location in Elden Ring, it is found in Leyndell, Royal Capital. You can reach the Elden Throne through the Queen's Bedchamber. Here the battle with Morgott, The Omen King takes place. After the fight, you can attempt to enter the Erdtree only for access to be denied, causing the Site of Grace to spawn in the center of the arena. Melina tells you that in order to unlock the entrance to the Erdtree you need to travel to Mountaintops of the Giants.

name: Ellac Greatbridge
description: Ellac Greatbridge is a Location in Elden Ring, added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Ellac Greatbridge is found north of Gravesite Plain. You can reach this place by riding north from the Three-Path Cross.

name: Elphael Brace of the Haligtree
description: Elphael, Brace of the Haligtree is a Legacy Dungeon in Elden Ring. Elphael, Brace of the Haligtree is a big castle that constitutes the second part of Miquella's Haligtree dungeon. It can be accessed after beating Loretta, Knight of the Haligtree by going down the elevator found shortly after.

name: Enir-Ilim
description: Enir-Ilim is a Legacy Dungeon in Elden Ring. Enir-Ilim is a dungeon exclusive to the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. You can gain access to an area containing a sealing tree by defeating Romina, Saint of the Bud in the Church of the Bud. You can then burn the sealing tree by using Messmer's Kindling, which you can obtain by defeating Messmer the Impaler. Enir-Ilim will reveal its true form after burning the sealing tree, teleporting you inside of it.

name: Erdtree Burial Watchdog
description: Erdtree Burial Watchdogs are Field Bosses in Elden Ring. These catlike hounds guard catacombs throughout the Lands Between, wielding swords and staves as well as elemental magic. These are optional bosses, meaning players don't need to defeat them in order to advance.
metadata: {"Immune to All Status Effects": "Weaker to Strike"}

name: Fia's Mist
description: Fia's Mist is a Sorcery in Elden Ring. Fia's Mist releases a mist of Deathblight before the caster.

name: Finger Ruins of Miyr
description: Finger Ruins of Miyr is a Location in Elden Ring, added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Finger Ruins of Miyr are found in Scadu Altus region, can be reached from the secret entrance under the throne in Cathedral of Manus Metyr. [See Shadow of the Erdtree Map]

name: Finger Ruins of Rhia
description: Finger Ruins of Rhia is a Region/Location in Elden Ring, added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Finger Ruins of Rhia is found in the Southern Shore region. You can reach this location by heading south from Cerulean Coast site of grace. When you are about to reach Cerulean Coast Cross, turn to northeast direction and travel along the coastline until you reach a sloped coffin ship. At this point, proceed north and the Finger Ruins of Rhia site of grace can be found on edge of a nearby cliff. [See Shadow of the Erdtree Map]

name: Fire Damage
description: Fire Damage is one of the Damage Types in Elden Ring. It is one of the eight main Damage Types and belongs to the Elemental Damage category. Damage Types are a major part of the calculation that determines how much damage is dealt in Combat and are affected by many factors including your equipment, skills and temporary buffs.

name: Fire Defense
description: Fire Defense is a Defensive Stat in Elden Ring. Fire Defense shows your defense power and damage negation against fire attacks. Stats determine the strengths and weaknesses of your character. Defensive Stats are determined by your Attributes and Equipment.
metadata: {"Type": "Defensive Stat", "Effect": "Shows your current defense against Fire damage"}

name: Flame Peak
description: Flame Peak is a Location in Elden Ring. The Flame Peak is found in Mountaintops of the Giants. South of the Guardian's Garrison, past the hanging chain.

name: Fog Rift Catacombs
description: Fog Rift Catacombs is a Location in Elden Ring, added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Fog Rift Catacombs are found in the southeast Rauh Ruins region.

name: Fog Rift Fort
description: Fog Rift Fort is a Location in Elden Ring, added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Fog Rift Fort is found in the Gravesite Plain region. You can reach this place by dropping down the rocky platforms near Scadu Altus, West Site of Grace.

name: Forbidden Lands
description: Forbidden Lands is a Location in Elden Ring. The Forbidden Lands region is a snow-covered area always enshrouded by thick fog. The Forbidden Lands is the only traversable path that connects the Altus Plateau with the Mountaintops of the Giants and Consecrated Snowfield. This path lies beyond the eastern end of Capital Outskirts and leads to the Grand Lift of Rold.

name: Fort of Reprimand
description: Fort of Reprimand is a Location in Elden Ring, added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Fort of Reprimand is in Scadu Altus, south of Moorth Highway. This place can also be reached from the spiritspring north to the Elder's Hovel.

name: Frostbite
description: Frostbite is a Status Effect in Elden Ring. Status Effects are various buffs or ailments that apply either a beneficial or detrimental effect to the target. Status Effects can be applied on both enemies and players alike. Status Effects are triggered after a buildup meter is filled by repeated application of attacks that cause the effect. Both players and enemies can have varying resistances to a given Status Effect.
metadata: {"Effect": "Deals damage and lowers target's damage absorption by 20%", "Mitigated by": "Invigorating Cured MeatStalwart Horn Charm", "Cured by": "Bestial ConstitutionThawfrost Boluses", "Resistive Stat": "Robustness"}

name: Full-Grown Fallingstar Beast
description: Full-Grown Fallingstar Beast is a Field Boss in Elden Ring. Full-Grown Fallingstar Beast is a four legged boss with rapid movement and is found in Mt. Gelmir. This is an optional boss, as players don't need to defeat it in order to advance in Elden Ring. However, doing so yields useful Items and Runes.
metadata: {"Location": "Mt. Gelmir", "HP": "13,010", "Strong VS Standard Slash Strike Pierce Immune to Hemorrhage Frostbite": "Weaker to Magic Fire Lightning Holy"}

name: Ghostflame Dragon
description: Ghostflame Dragon is a Field Boss in Elden Ring. Ghostflame Dragon is a massive dragon with withered wings and exposed bones. This boss is found throughout the Lands of Shadow. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat it to advance in Elden Ring: Shadow of the Erdtree.
metadata: {"Strong VS Magic Immune to Hemorrhage Frostbite Poison": "Weak to Strike Holy"}

name: Giants' Mountaintop Catacombs
description: Giants' Mountaintop Catacombs is a Location in Elden Ring. The Giants' Mountaintop Catacombs is found in the Mountaintops of the Giants region. To find this dungeon, go north from Zamor Ruins until you reach the bridge with fire monks, then turn south east and follow the slope down to the door.

name: Glintstone Sorcerer Ashes
description: Glintstone Sorcerer Ashes is a Spirit and Summon in Elden Ring. Glintstone Sorcerer Ashes summons the spirit of a glintstone sorcerer.

name: Glovewort Picker's Bell Bearing (2)
description: Glovewort Picker's Bell Bearing [2] is a Key Item in Elden Ring. Glovewort Picker's Bell Bearing [2] can be offered to the Twin Maiden Husks to gain access to new shop items. Key Items in Elden Ring include a wide variety of items found in specific locations or are given by a related NPCs which are used to unlock areas, quests, and to further progress the game's story.

name: Godfrey, First Elden Lord
description: Godfrey, First Elden Lord and Hoarah Loux, Warrior is a two-phase Legend Boss in Elden Ring. Godfrey was Queen Marika's first consort, and thus the first Elden Lord of the Lands Between. Before earning this title, he was known as Hoarah Loux, the chieftain of the badlands and a bloodthirsty warrior. Godfrey took the Beast Regent Serosh upon his back after committing to his role as a Lord in order to suppress his violent urges. After fighting countless wars, Marika deprived him and his warriors of their grace, marking them as the first Tarnished.
metadata: {"Location": "Leyndell, Ashen Capital", "Drops": "300,000Remembrance of Hoarah Loux", "HP": "21,903", "Strong vs Holy Sleep (Phase 2)": "Weak to Pierce (Phase 1) Lightning (Phase 1) Slash (Phase 2)", "wiki_url": "https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/Godfrey,+First+Elden+Lord"}

name: Godrick's Great Rune
description: Godrick's Great Rune is a Great Rune in Elden Ring. Godrick's Great Rune Raises all attributes. Great Runes in Elden Ring are special items dropped by Demigod Bosses that can be equipped to acquire special passive bonuses.

name: Godskin Apostle Set
description: Godskin Apostle Set is an Armor Set in Elden Ring. It provides minimal physical and magic damage negation and minimal resistance. The armor is lightweight and will total 10.9 meaning it can be used to achieve a light load on any build. Sets of Armor in Elden Ring are composed of four armor pieces which are Helms, Chest Armor, Gauntlets, and Leg Armor.

name: Godskin Noble Set
description: Godskin Noble Set is an Armor Set in Elden Ring. Godskin Noble Set is a gruesome amalgamation of smooth skin sewn together. Sets of Armor in Elden Ring are composed of four armor pieces which are Helms, Chest Armor, Gauntlets, and Leg Armor.

name: Golden Scarab
description: Gold Scarab is a Talisman in Elden Ring. Gold Scarab increases Rune acquisition by 20%. Players can use talismans in Elden Ring to boost a variety of Stats.

name: Golden Beast Crest Shield
description: Golden Beast Crest Shield is a Greatshield in Elden Ring. The Golden Beast Crest Shield is a Shield that scales primarily with Strength. Greatshields weigh a decent amount and provide the best protection in the game. Greatshields provide a greater value of blocking and protecting oneself from enemy and boss attacks, but greatly increases the weight and reduces the player's mobility. This type of shield works best at reducing damage or guarding instead of parrying.
