name: Golden Hippopotamus
description: Golden Hippopotamus is a Great Enemy Boss in Elden Ring. Golden Hippopotamus can be found resting near the foot of the giant Marika Statue in Shadow Keep. Once you enter the arena, the boss will charge toward you and start the fight. The Golden Hippopotamus is an optional boss. Defeating the Golden Hippopotamus will reward players with Aspects of the Crucible: Thorns and x2 Scadutree Fragments, and allow further exploration of Shadow Keep.
metadata: {"HP": "33,866", "Strong VS Hemorrhage Frostbite": "Weak to Fire Lightning"}

name: Golden Rune (1)
description: Golden Rune [1] is a Consumable Item in Elden Ring that grants 200 Runes upon use. These can sometimes be looted from Glowing Skulls that spawn throughout the map. Clear them to obtain their dropped loot.

name: Grand Cloister
description: Grand Cloister is a Location in Elden Ring. The Grand Cloister is found in Lake of Rot. You can reach it by going down the stairs by the waterfall in the southern section of the Lake of Rot. (Map Link)

name: Grave Warden Duelist
description: Grave Warden Duelist is a Boss in Elden Ring. Former gladiators who protect gravesites. They fight with dual battle hammers on chains, and will often grab opponents and slam them down. These are optional bosses, as players don't need to defeat it in order to advance.

name: Gravesite Plain
description: Gravesite Plain is a Location in Elden Ring. The Gravesite Plain region is added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC, located in the realm of shadow. [See Shadow of the Erdtree Map]

name: Gravitational Missile
description: Gravitational Missile is a Sorcery in Elden Ring. It was added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. Gravitational Missile creates a gravitational orb that pulls enemies towards it, pulsating before exploding.

name: Gravity Stone Peddler's Bell Bearing
description: Gravity Stone Peddler's Bell Bearing is a Key Item in Elden Ring. Gravity Stone Peddler's Bell Bearing allows you to buy items from the Twin Maiden Husks in Roundtable Hold. Key Items in Elden Ring include a wide variety of items found in specific locations or are given by a related NPCs which are used to unlock areas, quests, and to further progress the game's story.

name: Great Rune of the Unborn
description: Great Rune of the Unborn is a Great Rune in Elden Ring. Great Rune of the Unborn provides the perfect rebirth ability. Great Runes in Elden Ring are special items dropped by Demigod Bosses that can be equipped to acquire special passive bonuses.

name: Great Runes
description: Great Runes in Elden Ring are Key Items dropped by shardbearer Bosses whose powers can be unlocked at Divine Towers and then activated with Rune Arcs to strengthen the player until death. This page covers how to activate them, their names, effects, respective bosses, and Locations.

name: Greatblade Phalanx
description: Greatblade Phalanx is a Sorcery in Elden Ring. Greatblade Phalanx spell summons greatblades that float around the caster and attack enemies when they move close enough. Updated to Patch 1.07.

name: Greatsword of Solitude
description: Greatsword of Solitude is a Greatsword in Elden Ring. It is a brand new Greatsword in the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Greatsword of Solitude scales primarily with Strength and Dexterity and is a good Weapon for pure Strength Builds. Its weapon skill, the Solitary Moon Slash, lets you summon light that can damage your enemies.

name: Hallowhorn Grounds
description: Hallowhorn Grounds is a Location in Elden Ring. Two Hallowhorn Grounds exist in the game. One is found in the south-east of the Siofra River region in a big open space. It can be easily reached from the Siofra River Bank Site of Grace. Another is found in Nokron, Eternal City, north-east of the Ancestral Woods Site of Grace.

name: Heart of Bayle
description: Heart of Bayle is a Key Item in Elden Ring. It is a brand new Key Item in the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. Key Items in Elden Ring include a wide variety of items found in specific locations or are given by a related NPCs which are used to unlock areas, quests, and to further progress the game's story.

Both players and enemies can have varying resistances to a given Status Effect.

name: Horned Bairn
description: Horned Bairn is a Tool in Elden Ring. It is a Tool found in the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. Horned Bairn uses FP to summon vengeful spirits surrounding caster.

name: Elden Ring Map: Interactive
description: Elden Ring Map (Interactive): Find and track all Items, Bosses and Npcs in the game with our interactive map. Our Elden Ring Full Map is regularly updated with detailed information for all Quests, Equipment, Bosses and Locations, and much more! From Walking Mausoleums to special Teardrop Scarabs or NPC locations, you can find everything you need on this Elden Ring Map.

Most Consumables grant various effects such as restorative properties for recovering HP, removing certain negative status effects or applying temporary buffs and debuffs, while others can be thrown at enemies to deal damage.

name: Iron Rivet Set
description: Iron Rivet Set is an Armor Set in Elden Ring. It is a brand new Armor Set in the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. Sets of Armor in Elden Ring are composed of four armor pieces which are Helms, Chest Armor, Gauntlets, and Leg Armor. This set is good for early to med-game with decent resistance.

name: Jagged Peak
description: Jagged Peak is a Location in Elden Ring, added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Jagged Peak is a mountainous region southeast of Gravesite Plain. You can reach this region by heading southeast from Castle Front, enter the Castle Front, and then head east and pass through Dragon's Pit. [See Shadow of the Erdtree Map]

name: Jagged Peak Drake
description: Jagged Peak Drake is a Boss in Elden Ring. They are large dragons said to have come from the bloodline of Bayle, and in turn have inherited his power to conjure flame lightning. The first Drake is fought at the foothills of the Jagged Peak, while two others are fought on the way upwards. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat it to advance in Elden Ring.

name: Jori Elder Inquisitor
description: Jori, Elder Inquisitor is a Boss in Elden Ring. Jori, Elder Inquisitor is a hornsent summoner who wields the Barbed Staff-Spear and is found as the boss of the Darklight Catacombs, guarding the entrance to the Abyssal Woods. This is an optional boss as players do not need to defeat it to advance in Shadow of the Erdtree.
metadata: {"Location": "Darklight Catacombs", "Drops": "260,000Barbed Staff-Spear", "HP": "30,506", "Stronger VS None": "Weaker to Slash Fire"}

name: Lake of Rot
description: Lake of Rot is a Location in Elden Ring. The Lake of Rot region features treacherous red waters that inflict scarlet rot on players that stay in it too long. You can reach it from Ainsel River Main, by heading south-west from the Nokstella Waterfall Basin Site of Grace (find it on the Interactive Map here).

name: Lamenter
description: Lamenter is a Boss in Elden Ring. Lamenter is a small but sneaky boss that uses clones as its main attacking method and is found in Lamenter's Gaol. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat it to advance in Elden Ring.
metadata: {"Location": "Lamenter's Gaol", "Drops": "160,000 Lamenter's Mask", "HP": "54,963", "Stronger VS Magic Fire Holy": "Weaker to Lightning Physical"}

name: Lamenter's Gaol
description: Lamenter's Gaol is a Location in Elden Ring, added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Lamenter's Gaol is found in southwest part of Charo's Hidden Grave region. You can reach this place by heading south down the cliffside near Ensis Castle and following the river down, or by going through Dragon's Pit and heading southwest.

name: Lamenter's Mask
description: Lamenter's Mask is a reusable Tool in Elden Ring. It was added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. Tools are unique, reusable items which assist the player during various facets of gameplay, ranging from basic communication to assisting in boss encounters.
metadata: {"Effect Transforms wearer into a lamenter and causes head to swell in size": "Scaling Str B", "FP Cost": "-"}

name: Leda and Allies Boss
description: Leda and Allies is an NPC battle in Elden Ring exclusive to the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. Needle Knight Leda leads a band of Miquella's faithful to prevent you from stopping him from becoming a god. This is not an optional battle as players must defeat them to advance in Shadow of the Erdtree.

name: Legacy Dungeons
description: Legacy Dungeons in Elden Ring are special fortresses and areas with significant challenge and exploration rewards. Legacy Dungeons are home to Lords, and players will access them to challenge the Bosses that dwell within and obtain pieces of the Elden Ring. You cannot ride Torrent within these locations.

name: Leyndell Royal Capital (Legacy Dungeon)
description: Leyndell, Royal Capital is a Legacy Dungeon in Elden Ring. A sprawling capital city that houses various strong enemies, as well as champions that were previously encountered. The Royal Capital of Leyndell functions as the seat of government and administrative center of Altus Plateau. For an overview of this location outside of the "dungeon", visit our location page for Leyndell, Royal Capital.

name: Leyndell, Ashen Capital
description: Leyndell, Ashen Capital is a Location in Elden Ring. Leyndell, Ashen Capital is an instance of Leyndell, Royal Capital after it falls into ruin. This version of the capital is accessible only after making significant story progress, and is geared towards high-leveled players. The Ashen Capital features the same structures and landmarks as its intact counterpart, albeit significantly altered. Previously open paths may not be accessible and vice versa. The Ashen Capital also features its own set of Enemies, Bosses, and collectibles with varied placement distinct from the regular version of the city.

name: Leyndell Royal Capital
description: Leyndell, Royal Capital is a Location in Elden Ring. The Leyndell, Royal Capital northeastern gate is accessible to players who have gathered two Great Runes, but cannot be accessed without visiting the Roundtable Hold. For a detailed walkthrough, please visit the walkthrough page for Leyndell, Royal Capital Legacy Dungeon.

name: Lhutel the Headless
description: Lhutel the Headless is a Legendary Spirit and Summon in Elden Ring. Summons an allied spirit version of an unmounted Mausoleum Knight.

name: Lightning Damage
description: Lightning Damage is one of the Damage Types in Elden Ring. It is one of the eight main Damage Types and belongs to the Elemental Damage category. Damage Types are a major part of the calculation that determines how much damage is dealt in Combat and are affected by many factors including your equipment, skills and temporary buffs.

name: Lightning Defense
description: Lightning Defense is a Defensive Stat in Elden Ring. Lightning Defense shows your defense power and damage negation against lightning attacks. Stats determine the strengths and weaknesses of your character. Defensive Stats are determined by your Attributes and Equipment.
metadata: {"Type": "Defensive Stat", "Effect": "Shows your current defense against Lightning damage"}

name: Limgrave
description: Limgrave is a Location and Region in Elden Ring. The Limgrave region is the first accessible area of the game. Players will emerge from one of the underground catacombs and be treated to Limgrave's lush environments and scenery.

name: Elder Lion
description: Elder Lion is an Enemy in Elden Ring. Elder Lions are aggressive beasts that serve as guard animals, and fight with their sharp claws and a blade attached to their right arm. Once slain, they do not respawn.
metadata: {"Location": "Stormveil CastleFort Gael (Caelid)Redmane CastleCastle SolLeyndell, Royal Capital", "HP": "2,119 - 7,019 HP", "Strong VS Hemorrhage Frostbite": "Weak to Phy (Slash) Fire"}

name: Liurnia of the Lakes
description: Liurnia of the Lakes is one of the major continental areas in the world of Elden Ring. Found northwest of the starting area of Limgrave, this region has been the common backdrop of pre-launch images of the game, notably due to the prominent placement of The Academy of Raya Lucaria overlooking the misty lake below. It can be initially accessed via the passage beneath Godrick the Grafted's throne room in Stormveil Castle, or by following a narrow cliffside path around the east edge of the castle in northern Stormhill.

name: Locations
description: Locations in Elden Ring are vast and interconnected. The world of Elden Ring is a persistent Map that can be traversed without loading screens. There are vast landscapes in between the dungeon-esque areas. The larger world scale allows for freedom, promotes exploration, and introduces new and exciting mechanics, such as Horse Riding and Mounted Combat. There are no towns and villagers, as the world has collapsed due to the Shattering, but many NPCs and merchants can be found scattered throughout the world. There are plenty of ruins, dungeons and exploration hubs.

name: Lord Contender's Evergaol
description: Lord Contender's Evergaol is a Location in Elden Ring. The Lord Contender's Evergaol is found in Mountaintops of the Giants. Found at the southwest bank of the frozen lake. Activate it to fight Roundtable Knight Vyke.

name: Loretta's Greatbow
description: Loretta's Greatbow is a Sorcery in Elden Ring. Loretta's Greatbow spell creates a bow that fires a projectile. Can be charged to further increase damage. Updated to Patch 1.07.

name: Loretta's Mastery
description: Loretta's Mastery is a Sorcery in Elden Ring. Loretta's Mastery spell, unlike the Loretta's Greatbow that shoots one arrow from a magic greatbow, this Sorcery fires four great arrows at once. Updated to Patch 1.07.

name: Loretta, Knight of the Haligtree
description: Loretta, Knight of the Haligtree is a Greater Foe Boss in Elden Ring. This proud knight was previously in service to the Carian royal family. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat her to advance in Elden Ring, though they do need to defeat her to reach Elphael, Brace of the Haligtree and face Malenia, Blade of Miquella.
metadata: {"Location": "Miquella's Haligtree", "Drops": "200,000Loretta's MasteryLoretta's War Sickle", "HP": "13,397", "Stronger VS Magic Fire Hemorrhage Frostbite": "Weaker to Lightning"}

name: Madness
description: Madness is a Status Effect in Elden Ring. Status Effects are various buffs or ailments that apply either a beneficial or detrimental effect to the target. Status Effects can be applied to both enemies and players alike. Status Effects are triggered after a buildup meter is filled by repeated application of attacks that cause the effect. Both players and enemies can have varying resistances to a given Status Effect.
metadata: {"Effect": "Target loses FP and takes health damage", "Mitigated by": "Clarifying Cured MeatClarifying Horn Charm", "Cured by": "Clarifying BolusesLucidity", "Resistive Stat": "Focus"}

name: Magic Damage
description: Magic Damage is one of the Damage Types in Elden Ring. It is one of the eight main Damage Types and belongs to the Elemental Damage category. Damage Types are a major part of the calculation that determines how much damage is dealt in Combat and are affected by many factors including your equipment, skills and temporary buffs.

name: Magic Defense
description: Magic Defense is a Defensive Stat in Elden Ring. Magic Defense shows your defense power and damage negation against magical attacks. Stats determine the strengths and weaknesses of your character. Defensive Stats are determined by your attributes and Equipment.
metadata: {"Type": "Defensive Stat", "Effect": "Shows your current defense against Magic attacks"}

description: Magic Spells in Elden Ring are cast by players in the form of Sorceries and Incantations. From conjuring glintstone pebbles to invoking the power of a dragon's breath, spells cover a wide variety of offensive, defensive, and utility functions. This page covers the basics of using spells and each spell available in the game.

name: Malenia's Great Rune
description: Malenia's Great Rune, also known as the Rune of Decay, is a Great Rune in Elden Ring. Great Runes in Elden Ring are special items dropped by Demigod Bosses that can be equipped to acquire special passive bonuses.

name: Malenia Blade of Miquella
description: Malenia, Blade of Miquella and Malenia, Goddess of Rot is a two-phase Demigod Boss in Elden Ring. She is the Empyrean twin sister of Miquella and gained renown for her legendary battle against Starscourge Radahn during the Shattering, in which she unleashed the power of the Scarlet Rot and reduced Caelid to ruins. This is an optional boss, as players do not need to defeat her in order to advance in Elden Ring.

name: Mantle of Thorns
description: Mantle of Thorns is a Sorcery in Elden Ring. It was added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. Mantle of Thorns covers the caster's body with piercing Scadutree thorns.

name: Margit, The Fell Omen
description: Margit, the Fell Omen is a Great Enemy Boss in Elden Ring. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat him to advance in Elden Ring, though they do need to defeat Margit to advance to Stormveil Castle.

name: Maternal Staff
description: Maternal Staff is a Glintstone Staff in Elden Ring. It was added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Maternal Staff scales primarily with Intelligence and Arcane and is a good Weapon for INT/ARC Builds and those using Finger Sorceries.

name: Meat Peddler's Bell Bearing
description: Meat Peddler's Bell Bearing is a Key Item in Elden Ring. Meat Peddler's Bell Bearing can be used to offer to the Twin Maiden Husks for new items access. Key Items in Elden Ring include a wide variety of items found in specific locations or are given by a related NPCs which are used to unlock areas, quests, and to further progress the game's story.

name: Medicine Peddler's Bell Bearing
description: Medicine Peddler's Bell Bearing is a Key Item in Elden Ring. Medicine Peddler's Bell Bearing allows you to buy items from the Twin Maiden Husks in Roundtable Hold. Key Items in Elden Ring include a wide variety of items found in specific locations or are given by a related NPCs which are used to unlock areas, quests, and to further progress the game's story.

name: Mending Rune of Perfect Order
description: Mending Rune of Perfect Order is a Great Rune in Elden Ring. Unlike most other Great Runes, it can't be equipped. Its only effect is to alter the ending of the game.

name: Mending Rune of the Death-Prince
description: Mending Rune of the Death-Prince is a Great Rune in Elden Ring. Unlike most other Great Runes, it can't be equipped. Its only effect is to alter the ending of the game.

name: Messmer's Kindling
description: Messmer's Kindling is a Key Item in Elden Ring. It is a brand new Key Item in the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. Key Items in Elden Ring include a wide variety of items found in specific locations or are given by a related NPCs which are used to unlock areas, quests, and to further progress the game's story.

name: Meteorite
description: Meteorite is a Sorcery in Elden Ring. Meteorite spell is cast to create 3 offensive meteorites that fall from the sky.

name: Meteorite of Astel
description: Meteorite of Astel is a Sorcery in Elden Ring. Meteorite of Astel spell allows you to call a hail of small meteorites from the void.

name: Metyr Mother of Fingers
description: Metyr, Mother of Fingers is a Legend Boss in Elden Ring. Metyr, Mother of Fingers is a large monster that is composed of several fingers with two arms in front, and has a stomach made of smaller fingers, and is found in the Finger Ruins of Miyr. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat it to advance in Shadows of the Erdtree.
metadata: {"Location": "Finger Ruins of Miyr", "Drops": "420,000Remembrance of the Mother of Fingers", "HP": "43,296", "Stronger VS Magic Fire Lightning Holy": "Weaker to Slash"}

name: Midra's Manse
description: Midra's Manse is a Minor Legacy Dungeon in Elden Ring. Midra's Manse is a dungeon exclusive to the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. It is located in the Abyssal Woods region, southeast of the Dragon's Pit Terminus Site of Grace [See Elden Ring Map].

name: Midra Lord of Frenzied Flame
description: Midra, Lord of Frenzied Flame is a Legend Boss in Elden Ring. He is the embodiment of the Frenzied Flame found in Midra's Manse. This is an optional boss as players do not need to defeat it to advance in Shadow of the Erdtree.
metadata: {"Location": "Midra's Manse", "Drops": "410,000 Remembrance of the Lord of Frenzied Flame", "HP": "47,171", "Stronger VS Fire Poison Scarlet Rot": "Weaker to Slash", "wiki_url": "https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/Midra,+Lord+of+Frenzied+Flame"}

name: Miquella's Great Rune
description: Miquella's Great Rune, also known as the Rune of Abundance, is a Great Rune in Elden Ring. It is a brand-new Great Rune introduced in the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. Unlike other Great Runes, it functions as a reusable Tool rather than a Key Item.

name: Miquella's Haligtree
description: Miquella's Haligtree is a Legacy Dungeon in Elden Ring. Miquella's Haligtree is found far to the north of the Consecrated Snowfield and the entire Lands Between. You'll find yourself on the canopy of a great branching tree, fighting against deadly foes. If you're looking for the castle area situated within Miquella's Haligtree, visit Elphael, Brace of the Haligtree. [Elden Ring Map here]

name: Misbegotten Warrior
description: Misbegotten Warrior is an Enemy in Elden Ring. Misbegotten Warrior is a stronger variant of the feral Misbegotten and is found in multiple places throughout the Lands Between, and is a serious obstacle to those who come across it. In battle they buff themselves with a roar and wield an Iron Greatsword.

name: Mohg's Great Rune
description: Mohg's Great Rune is a Great Rune and Multiplayer Item in Elden Ring. Great Runes in Elden Ring are special items dropped by Demigod Bosses that can be equipped to acquire special passive bonuses.

name: Mohgwyn Palace
description: Mohgwyn Palace is a Location in Elden Ring. The Mohgwyn Palace region is found beneath Caelid, but is only accessible from a gateway teleporter in the frozen west of Consecrated Snowfield (northwest of the Yelough Anix Ruins and west of where the Sanguine Noble invades you) or by using the Pureblood Knight's Medal given by White Mask Varr at the end of his questline.

name: Moorth Ruins
description: Moorth Ruins is a Location in Elden Ring, added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Moorth Ruins are found in the Scadu Altus region. You can reach this location by following Moorth Highway south, it's on the east side of the road.

name: Morgott's Great Rune
description: Morgott's Great Rune is a Great Rune in Elden Ring. Morgott's Great Rune raises maximum HP. Great Runes in Elden Ring are special items dropped by Demigod Bosses that can be equipped to acquire special passive bonuses.

name: Morgott the Omen King
description: Morgott, The Omen King, also known as Morgott the Grace Given, is a Demigod Boss in Elden Ring. Morgott is the true identity of Margit, the Fell Omen, and the self-proclaimed "Last of All Kings". Although he and his twin brother Mohg were imprisoned deep in the Subterranean Shunning-Grounds for being born as Omen royalty, Morgott still loved the Golden Order and defended the capital when his fellow demigods invaded during the Shattering. This is not an optional boss as players must defeat him to advance in Elden Ring.
metadata: {"Location": "Leyndell, Royal Capital", "HP": "10,399", "Stronger VS Holy Sleep": "Weak to Slash", "wiki_url": "https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/Morgott+the+Omen+King"}

name: Mountaintops of the Giants
description: Mountaintops of the Giants is a Location in Elden Ring. The Mountaintops of the Giants region is located at the very north-east of The Lands Between, and showcases the powerful devastation that overcame the Giants who used to dwell here.

name: Mt Gelmir
description: Mt. Gelmir is a Location in Elden Ring. Mt. Gelmir is a volcanic region found north of Liurnia and west of Altus Plateau. The mountain proper can be accessed by either:

name: Multiplayer Coop and Online
description: Multiplayer Coop and Online for Elden Ring contains information on the various features contained within online mode. Elden Ring Multiplayer contains various modes, from cooperative game styles in PvE, to competitive game modes in PvP and Invasions. Online players can make Gestures that may even include some vocal expression, and every player at close range will hear them.

name: NPC Summons
description: NPC Summons in Elden Ring are the summonable cooperator NPCs that can be available in a boss fight. These are different from Spirit Ashes and can be activated by using their summon signs that appear in gold. A number of NPC summons have been added since the 1.03 Patch. These are specific to each boss and may have conditions that must be met before they are available as a summon. These conditions could be simple or part of different questlines and may require you to find each NPC and exhaust their dialogue before they become available. When they become available, their sign will usually be visible just outside of the boss fog gates where they can be summoned. Below is the list of NPC Summons and the conditions required.

name: Noble Sorcerer Ashes
description: Noble Sorcerer Ashes is a Spirit and Summon in Elden Ring. Noble Sorcerer Ashes summons a Sorcerer that can move and use spells to attack enemies from a distance.

name: Nokron, Eternal City
description: Nokron, Eternal City is a Location in Elden Ring. The Nokron, Eternal City region is a sprawling city ruin located a level above the Siofra River. Much like the Siofra River, this underground region has features that you could mistake for an overland area - the fauna, growing vegetation, and a sky seemingly filled with stars. You can reach this area by going down Starfall Crater in southern Mistwood created by a falling star after you've defeated Starscourge Radahn. See below for the location the meteor falls on your map. One of the Eternal Cities, its sister city is Nokstella.

name: Northern Nameless Mausoleum
description: Northern Nameless Mausoleum is a Location in Elden Ring, added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Northern Nameless Mausoleum is found in the Gravesite Plain region.

name: Omenkiller Rollo
description: Omenkiller Rollo is a Spirit and Summon in Elden Ring. Omenkiller Rollo. Once a famous perfumer, Rollo imbibed a physick to rid himself of emotion, thus enabling him to enact his nightmarish labor, hunting the Omen.

name: Omenkiller and Miranda, the Blighted Bloom
description: Omenkiller and Miranda Flower is a Field Boss in Elden Ring. The hunter of cursed omens fights alongside a giant, toxic bloom in Perfumer's Grotto. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat it to advance.
metadata: {"Location": "Perfumer's Grotto", "Drops": "8,400Great Omenkiller Cleaver", "HP": "5,212", "Strong VS Fire Poison Scarlet Rot": "Weaker to Physical Sleep", "Strong VS Strike Lightning Holy Poison": "Weak to Slash Fire Frostbite"}

name: Pelt of Ralva
description: Pelt of Ralva is a Helm in Elden Ring. It is a brand-new Helm in the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. Pelt of Ralva is part of the Iron Rivet Set, and grants players a feral look, with the pelt of the beast. Pelt of Ralva protect the player's head by applying various defensive properties, it also changes the appearance as well when it is equipped. Some armor pieces may be available to both genders, but may be slightly different for male and female characters.

name: Perfumer's Grotto
description: Perfumer's Grotto is a Location in Elden Ring. The Perfumer's Grotto is found in the Altus Plateau. It can be accessed by exploring the north side of the great bridge heading east into the capital.

name: Perfumer Tricia Ashes
description: Perfumer Tricia is a Spirit and Summon in Elden Ring. Perfumer Tricia is a support spirit with moves similar to the Boss variant.

name: Standard Damage
description: Standard Damage is one of the Damage Types in Elden Ring. It is one of the eight main Damage Types and belongs to the Physical Damage category. Damage Types are a major part of the calculation that determines how much damage is dealt in Combat and are affected by many factors including your equipment, skills and temporary buffs.

name: Physical Defense
description: Physical Defense is a Defensive Stat in Elden Ring. Physical Defense shows your defense power and damage negation against standard physical attacks. Stats determine the strengths and weaknesses of your character. Defensive Stats are determined by Attributes and Equipment.

name: Pierce Damage
description: Pierce Damage is one of the Damage Types in Elden Ring. It is one of the eight main Damage Types and belongs to the Physical Damage category. Damage Types are a major part of the calculation that determines how much damage is dealt in Combat and are affected by many factors including your equipment, skills and temporary buffs.

name: Poison
description: Poison is a Status Effect in Elden Ring. Status Effects are various buffs or ailments that apply either a beneficial or detrimental effect to the target. Status Effects can be applied on both enemies and players alike. Status Effects are triggered after a buildup meter is filled by repeated application of attacks that cause the effect. Both players and enemies can have varying resistances to a given Status Effect.

name: Promised Consort Radahn
description: Promised Consort Radahn is a God Boss in Shadow of the Erdtree. He is an imposing, fully armored humanoid enemy adorned in red and gold with a lion-shaped helmet, wielding two colossal swords, and is found in Enir-Ilim. The second phase of this boss is called Radahn, Consort of Miquella. This is not an optional boss as players need to defeat him to conclude Shadow of the Erdtree.

name: Putrescent Knight
description: Putrescent Knight is a Legend Boss in Shadow of the Erdtree. The Putrescent Knight is a large decrepit skeleton wielding a cleaver and riding a steed. It is found guarding the entrance to St. Trina's cave at the end of Stone Coffin Fissure. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat it to advance in Shadow of the Erdtree.

name: Putrid Avatar
description: Putrid Avatar is a Field Boss in Elden Ring. They are still guardians of the Minor Erdtrees, despite rotting from within. A few can also be found guarding Elphael from intruders.

name: Putrid Corpse Ashes
description: Putrid Corpse Ashes is a Spirit and Summon in Elden Ring. Putrid Corpse Ashes are slow and erratic undead beings able to induce some level of poison to Enemies when approached.

name: Putrid Crystalians
description: Putrid Crystalians is a Boss in Elden Ring. Putrid Crystalians are crystalline humanoids inflicted with Scarlet Rot. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat it to advance in Elden Ring.

name: Radahn's Great Rune
description: Radahn's Great Rune is a Great Rune in Elden Ring. Radahn's Great Rune Raises maximum HP, FP and Stamina. Great Runes in Elden Ring are special items dropped by Demigod Bosses that can be equipped to acquire special passive bonuses.

name: Rakshasa
description: Rakshasa is a Boss in Elden Ring. Rakshasa is a humanoid enemy equipped with a great katana and is found in Eastern Nameless Mausoleum. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat it to advance in Elden Ring.

description: Rakshasa's Great Katana is a Great Katana in Elden Ring. It is found in the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Rakshasa's Great Katana scales primarily with Strength and Dexterity and is a good Weapon for STR/DEX builds. This weapon has blood-loss buildup and reduces your chances of getting staggered during attacks.

name: Ralva the Great Red Bear
description: Ralva the Great Red Bear is a Field Boss in Elden Ring. Ralva the Great Red Bear is a ferocious boss that fights with the strength of its limbs and is found in Scadu Altus. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat it to advance in Shadow of the Erdtree.

name: Rauh Base
description: Rauh Base is a Location in Elden Ring, added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Rauh Base region is located beneath the Ancient Ruins of Rauh, in the valley. You can reach this location by traveling through the tunnel between Scadu Altus (From Moorth Ruins, head all the way north through the swamp) and head west. [Map Link]

name: Raya Lucaria Academy
description: The Academy of Raya Lucaria is a Legacy Dungeon in Elden Ring. Quite a different area as it has a variety of blue hues, compared to the green open spaces of Limgrave, covered in crystals not only in its environment but also the creatures that inhabit it. These range from snails to more vicious animals to the underwater crustaceans such as crabs and are heavily guarded by the academy's scholars.

name: Red Bear
description: Red Bear is a Great Enemy Boss in Elden Ring. Red Bear is a humanoid boss who glows white and almost looks like wears a fur coat from a bear and is found in the Northern Nameless Mausoleum. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat it to advance in Shadow of the Erdtree.

description: Red Bear's Claw is a Beast Claw in Elden Ring. It was added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Red Bear's Claw scales primarily with Strength and Dexterity and is a good Weapon that deals damage fast and inflicts Hemorrhage.

name: Redmane Knight Ogha Ashes
description: Redmane Knight Ogha is a summonable Spirit in Elden Ring. Redmane Knight Ogha Ashes are used to summon the spirit of Ogha, the Redmane Knight.

name: Rellana Twin Moon Knight
description: Rellana, Twin Moon Knight is a Legend Boss in Elden Ring. A former princess of the Carian Royal Family, she is the younger sister of Rennala, Queen of the Full Moon. Wielding her signature Twin Blades that she can infuse with Glintstone magic and Messmer's Flame respectively, she is fought at the end of Castle Ensis. This is an optional boss as players do not need to defeat her to advance in Shadow of the Erdtree.

name: Rennala Queen of the Full Moon
description: Rennala, Queen of the Full Moon is a Legend Boss in Elden Ring. Though not a demigod, Rennala is one of the shardbearers who resides in the Academy of Raya Lucaria. Rennala is a powerful sorceress, head of the Carian Royal Family, and erstwhile leader of the Academy. Rennala is an optional boss, and doesn't need to be defeated in order to advance in Elden Ring. However, she is a shardbearer, and two of the five available shardbearers must be defeated before entering Leyndell, Royal Capital. In addition, she must be defeated to achieve a certain ending.

name: Rivermouth Cave
description: Rivermouth Cave is a Location in Elden Ring, added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Rivermouth Cave is found in Gravesite Plain region. To get to Rivermouth Cave, travel to the Temple Town Ruins site of grace and head South. Scale the edge of the cliff until you find gravestones on the edge and traverse down. Then, follow the wall going west until you get to the entrance of Rivermouth Cave.

name: Roar Medallion
description: Roar Medallion is a Talisman in Elden Ring. Roar Medallion increases the damage of roars and breath attacks by 15%. Players can use talismans in Elden Ring to boost a variety of Stats.

name: Roar of Rugalea
description: Roar of Rugalea is an Incantation in Elden Ring. It was added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. Roar of Rugalea spell emits a powerful roar that deals damage.

name: Romina Saint of the Bud
description: Romina, Saint of the Bud is a Legend Boss in Elden Ring. She appears humanoid, though her lower half has inexplicably transformed into a centipede with a scorpion's stinger. After her church was burned during Messmer's crusade, she discovered a twisted divine element and weaved it into the Scarlet Rot, wielding the bud she cradled as a deadly poleblade in combat. She can be found in the Church of the Bud, which you can access at the end of your exploration in the Ancient Ruins of Rauh. This is not an optional boss, as players need to defeat her to advance in Shadow of the Erdtree.

name: Roundtable Knight Vyke
description: Roundtable Knight Vyke, also known as Vyke, Knight of the Roundtable is a Boss in Elden Ring. Vyke is a Tarnished champion from the past and this version is likely him in his prime, with no trace of frenzied flame. In combat, he uses his unique Greatspear alongside various Dragon Cult Incantations. This is an optional boss as players don't have to defeat it to advance in Elden Ring, but will be rewarded with useful items and Runes for doing so.

name: Rugalea the Great Red Bear
description: Rugalea the Great Red Bear is a Boss in Elden Ring. Rugalea the Great Red Bear is a large red bear found in Rauh Base. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat it to advance in Shadow of the Erdtree.

name: Runes
description: Runes in Elden Ring, analogous to the Souls of previous FromSoftware titles, act as the player's EXP and currency for Merchants. You will drop any runes in your possession at the site of your death. If you die again before reclaiming those runes, they will be lost forever. The compass at the top of the screen indicates the direction of the lost runes.

name: Rykard's Great Rune
description: Rykard's Great Rune is a Great Rune in Elden Ring. Rykard's Great Rune restores HP upon defeating enemies. Great Runes in Elden Ring are special items dropped by Demigod Bosses that can be equipped to acquire special passive bonuses.

name: Sainted Hero's Grave
description: Sainted Hero's Grave is a Location in Elden Ring. The Sainted Hero's Grave is found in Altus Plateau, west of Rampartside Path. It is recommended that you bring 2 Stonesword Keys to this location in order to obtain all the items available.

name: Sanguine Noble
description: Sanguine Noble is a Boss in Elden Ring. It is hidden beneath Writheblood Ruins and wields a sword designed to draw blood. This is an optional boss as players don't have to defeat it to advance in Elden Ring.
metadata: {"Location": "Writheblood Ruins", "Drops": "8,800", "HP": "3,128", "Strong VS Fire": "Weak to Slash Hemorrhage"}

name: Scadu Altus
description: Scadu Altus is a Location in Elden Ring, added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Scadu Altus region is to the northeast of Gravesite Plain. [See Shadow of the Erdtree Map]

name: Scadutree Avatar
description: Scadutree Avatar is a Legend Boss in Elden Ring. Scadutree Avatar is the Realm of Shadow's equivalent of the Erdtree Avatar, but in design it resembles an enlarged Shadow Sunflower with two massive roots for arms and can summon thorns and conjure the Scadutree's light for offense. It is found in the Scadutree Base, accessible through a hidden path in the Shadow Keep. This is an optional boss as players don't need to defeat it in order to advance in Shadow of the Erdtree.

name: Scadutree Fragment
description: Scadutree Fragment is an Upgrade Material in Elden Ring, debuting in the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. Scadutree Fragments are optional consumables that can be used to simultaneously enhance offensive and defensive capabilities at any Sites of Grace, acting like a permanent boost to your damage dealt and damage negation in the Land of Shadow.

name: Scaduview
description: Scaduview is a Region/Location in Elden Ring, added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Scadu Altus region is to the north of Scadu Altus. You can reach this location by climb down Moorth Ruins, travel through Bonny Village eastward. Then go all the way north until you reach the Church District of Shadow Keep. Climb the laddar at Storehouse, Back Section site of grace. Take the wooden stairs and then hop out the window to the right and go up the wooden walkways alongside the outside of the walls to reach the "Storehouse, Loft" grace. Then, use the small elevator just to the north, go over the wooden beam to the west, climb up the ladder, head east across the beam, jump down to the beam below and then off to the floor, hop down onto a small elevator, and then enter it and go up, work your way toward the ladder down, take that and then hop onto the floor to the north. Go outside and take the small elevator down, and then another elevator to reach the "Shadow Keep, Back Gate" grace.

name: Scarlet Rot
description: Scarlet Rot is a Status Effect in Elden Ring. Status Effects are various buffs or ailments that apply either a beneficial or detrimental effect to the target. Status Effects can be applied on both enemies and players alike. Status Effects are triggered after a buildup meter is filled by repeated application of attacks that cause the effect. Both players and enemies can have varying resistances to a given Status Effect.

name: Scorpion River Catacombs
description: Scorpion River Catacombs is a Location in Elden Ring, added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Scorpion River Catacombs are found in the Rauh Ruins region.

name: Serpent's Amnion
description: Serpent's Amnion is a Key Item in Elden Ring. Serpent's Amnion from a womb that bore unintended offspring. Key Items in Elden Ring include a wide variety of items found in specific locations or are given by a related NPCs which are used to unlock areas, quests, and to further progress the game's story.

name: Shadow Keep
description: Shadow Keep is a Legacy Dungeon in Elden Ring. The Shadow Keep is a legacy dungeon exclusive to the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC, it accommodates the main army of Messmer the Impaler. The Shadow Keep is located at the center or the heart of the Scadu Altus region and has multiple entrances and exits, considering it to be a non-linear dungeon where adventurers will encounter many enemies such as Messmer Soldiers, Fire Knights, Giant Crabs, Giant Bats, Shadow Militia, Black Knights, and devastating creatures. [See Shadow of the Erdtree Map]

name: Shadow of the Erdtree
description: Shadow of the Erdtree is a fully fledged expansion for Elden Ring that adds a whole new map with 70 new Weapons, 10 new Shields, 39 new Talismans, 14 new Sorceries, 28 new Incantations, 20 new Spirit Ashes, 25 new Ashes of War, 30 new Armor Sets and new Consumables & Craftables. The expansion was announced via Twitter by the official Elden Ring account on February 28th, 2023. A Gameplay Trailer released on February 21st 2024, and a Story Trailer followed on May 21st, 2024. The release date of the DLC was June 21st, 2024.

name: Shaman Village
description: Shaman Village is a Location in Elden Ring, added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. It is revealed to be the hometown of Queen Marika, The Eternal, the current ruler of the Lands Between. The village is found in the Scaduview region, a hidden area that is unlocked by using the "O Mother" gesture on a statue of Marika nearby the Shadow Keep, Back Gate Site of Grace.

name: Side Quests
description: Side Quests in Elden Ring are numerous optional progression options and questlines that can be triggered by an event or NPC. This page is an overview of all the Quests in Elden Ring. It will inform you about the quest giver, steps required to complete the quest, and any NPCs affected by the quest. There are currently 36 side quests you can do in Elden Ring.

name: Siofra Aqueduct
description: Siofra Aqueduct is a Location in Elden Ring. The Siofra Aqueduct is found in Nokron, Eternal City. In order to reach this location, start from the Mimic Tear site of grace in Nokron, Eternal City and follow the long stone bridge until you are able to get back onto land via a broken section on the left. From here, head north and towards the cliffs to the left of the northern Hallowhorn Grounds. If you see 4 Spirit Jellyfish by the cliffs, you're in the right place. Drop down the cliff edge and follow the slope towards a tunnel in the north. This tunnel leads to the Aqueduct proper.

name: Siofra River
description: Siofra River is a Location in Elden Ring. This underground region can be reached by taking the lift at either the Siofra River Well in Limgrave or Deep Siofra Well in Caelid.

name: Sir Gideon Ofnir, the All-Knowing (Boss)
description: Sir Gideon Ofnir, The All-Knowing is a Boss in Elden Ring. This Elden Ring Sir Gideon Ofnir, The All-Knowing Guide features boss locations, tips, strategies and videos on how to defeat Sir Gideon Ofnir easily, as well as boss stats and lore for Sir Gideon Ofnir.

name: Slash Damage
description: Slash Damage is one of the Damage Types in Elden Ring. It is one of the eight main Damage Types and belongs to the Physical Damage category. Damage Types are a major part of the calculation that determines how much damage is dealt in Combat and are affected by many factors including your equipment, skills and temporary buffs.

name: Sleep
description: Sleep is a Status Effect in Elden Ring. Status Effects are various buffs or ailments that apply either a beneficial or detrimental effect to the target. Status Effects can be applied on both enemies and players alike. Status Effects are triggered after a buildup meter is filled by repeated application of attacks that cause the effect. Both players and enemies can have varying resistances to a given Status Effect.

name: Smithing Stone (6)
description: Smithing Stone [6] is an Upgrade Material in Elden Ring. Smithing Stone [6] is one of the rare smithing stones that are mainly used to acquire high equipment level with great stats. Upgrade Materials can be acquired through exploration, looting it from specified areas of a Location, dropped by a specific Enemy or Boss, given by an NPC, or sold by a Merchant.

name: Smithing Stone (7)
description: Smithing Stone [7] is an Upgrade Material in Elden Ring. Smithing Stone [7] is one of the uncommon and rarest form of smithing stones that are used to forge greater levels of equipment. Upgrade Materials can be acquired through exploration, looting it from specified areas of a Location, dropped by a specific Enemy or Boss, given by an NPC, or sold by a Merchant.

name: Smithing-Stone Miner's Bell Bearing (4)
description: Smithing-Stone Miner's Bell Bearing [4] is a Key Item in Elden Ring. Smithing-Stone Miner's Bell Bearing [4] can be offered to the Two Maiden Husks for new item access. Key Items in Elden Ring include a wide variety of items found in specific locations or are given by a related NPCs which are used to unlock areas, quests, and to further progress the game's story.

name: Soldjars of Fortune Ashes
description: Soldjars of Fortune Ashes is a Spirit and Summon in Elden Ring. Soldjars of Fortune Ashes are used to summon the spirits of three little living jars.

name: Solitude Set
description: Solitude Set is an Armor Set in Elden Ring. It is a brand new Armor Set in the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. Sets of Armor in Elden Ring are composed of four armor pieces which are Helms, Chest Armor, Gauntlets, and Leg Armor. Great damage negation and resistance make this set suitable for tank builds.

name: Somber Smithing Stone (5)
description: Somber Smithing Stone [5] is an Upgrade Material in Elden Ring. Somber Smithing Stone [5] is a rare special smithing stone that is only used to upgrade and strengthen special equipment. Upgrade Materials can be acquired through exploration, looting it from specified areas of a Location, dropped by a specific Enemy or Boss, given by an NPC, or sold by a Merchant.

name: Somber Smithing Stone (6)
description: Somber Smithing Stone [6] is an Upgrade Material in Elden Ring. Somber Smithing Stone [6] allows the user to further increase the stats and acquire a high level for special equipment. Upgrade Materials can be acquired through exploration, looting it from specified areas of a Location, dropped by a specific Enemy or Boss, given by an NPC, or sold by a Merchant.

name: Somber Smithing Stone (1)
description: Somber Smithing Stone [1] is an Upgrade Material in Elden Ring. Somber Smithing Stone [1] is a variation of the regular colored Smithing Stone, a base material for upgrading special equipment used at the lowest level. Upgrade Materials can be acquired through exploration, looting it from specified areas of a Location, dropped by a specific Enemy or Boss, given by an NPC, or sold by a Merchant.

name: Somberstone Miner's Bell Bearing (1)
description: Somberstone Miner's Bell Bearing [1] is a Key Item in Elden Ring. Somberstone Miner's Bell Bearing [1] Offer to Twin Maiden Husks for new item access. Key Items in Elden Ring include a wide variety of items found in specific locations or are given by a related NPCs which are used to unlock areas, quests, and to further progress the game's story.

name: Southern Nameless Mausoleum
description: Southern Nameless Mausoleum is a Location in Elden Ring, added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Southern Nameless Mausoleum is found in the Southern Shore region, on an island that can only be accessed through an underground cave. The entrance to the cave is on the mainland shore just south-east from the Cerulean Coast West site of grace on a ledge behind and below the large dead tree.

name: Spiritcaller Cave
description: Spiritcaller Cave is a Location in Elden Ring. The Spiritcaller Cave is found in the Mountaintops of the Giants in the east, along the western bank of the Freezing Lake. Players can reach this location by traversing the edges of the lake. The cave's entrance is sealed by an Imp Statue, requiring 2 Stonesword Keys to unlock.

name: Star-Lined Sword
description: Star-Lined Sword is a Katana in Elden Ring. It is found in the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Star-Lined Sword scales primarily with Strength, Dexterity, and Intelligence and is a good Weapon for dex oriented builds. This is a weapon that causes blood loss and has a skill called Onze's Line of Stars, which lets you slash multiple times with each slash getting stronger.

name: Stats
description: Statistics in Elden Ring refer to various properties that govern your character's strengths and weaknesses, as well as how they are affected by interactions in and out of combat. There are 8 main Stats in Elden Ring, as well as several dozen secondary stats which all contribute to your character's growth and effectiveness in various situations. Stats are affected by a number of things and can be modified by your Level, Equipment, and any active buffs and effects.

name: Status Effects
description: Status Effects in Elden Ring covers information regarding the different status effects that are obtained by both players and NPCs. Status Effects can be equally devastating to the player, Bosses, and other Enemies of the Lands Between. This page contains a full list of all the Status Effects in the game.

name: Stone Coffin Fissure
description: Stone Coffin Fissure is a Location in Elden Ring, added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. Stone Coffin Fissure is found on a peninsula on the southwestern tip of the Cerulean Coast region. To reach the entrance to the fissure, travel southwest from the Cerulean Coast Cross and descend the large hole at the end of the peninsula.

name: Stonedigger Troll
description: Stonedigger Troll is a Boss in Elden Ring. This Elden Ring Stonedigger Troll Guide features boss locations, tips, strategies and videos on how to defeat Stonedigger Trolls easily, as well as boss stats and lore for the Stonedigger Trolls.
metadata: {"Strong VS Standard Slash Pierce Poison": "Weak to Strike Magic Holy Sleep"}

name: Stormveil Castle
description: Stormveil Castle is a Legacy Dungeon in Elden Ring. A castle that lies on the cliffs of Stormhill, a stronghold of Godrick the Grafted. Be wary of this location since there are hordes of soldiers and hostile creatures that will stop anything and anyone who tries to infiltrate the area. Players entering Stormveil Castle should beware that it's a challenging dungeon with groups of numerous enemies with traps and ballistas as well as mini-bosses. This area does not allow riding.

name: Strike Damage
description: Strike Damage is one of the Damage Types in Elden Ring. It is one of the eight main Damage Types and belongs to the Physical Damage category. Damage Types are a major part of the calculation that determines how much damage is dealt in Combat and are affected by many factors including your equipment, skills, attacks and temporary buffs.

name: Subterranean Shunning-Grounds
description: Subterranean Shunning-Grounds is a Location in Elden Ring. The Subterranean Shunning-Grounds is found in Leyndell, Royal Capital (or later, Leyndell, Ashen Capital). It is accessible by descending the stairs at the Avenue Balcony Site of Grace and immediately turning left out of the double grate doors. First walk to the railing, and then move northwest until the rooftops are directly to your left. Hop over the railing onto the rooftops, then descend into the plaza. From the plaza's center, face due North. The well's wooden structure will be visible between a dilapidated ruin and the walkway.

name: Suppressing Pillar
description: Suppressing Pillar is a Location in Elden Ring, added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Suppressing Pillar is found in the east part of the Gravesite Plain region.

name: Swamp of Aeonia
description: Swamp of Aeonia is a Location in Elden Ring. The Swamp of Aeonia is a sub-region of Caelid, found right in the center. This location is easily accessible on horseback as there are entry points all around the swamp.

name: The Lands Between
description: e

name: Trophy & Achievement Guide
description: Trophy & Achievement Guide for Elden Ring is an overview of the various trophies and achievements you can unlock throughout the game.

name: Twinbird Kite Shield
description: Twinbird Kite Shield is a Medium Shield in Elden Ring. The Twinbird Kite Shield is a Shield that scales primarily with Strength. Medium Shields feature a good balance between defense and weight, which is great for most situations in combat. Although it may not be as light as a Small Shield which is good for agility and parrying, the Standard Shield works best at reducing damage and blocking.

name: Uhl Palace Ruins
description: Uhl Palace Ruins is a Location in Elden Ring. The Uhl Palace Ruins is found underground in Ainsel River. The ruins are separated into two parts and each are reached from different entrances of Ainsel River. You can reach the southern section by heading south-west from the Ainsel River Well Depths Site of Grace when first arriving at Ainsel River from the Ainsel River Well. The northern section of the Uhl Palace Ruins can be found in Ainsel River Main by heading south from the Ainsel River Main Site of Grace after entering from Renna's Rise.

name: Volcano Manor
description: Volcano Manor is a Legacy Dungeon in Elden Ring. Volcano Manor is unique in that much of its progression, if you so choose, can be done outside of the manor itself. You will be tasked with assassinating Tarnished from other worlds, rebelling against the Fingers and the Erdtree itself. There is another way to beat the dungeon, however, if this band of dissenters and their tasks do not appeal to you. You'll find guides for both the assassination questline and the dungeon area here for a complete run of this Legacy Dungeon.

name: The War-Dead Catacombs
description: War-Dead Catacombs is a Location in Elden Ring. The War-Dead Catacombs are found in Wailing Dunes in East Caelid. The War-Dead Catacombs can be found to the far northern corner of the area, after having defeated Starscourge Radahn. From the site of grace after defeating Radahn, travel north until you reach the upper most corner of the area, and you'll find a small door along the cliffside.

name: Waygates
description: Waygates in Elden Ring are transporter portals or gateways that teleport players to a set location when interacted with. They are also referred to as Sending Gates or Gateways. Each Waygate will teleport the player to one set location. Before it is used, players will be prompted with the option to travel to another location. They are located throughout different regions and their destinations vary.

name: Weapons
description: Weapons in Elden Ring are pieces of offensive equipment that are used by the player's character to inflict damage against Enemies and Bosses. Elden Ring features 308 Weapons from new categories as well as some returning ones from previous Souls games. Press and hold the interact button (triangle/Y) and the attack button (R1/RB) to two-hand your equipped weapon.

name: Weeping Peninsula
description: Weeping Peninsula is a Location in Elden Ring. The Weeping Peninsula region is a region players can reach by heading south east from Limgrave. The Weeping Peninsula is a land with many changes in height, featuring a Minor Erdtree in its center and is constantly raining.

name: Western Nameless Mausoleum
description: Western Nameless Mausoleum is a Location in Elden Ring. The Western Nameless Mausoleum is located west of the Gravesite Plain region.. The Western Nameless Mausoleum is a location exclusive to the Shadow of the Erdtree expansion.

name: Ymir's Bell Bearing
description: Ymir's Bell Bearing is a Key Item in Elden Ring. Ymir's Bell Bearing can be offered to the Twin Maiden Husks to gain access to new shop items. Key Items in Elden Ring include a wide variety of items found in specific locations or are given by a related NPCs which are used to unlock areas, quests, and to further progress the game's story.

name: Gestures
description: Gestures in Elden Ring are a useful tool to express yourself to other players, some including a vocal performance or making sound. Up to six can be bound to a shortcut menu just below the pouch.

name: Abandoned Merchant Siofra River
description: Abandoned Merchant Siofra River is an NPC and one of several Nomadic Merchants in Elden Ring. Abandoned Merchants sell various items and equipment including Consumables, Materials, Weapons and Armor as well as notes containing hints on how to acquire certain items. This Abandoned Merchant can be found inside one of the ruins in Central Siofra River.

name: Aeonian Spirit
description: The Aeonian Spirit is an NPC in Elden Ring. He stands upon the northern cliffs of the Swamp of Aeonia.

name: Aeonian Swamp Spirit
description: The Aeonian Swamp Spirit is an NPC in Elden Ring. He rests on the shore of the swamp and looks out towards the Heart of Aeonia.

name: Albinauric Village Spirit
description: The Albinauric Village Spirit is an NPC in Elden Ring. Located in the Village of the Albinaurics, he wishes for Albus' safety and gives you a hint on how to find him.

name: Ashen Spirit
description: Ashen Spirit is an NPC in Elden Ring. Ashen Spirit can be found sitting on the ground in the ash.

name: Aureliette
description: Aureliette is an NPC in Elden Ring. Aureliette is a jellyfish spirit found in Stargazers' Ruins.

name: Carian Manor Spirit
description: The Carian Manor Spirit is an NPC in Elden Ring. He can be found sitting on a chair, inside the

name: Church Of Pilgrimage Spirit
description: The Church of Pilgrimage Spirit is an NPC in Elden Ring. They can be found outside of the Church of Pilgrimage in the Weeping Peninsula.

name: Count Ymir, High Priest
description: Count Ymir, High Priest is an NPC in Elden Ring. Count Ymir, High Priest is a High Priest who oversees the Cathedral of Manus Metyr. He sells a collection of spells that can be purchased with runes. He has a servant named Jolan, who can be summoned during certain fights after progressing his questline. He speaks on many topics including the nature of the world and the Greater Will. Count Ymir, High Priest is an NPC exclusive to the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC and does not appear in the base game.

name: D's Twin Brother
description: D, Beholder of Death (real name: Devin) is an NPC in Elden Ring. He can be found in Nokron, Eternal City, east of the Great Waterfall Basin grace. To interact with D, Beholder of Death, you need the Twinned Armor. If given the armor, he will be available as a summon against the Valiant Gargoyle pair. He is the twin brother of Darian, also known as D, Hunter of the Dead.

name: Deathtouched Spirit
description: The Deathtouched Spirit is an NPC in Elden Ring. He can be found sitting defeated out the front of the Deathtouched Catacombs in Northern Limgrave.

name: Diallos
description: Knight Diallos is an NPC in Elden Ring. Diallos is a noble found at the Roundtable Hold, first mentioning that he's looking for his loyal servant, but is later involved in a quest of his own.
metadata: {"Locations": "Roundtable Hold Liurnia of the LakesVolcano ManorJarburg", "Role": "Quest NPC", "Voiced by": "Peter Caulfield", "wiki_url": "https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/Diallos"}

name: Dragon Communion Priestess
description: Dragon Communion Priestess is an NPC in Elden Ring. She is a surviving Ancient Dragon and worshipper of Dragonlord Placidusax. She informs players about the infamous dragon Bayle and her lord Placidusax. Dragon Communion Priestess is exclusive to the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC and does not appear in the base game. Players learn from either her spell or spirit ash that her name is Florissax.

name: Dryleaf Dane
description: Dryleaf Dane is an NPC in Elden Ring. He is an NPC exclusive to the Shadow of the Erdtree expansion. Dryleaf Dane is a master of hand-to-hand combat and is a fervent follower of Miquella. He leaves a Monk's Missive for travelers to find and wish to seek a challenge and learn the way of the warrior.

name: Eclipse Spirit
description: The Eclipse Spirit is an NPC in Elden Ring. He can be seen praying inside the Church of Eclipse.

name: Ensha
description: Ensha of the Royal Remains or Ensha is an NPC in Elden Ring. He will refuse to speak to the player, but instead stare at them. He is the servant of Gideon Ofnir.

name: Erdtree Sanctuary Spirit
description: Erdtree Sanctuary Spirit is an NPC in Elden Ring. He is sitting in a chair facing the bridge that connects the Queen's Bedchamber to the Elden Throne.

name: Finger Maiden Therolina
description: Finger Maiden Therolina is an NPC in Elden Ring. Finger Maiden Therolina is a sorcerer controlled by Seluvis and one of participants in Radahns' Festival

name: Fire Knight Queelign (NPC)
description: Fire Knight Queelign is an NPC in Elden Ring. Fire Knight Queelign is an NPC exclusive to the Shadow of the Erdtree expansion, he is a knight who pledges his loyalty to Marika. Fire Knight Queelign is first encountered as an NPC Invader in Belurat Tower Settlement and at the Church of Crusade.
metadata: {"Location": "NPC Invader:Belurat Tower SettlementChurch of CrusadePhysical Body:Church District, Shadow Keep", "Role": "NPC Invader, NPC", "Voiced by": "George Blagden", "wiki_url": "https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/Fire+Knight+Queelign+(NPC)"}

name: Frenzied Spirit
description: The Frenzied Spirit is an NPC in Elden Ring. He can be seen near the Church of Inhibition of in Northern Liurnia.

name: Gate Town Bridge Spirit
description: The Gate Town Bridge Spirit is an NPC in Elden Ring. He is upset over the Raya Lucaria Academy closing their gates to him.

name: Godwyn the Golden
description: Godwyn the Golden is a background character in Elden Ring. He was a demigod and the son of Queen Marika the Eternal and Godfrey the First Elden Lord, making him a member of the royal Golden Lineage. In the Night of the Black Knives, he was assassinated by Black Knife Assassins with the use of daggers imbued with the Rune of Death, stolen from Maliketh, the Black Blade. His death would precipitate the Shattering, a war between the demigods which would be responsible for much of the current state of the Lands Between.

name: Grape Spirit
description: The Grape Spirit is an NPC in Elden Ring. Located in Stormveil Castle. He is looking for a maiden to give his grapes to and seems to have lost one, since a Shabiri Grape can be found beside him.

name: Gurranq Beast Clergyman
description: Gurranq, Beast Clergyman is an NPC in Elden Ring. Gurranq appears to be a large, hunched creature that lies isolated in the Bestial Sanctum. Constantly hungering for Deathroot, he will reward those who offer it to him.
