name: Hermit Merchant
description: Hermit Merchant Capital Outskirts is an NPC in Elden Ring. Hermit Merchants sell various items and equipment including Consumables, Materials, Weapons and Armor as well as notes containing hints on how to acquire certain items. This merchant lives a life of seclusion within Hermit Merchant's Shack outside Leyndell.

name: Hornsent
description: Hornsent is an NPC in Elden Ring. Hornsent can be found alongside Freyja at the Three-Path Cross in Gravesite Plain. He is exclusive to the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC, and can't be found in the base game. The Hornsent are a race of inhabitants from the Realm of Shadow who were purged by Messmer the Impaler, and this individual swears vengeance upon him.
metadata: {"Location": "Three-Path Cross, Gravesite Plain", "Role": "Amicable NPC, Invader NPC", "Voiced by": "Jonathan Forbes", "wiki_url": "https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/Hornsent"}

name: Hornsent Grandam
description: Hornsent Grandam is an NPC in Elden Ring. Hornsent Grandam is a member of the antique race that inhabited Belurat, Tower Settlement. Her people were set to the torch by Messmer the Impaler and his forces. Hornsent Grandam is an NPC exclusive to the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC, and is not present in the base game.
metadata: {"Location": "Storeroom, Belurat, Tower Settlement", "Role": "Hornsent Survivor", "Voiced by": "Sorcha Cusack", "wiki_url": "https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/Hornsent+Grandam"}

name: Igon
description: Drake Warrior Igon is an NPC in Elden Ring. Igon can be heard screaming in pain from his injuries, and swearing revenge against the dread dragon he calls Bayle. Igon is an NPC exclusive to the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC and does not appear in the base game.

name: Isolated Merchant Raya Lucaria
description: Isolated Merchant Raya Lucaria is an NPC and one of several Isolated Merchants in Elden Ring. Isolated Merchants sell various items and equipment including Consumables, Materials, Weapons and Armor as well as notes containing useful tips for the player. This Isolated Merchant can be found near the end of the South East bridge leading from the Main Academy Gate grace.
metadata: {"Location": "Raya Lucaria Academy, Liurnia of the Lakes", "Role": "General Goods Shop", "Voiced by": "Mathew Marsh"}

name: Isolated Merchants
description: Isolated Merchants in Elden Ring refer to several NPC Merchants that can be found in multiple locations. Isolated Merchants sell various items and equipment including Consumables, Materials, Weapons and Armor as well as notes containing hints for the player. Each Isolated Merchant has a different stock and they are usually found in or around an Isolated Merchant's Shack, complete with their own Sites of Grace. This page contains a list of all known Isolated Merchants in the game.

name: Jar Bairn
description: Jar Bairn is an NPC in Elden Ring. Jar Bairn is a small living jar NPC that can be found sitting on top of some stairs at the west end of Jarburg. They're quite friendly to visitors and their quest is closely tied to Iron Fist Alexander and Diallos.
metadata: {"Location": "Jarburg, Liurnia of the Lakes", "Role": "Quest NPC", "Voiced by": "Grace Saif", "wiki_url": "https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/Jar+Bairn"}

name: Jolan
description: Swordhand of Night Joln is an NPC in Elden Ring. Jolan is the loyal warrior in service to Ymir and can be found in the Cathedral of Manus Metyr. In the same room where you speak with Count Ymir, she can be seen on the pillar to your right.
metadata: {"Location": "Cathedral of Manus Metyr", "Role": "Servant of Count Ymir", "Voiced by": "Eleanor Matsuura", "wiki_url": "https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/Jolan"}

name: Kingsrealm Spirit
description: Kingsrealm Spirit is an NPC in Elden Ring. Kingrealm Spirit rests at the Kingsrealm Ruins in Northern Liurnia.

name: Laiedd Spirit
description: The Laiedd Spirit is an NPC in Elden Ring. He is hiding in Fort Laiedd.

name: Lionel the Lionhearted
description: Lionel the Lionhearted is an NPC in Elden Ring. Lionel the Lionhearted acts as the Father of Fia and can be encountered as an NPC Invader as one of Fia's Champions. He is also available as an NPC Summon and can be seen wielding a Great Epee, as well as the Prince of Deaths Staff, casting Rancorcall and Fias Mist.

name: Liurnian Highway Spirit
description: The Liurnian Highway Spirit is an NPC in Elden Ring. He can be found on the Liurnia Highway in a defeated position, talking about puppet soliders.

name: Liurnian Lake Spirit
description: The Liurnian Lake Spirit is an NPC in Elden Ring. He can be found knelt down in the shallow water, just east of the Revenger's Shack.
metadata: {"Location": "Near Revengers Shack, Liurnia of the Lakes", "Role": "Benevolent", "wiki_url": "https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/Liurnian+Lake+Spirit"}

name: Lost Snow Spirit
description: The Lost Snow Spirit is an NPC in Elden Ring. He is lost and looking for the Haligtree.

name: Master Lusat
description: Master Lusat (aka Primeval Sorcerer Lusat) is an NPC in Elden Ring. Master Lusat can be found at Sellia Hideaway.

name: Medallion Spirit
description: Medallion Spirit is an NPC in Elden Ring.

name: Merchant Kale
description: Merchant Kal is a Merchant and NPC in Elden Ring. Merchant Kal can be found in Limgrave: Church of Elleh, soon after emerging from the Stranded Graveyard at the start of the game, youll see a building to the North which is the Church of Elleh.
metadata: {"Location": "Limgrave: Church of Elleh", "Role": "General Goods Shop", "Voiced By": "Nabil Elouahabi", "wiki_url": "https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/Merchant+Kal"}

name: Millicent's Sisters
description: Millicent's Sisters is a NPC collective in Elden Ring. They are group of female warriors associated with Sage Gowry and are encountered following Millicent's questline. Polyanna can be summoned much earlier against Commander O'Neil if Gowry is spoken to.
metadata: {"Location": "Elphael, Brace of the Haligtree", "Role": "End of Millicent questline", "Voiced by": "N/A"}

name: Miquella
description: Miquella, also known as Miquella the Kind or Kindly Miquella, is a background character in Elden Ring and a central character in Shadow of the Erdtree. One of the Empyrean children born from the union of Queen Marika and Radagon, he is the twin brother of Malenia, together known as the Twin Prodigies. It is revealed that Miquella has stripped himself of his flesh and Empyrean lineage in the Land of Shadow, a place obscured by the Erdtree and purged in an unsung war.

name: Miriel Pastor of Vows
description: Miriel, Pastor of Vows is an NPC in Elden Ring. Miriel, Pastor of Vows is the Liurna Church of Vow's steward, a huge silver tortoise wearing a mitre. He first interacts with you when arriving at the Church of Vows. Miriel, Pastor of Vows welcomes you and offers to share their knowledge of Sorceries and Incantations, as well as lore on certain characters.

name: Moore
description: Moore is an NPC in Elden Ring. Moore is one of the followers of Miquella and is a gentle giant that also acts as a Merchant. Moore is an NPC exclusive to the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC and does not appear in the base game.

name: Morne Spirit
description: The Morne Spirit is an NPC in Elden Ring. He can be found locked inside a cage behind the castle.

name: Mushroom Spirit
description: Mushroom Spirit is an NPC in Elden Ring. Mushroom Spirit can be found seated on a chair next to remains at the Stormfoot Catacombs' entrance.

name: Nanaya
description: Nanaya is a deceased NPC in Elden Ring. Nanaya has lore significance to the Abyssal Woods, and was an important person to Midra, Lord of Frenzied Flame before the hornsent's inquisition and his fall into madness. She perished long before the events of the game.

name: Needle Knight Leda
description: Needle Knight Leda is an NPC in Elden Ring. Needle Knight Leda is the ringleader of Miquella's band of followers in the Realm of Shadow. She is an NPC exclusive to Shadow of the Erdtree and does not appear in the base game. She was part of an order of knights under the service of Miquella known as the needle knights.

name: Nomadic Merchant West Altus Plateau
description: Nomadic Merchant Altus Plateau is an NPC and one of several Nomadic Merchants in Elden Ring. Nomadic Merchants sell various items and equipment including Consumables, Materials, Weapons and Armor as well as notes containing hints on how to acquire certain items. This Nomadic Merchant can be found in Altus Plateau, just next to the Forest-Spanning Greatbridge Site Of Grace.

name: Nomadic Merchants
description: Nomadic Merchants in Elden Ring refer to several NPC Merchants that can be found in multiple locations. Nomadic Merchants sell various items and equipment including Consumables, Materials, Weapons and Armor as well as notes containing hints on how to acquire certain items. Each Merchant has a different stock and they are usually found near Sites of Grace or other easily accessed landmarks. This page contains a list of all Merchants in the game.

name: Phillia, Towering Little Sister
description: Phillia, Towering Little Sister is an NPC in Elden Ring. Phillia, Towering Little Sister is a gigantic first-generation albinauric without an accompanying direwolf. She is related to Latenna's quest, and Latenna will call out her name if slain.

name: Redmane Freyja
description: Redmane Freyja is an NPC in Elden Ring. Redmane Freyja is a former follower of Radahn, but is now a fervent follower of Miquella. She is an NPC that can be found exclusively in the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC, and can't be encountered in the base game.
metadata: {"Location": "Three-Path Cross, Gravesite Plain", "Role": "Cooperator, Questline Related", "Voiced by": "Stefanie Martini", "wiki_url": "https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/Redmane+Freyja"}

name: Rennala, Queen of the Full Moon (NPC)
description: Rennala, Queen of the Full Moon is an NPC in Elden Ring. Rennala gives access to the Rebirth function, allowing the player to reallocate their stats by using a Larval Tear (also called respeccing). She can also be used to change the player's appearance.
metadata: {"Location": "Academy of Raya Lucaria", "Role": "Last Carian Queen", "Voiced by": "Mali Harries", "wiki_url": "https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/Rennala,+Queen+of+the+Full+Moon+(NPC)"}

name: Sanguine Noble (NPC)
description: Sanguine Noble is an NPC enemy invader located in the Consecrated Snowfield. By heading West of the Inner Consecrated Snowfield grace, and just North of the Yelough Anix Ruins towards the cliff edge.

name: Shaded Castle Spirit
description: The Shaded Castle Spirit is an NPC in Elden Ring. The Shaded Castle Spirit lays defeated within The Shaded Castle.

name: Siofra River Spirit
description: The Siofra River Spirit is an NPC in Elden Ring. He can be seen worshipping the Mohgwyn Dynasty Mausoleum.

name: Sir Ansbach
description: Sir Ansbach is an NPC in Elden Ring. Sir Ansbach is a former servant of Mohg, Lord of Blood and his dynasty, but is now part of the group that follows Miquella through the Realm of Shadow. Sir Ansbach is an NPC exclusive to Shadow of the Erdtree and does not appear in the base game.
metadata: {"Location": "Outside Belurat, Tower Settlement", "Role": "Pureblood Knight Captain (former), NPC Quest Related", "Voiced by": "Ben Miles", "wiki_url": "https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/Sir+Ansbach"}

name: St. Trina
description: St. Trina is an NPC in Elden Ring, exclusive to the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. She is found at the Garden of Deep Purple in the deepest part of Stone Coffin Fissure. St. Trina was first mentioned in the base game through various item descriptions, such as St. Trina's Torch. She has a deep association with the Sleep status effect, granting followers and foes a blissful slumber. The Stone Fissure Cross reveals that she was abandoned by her other half, Miquella, in his journey towards godhood.
metadata: {"Location": "Garden of Deep Purple, Stone Coffin Fissure", "Role": "NPC Quest Related", "Voiced by": "Jessica Rhodes", "wiki_url": "https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/St.+Trina"}

name: Stranded Graveyard Spirit
description: The Stranded Graveyard Spirit is a Spirit NPC in Elden Ring. He is located in the Stranded Graveyard and tells you where the training area for the game is.

name: Study Hall Spirit
description: The Study Hall Spirit is an NPC in Elden Ring. He can be found inside the Carian Study Hall behind a pew.

name: The Gloam-Eyed Queen
description: The Gloam-Eyed Queen is a mentioned-only character in Elden Ring. The Gloam-Eyed Queen was a mysterious figure who existed long ago and is only mentioned in different item and weapon descriptions. She created the god-slaying Black Flame Incantations and opposed Queen Marika's rule as an Empyrean chosen by the Fingers.

name: Thiollier
description: Thiollier is an NPC in Elden Ring. Thiollier has an eye for crafting poison and is not a fighter. Thiollier is an NPC that can be found exclusively in the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC, and can't be found in the base game.
metadata: {"Location": "Gravesite Plain, next to Pillar Path Cross", "Role": "Merchant, NPC Quest Related", "Voiced by": "Sam Glen", "wiki_url": "https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/Thiollier"}

name: Tower of Return Spirit
description: The Tower of Return Spirit is an NPC in Elden Ring. He rests on a rock with a forlonging stare towards the Tower of Return.
metadata: {"Location": "On a Western cliff in the Weeping Peninsula", "Role": "Benevolent", "wiki_url": "https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/Tower+of+Return+Spirit"}

name: Two Fingers
description: The Two Fingers are a manifestation of the Greater Will. The Two Fingers act as a destiny to the demigods, choosing the path which they must take. They are the main manifestation of the Greater Will in the game, besides Elden Beast. The Two Fingers have responsibilities include selecting Empyrean candidates to inherit the Elden Ring, furnishing these candidates with shadowbound beasts, and offering wisdom to the Tarnished through Finger Readers. You can find a total of seven Two Fingers throughout the game, the only one found alive is in the Roundtable Hold, interpreted by Enia. There are Two Fingers for almost every demi-god in the game, except Morgott and Mohg, who share Two Fingers. There is also no Two Finger for Messmer, Melina, or Miquella. Miquella and Malenia might share a Two Finger like Morgott and Mohg but it is currently unkown.

name: Volcano Manor Spirit
description: The Volcano Manor Spirit is an NPC in Elden Ring. He rests in the Volcano Manor.

name: Wandering Artist Spirit
description: The Wandering Artist Spirit is an NPC in Elden Ring. He is the artist that painted the landscape paintings that can be collected through the Lands Between.For a guide and more information on the Wandering Artist Spirit's quest, visit the Paintings page.
metadata: {"Location": "LimgraveLakes of LiurniaDragonbarrowAltus PlateauMountaintops of the Giants", "Role": "Quest NPC", "wiki_url": "https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/Wandering+Artist+Spirit"}

name: White Mask Varre
description: White Mask Varr is an NPC in Elden Ring. White Mask Varr is encountered near the start of the game, right by The First Step Site of Grace, and will offer advice to the player. He can be found multiple times in different locations as the story progresses.
metadata: {"Location": "Various Locations", "Role": "Guide and Quest NPC", "Voiced by": "Pip Torrens", "wiki_url": "https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/White+Mask+Varr"}

name: Windmill Spirit
description: The Windmill Spirit is an NPC in Elden Ring. He can be found hiding from the Celebrants behind a cart and a wooden box in the Windmill Village.,

name: Ashes of War
description: Ashes of War in Elden Ring are special items that allow you to grant your armaments (Weapons and Shields) new Skills and Affinities. They're integral for creating Builds and adapting to the many Enemies and Bosses of The Lands Between.

name: Cathedral of Manus Metyr
description: Cathedral of Manus Metyr is a Location in Elden Ring, added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Cathedral of Manus Metyr is found in Scadu Altus region.

name: Cathedral of the Forsaken
description: Cathedral of the Forsaken is a Location in Elden Ring. The Cathedral of the Forsaken is found within the Subterranean Shunning-Grounds.

name: Equipment & Magic
description: Elden Ring Equipment and Magic covers links to all pieces of a player's arsenal for use both in and out of combat, including armaments, magic, items, summons, and all of their respective upgrades.

name: Finger Reader Crone
description: Finger Reader Crones are NPCs in Elden Ring They are elderly women that hold staves with bells attached to the tips. They somehow have the gift of foresight, often telling vague hints about the future. Whenever they come across the Tarnished, they become overly excited and ask if they could read their fingers. Enia, found in the Roundtable Hold, is one of them.
metadata: {"Location": "In almost every region in the Lands Between", "Role": "NPCs", "Voiced by": "???", "wiki_url": "https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/Palm+Reader"}

name: Grand Altar of Dragon Communion
description: Grand Altar of Dragon Communion is a Location for Dragon Communion in Elden Ring, added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Grand Altar of Dragon Communion is in the Southern Shore region, west of the Finger Ruins of Rhia. You can reach this location by heading east then south from the Dragon's Pit Terminus Site of Grace.

name: Incantations
description: Incantations are a type of Magic in Elden Ring. Incantation spells are typically dependent on the Faith stat and have a variety of effects (such as healing, curing status effects, dealing damage, and enchanting people or weapons). Incantation spells are cast using Sacred Seals or the Staff of the Great Beyond. Incantations in Elden Ring are a combination of what would be Miracles and Pyromancies from past Souls games. You will find familiar favorites, as well as new ones.
metadata: {"Name": "Unlocks", "Two Fingers' Prayerbook": "Lord's Heal Lord's Aid", "Assassin's Prayerbook": "Assassin's Approach Darkness", "Golden Order Principia": "Radagon's Rings of Light Law of Regression", "Dragon Cult Prayerbook": "Lightning Spear Honed Bolt Electrify Armament", "Ancient Dragon Prayerbook": "Ancient Dragons' Lightning Spear Ancient Dragons' Lightning Strike", "Fire Monks' Prayerbook": "O, Flame! Surge, O Flame!", "Giant's Prayerbook": "Giantsflame Take Thee Flame, Fall Upon Them", "Godskin Prayerbook": "Black Flame Black Flame Blade"}

name: Items
description: Items in Elden Ring contain all obtainable items such as Consumables, Key Items, Materials, and more. Items may be obtained as drops from Enemies and Bosses, given by NPCs, looted from chests, or found throughout the Lands Between. This page includes links to the categories of all items in Elden Ring, covering their names, descriptions, effects, and locations.

name: Lore
description: Lore in Elden Ring covers all the information related to the world and mythos of the game. From past events that occurred long ago, to the history of the Lands Between and the mystery of the elusive Elden Ring, all can be found here. Please note that this page contains heavy spoilers.
metadata: {"Volcano Manor": "The Volcano Manor houses a group of Recusant Tarnished led by Praetor Rykard. Those in this faction seek to rebel against the Erdtree. Before being granted an audience with their Lord and becoming a part of the family, a newly recruited Tarnished must first invade their fellow Tarnished to prove their resolve.", "Mohgwyn Dynasty": "A faction led by Mohg, Lord of Blood. Similar to the Volcano Manor, those in service to the Mohgwyn Dynasty invade other Tarnished and renounce the Greater Will. Bloodshed is the only motive for invasion in this faction. You'll find the beginnings of the dynasty in Mohgwyn Palace.", "Carian Royal Family": "The remaining members of this faction are Rennala, Ranni, and their trusted advisors. Though they once held power over the Academy of Raya Lucaria, Rennala's grief over Radagon's departure caused her to weaken and the academy's scholars to rebel. Now, serving the royal family means serving the last Carian princess, Ranni, in her mission to usurp the Two Fingers and Greater Will, and rebel against her fate as an Empyrean.", "Those Who Live in Death": "Those Who Live in Death refer to the numerous undead plaguing the Lands Between. Their very existence defies the tenets of the prevalent Golden Order and so they live in persecution. Those in this faction are empathetic towards Those Who Live in Death and join them in awaiting the rise of their Lord, the first of the dead demigods, Godwyn, Prince of Death.", "Golden Order": "The Golden Order, established by Queen Marika when brought to the Lands Between by the Greater Will, is the most dominant faction in the land. The tenets of this Order govern the rules and status quo to be practiced by it's followers, many of who follow blindly. However, after the Shattering and the recent departure of the Greater Will from the Lands Between, a few of its members are starting to question the infallibility of the Order.", "The Frenzied Flame": "A covert faction led by the Three Fingers. Similar to the Two Fingers, the Three Fingers are vassals for a different unknown Outer God. This outer god rejects the Greater Will and proclaims that all that is wrong with the Lands Between are due to their mistakes. Those in this faction await one who would take up the mantle of Lord of Chaos to burn the world down and melt all of its troubles away. To them, may chaos take the world."}

name: Man-Serpent
description: Man-Serpent is an Enemy in Elden Ring. Man-Serpents are large humanoid lizards patrolling the lava-submerged town at Volcano Manor. Most Man-Serpents you'll find wield a sword and shield, but there is also a variation that attacks with a whip.
metadata: {"Location": "Volcano Manor", "Drops": "728 - 741 RunesGelmir Glintstone StaffMagma BladeMan-Serpent's ShieldVolcanic Stone"}

Players will be able to buy certain items and as well as trade a variety of goods and resources that have been gathered or are no longer needed for a certain amount of Runes. You can find detailed information on a merchant's location and more on each individual page linked below.

name: NPC Invaders
description: NPC Invaders in Elden Ring are hostile NPCs or human Enemies that could appear once players reach specific locations. If an NPC invader is close, players will receive a prompt stating who they are invaded by. If they are riding on horseback, Torrent will despawn. Upon their defeat the game notifies players with the prompt, Invader Vanquished. It is also possible to be invaded by some familiar ally NPCs. On the other hand, it is also possible to have a sign available for you invade specific NPCs as well. Upon defeat, this will instead inform the player that the host has be vanquished. Below is a list of all available NPC Invaders including NPCs that players can invade in Elden Ring sorted by Location.

name: Paintings
description: Paintings in Elden Ring are Info Items scattered all around The Lands Between that act as a form of treasure hunt. The Wandering Artist Spirit's Paintings depict specific locations you'll have to find in order to meet the spirits of the artists themselves. Upon finding and inspecting one of the seven drawings, a ghost of the artist will manifest at the location from which they were painted, granting a specific reward. Note that the location you must seek is not the structure or landscape depicted itself, but rather the spot the artist would have been when painting it. This page covers a full list of all the Paintings found in Elden Ring, including their location, solution, and rewards.

name: Roundtable Hold
description: Roundtable Hold is a Location in Elden Ring. The Roundtable Hold is found after Melina invites to take you there. This area can only be accessed via fast travel. It is a place where the Two Fingers gathers worthy tarnished to pursue the shardbearers and eventually repair the Elden Ring.

name: Sellia Hideaway
description: Sellia Hideaway is a Location in Elden Ring. The Sellia Hideaway is found in North-East Caelid, near Sellia town proper. It is in the border Region of Caelid and Dragonbarrow but it is slightly into Dragonbarrow.

name: Sorceries
description: Sorceries are a type of Magic in Elden Ring. Sorcery Spells are often dependent on the Intelligence stat and have a variety of effects. These can range from conjuring magic projectiles, to calling down meteors, and even attacking using blood magic. (There are also a few spells with effects other than dealing damage.) Sorceries are cast using a Glintstone Staff or the Carian Sorcery Sword. There are trainers that allow you to purchase many spells for Runes, while others are found in the world.
metadata: {"Name": "Unlocks", "Academy Scroll": "Great Glintstone Shard Swift Glintstone Shard", "Conspectus Scroll": "Glintstone Cometshard Star Shower", "Royal House Scroll": "Glintblade Phalanx Carian Slicer"}

name: Spirit Ashes
description: Spirit Ashes in Elden Ring are companions, often mimicking the Lands Between's Enemies, summoned by the Spirit Calling Bell to aid you in Combat. This page covers how they function, the spirit ashes available, summon costs, and a community-driven list of their relative strength.

name: Spirit NPC
description: Spirit NPCs are ghosts in Elden Ring. You can interact with them to get dialogue, and they help shed light on events that have happened throughout the Lands Between. Some Spirits offer side quests and will reward players with items, while others only state a recall of a particular event. Many spirits give insight to the Lore of certain characters.

name: Three Sisters
description: Three Sisters is a Location in Elden Ring. Three Sisters is a sub-region of Liurnia of the Lakes. It is found west of Caria Manor and is accessible only after completing the manor and defeating its boss Royal Knight Loretta.

name: Ancient Meteoric Ore Greatsword
description: Ancient Meteoric Ore Greatsword is a Colossal Sword in Elden Ring. It was added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Ancient Meteoric Ore Greatsword scales primarily with Strength, Dexterity and Arcane and is a good Weapon for Arcane players that want to use a humongous weapon. This greatsword has high physical damage and does a decent amount of magic damage. It comes with the White Light Charge skill that lets you charge foes and blast them with light magic.

name: Ansbach's Longbow
description: Ansbach's Longbow is a Bow in Elden Ring. It was added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Ansbach's Longbow scales primarily with Strength and Dexterity and is wielded by Sir Ansbach. All Bows require Arrows to fire.

name: Anvil Hammer
description: Anvil Hammer is a Colossal Weapon in Elden Ring. It is a brand new Colossal Weapon in the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Anvil Hammer scales primarily with Strength, Dexterity, Intelligence and Faith and is a good Weapon for Strength or multi-attribute Builds. This weapon comes with the Smithing Art Spears skill which lets you smash the ground very hard and summons multiple spears from the ground.

name: Axes
description: Axes are a type of Weapon in Elden Ring. Axes are heavy weapons that can be wielded with one hand. They are best used in close combat and provide a wide variety of attacks.

name: Backhand Blade
description: Backhand Blade is a Backhand Blade in Elden Ring. It is found in the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Backhand Blade scales primarily with Strength and Dexterity and is a good paired Weapon for agile builds that prefer DEX as it has S scaling in DEX at max upgrade with the Keen affinity

name: Backhand Blades
description: Backhand Blades are a type of Weapon in Elden Ring. Backhand Blades are wielded with the blade of the sword opposite to the direction of the wielding hand thumb, and they can be dual wielded too, granting the player new ways to block attacks.

name: Ballistas
description: Ballistae are a type of Weapon in Elden Ring. Ballistae are ranged weapons that can be used to inflict high damage on hostile characters from afar and with great potential to break guard. Unlike Crossbows, they do not need to be loaded before firing each shot. They grant no guard protection, encouraging users to maintain distance from advancing enemies. Ballistae do not share the ability to fire mid-jump with crossbows. Ballistae require Great Bolts as ammunition.

name: Bandit's Curved Sword
description: Bandit's Curved Sword is a Curved Sword in Elden Ring. The Bandit's Curved Sword scales primarily with Strength and Dexterity and is a good Weapon for high dexterity characters who can excel at slashing attacks while spinning.

name: Beast Claw (Weapon)
description: Beast Claw (Weapon) is a Beast Claw weapon in Elden Ring. It is found in the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Beast Claw (Weapon) scales primarily with Strength and Dexterity and is weapon that allows the wielder to behave like a beast. This weapon lets you execute a barrage of slash attacks that cause blood loss buildup.

name: Beast Claws
description: Beast Claws are a type of Weapon in Elden Ring. Beast Claws are similar to previous known Claw Weapons but grant a new playstyle with a whole new moveset of different attacks.

name: Black Steel Greathammer
description: Black Steel Greathammer is a Great Hammer in Elden Ring. It was added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Black Steel Greathammer scales primarily with Strength, Dexterity and Faith and is a good Weapon for Faith builds that are looking for a massive weapon that also scales with Strength and Dexterity.

name: Black Steel Twinblade
description: Black Steel Twinblade is a Twinblade in Elden Ring. It is a brand new Twinblade in the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Black Steel Twinblade scales primarily with Strength and Dexterity and is a good Weapon for builds that want to maintain Faith Scaling despite changing its infusion. This weapon does Physical and Holy damage and comes with the Spinning Slash skill.

name: Bloodfiend's Arm
description: Bloodfiend's Arm is a Colossal Weapon in Elden Ring. It was added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Bloodfiend's Arm scales primarily with Strength, Dexterity and Arcane and is a good Weapon for Bleed and Arcane Builds. This is a slow but hard-hitting weapon that sprays blood when using the heavy attacks.

The Bloodfiend's Fork scales primarily with Strength, Dexterity and Arcane and is a good Weapon for Bleed and Arcane Builds. This weapon causes blood loss build-up and can increase attack power by using the Barbaric Roar skill along with a combo.

The Bloodfiend's Sacred Spear scales primarily with Strength, Dexterity and Arcane and is a good Weapon for Arcane builds. This weapon causes blood-loss build-up and comes with the Bloodfiend's Bloodboon skill that lets you summon blood flames to your enemy.

name: Bone Bow
description: Bone Bow is a Light Bow in Elden Ring. It was added with the Shadow of the Erdtree DLC. The Bone Bow scales primarily with Strength and Dexterity and is a good Weapon for setting status effects and enemies who input read projectiles. This is a fast weapon that comes with the Rancor Shot skill that lets you engulf your arrows with spirits that go for an enemy. All Light Bows require Arrows to fire.

name: Claws
description: Claws are a type of Weapon in Elden Ring. Claws are equipped on both hands and excel in fast, close-range combat. They are lightweight weapons with rapid slash attacks, and users usually wear them on Dexterity Builds or Arcane Builds for Status Buildup.

name: Colossal Swords
description: Colossal Swords are a type of Weapon in Elden Ring (not to be confused with Colossal Weapons). Colossal Swords replace Ultra Greatswords from the Dark Souls series. Colossal Swords have lengths often exceeding the height of the Tarnished themselves. While they are extremely heavy and swing much slower than other swords, they make up for it with a long reach and massive damage output. Colossal Swords typically require very high Strength to wield properly- if the player falls a few points short of the requirements, wielding them two-handed will make up the difference.

name: Crossbows
description: Crossbows are a type of Weapon in Elden Ring. Crossbows are ranged weapons that can be used to inflict high damage on hostile characters from afar. Unlike Bows, they must be loaded before firing each shot, but in turn can fire immediately without a draw animation if the weapon is loaded beforehand. They grant no guard protection, encouraging users to maintain distance from advancing enemies. They are best used in the offhand as a ranged option that can also be used to apply Statuses. Crossbows require Bolts as ammunition.

name: Dexterity
description: Dexterity is one of the Stats in Elden Ring. Stats refer to various properties that govern your character's strengths and weaknesses, as well as how they are affected by interactions in and out of combat. Dexterity primarily affects a player's ability to wield Dexterity-based Armaments, as well as the damage dealt by such weapons. It is one of the 8 Main Attributes that players can spend Runes on to level up, increasing the Stat's effectiveness and influencing their relative secondary stats. Stats such as Dexterity are an important aspect of character progression in Elden Ring.
metadata: {"Type": "Main Attribute", "Effect": "Attribute required to wield advanced armaments.Also boosts attack power of dexterity-scaling armaments, reduces casting time of Spells, softens fall damage, and makes it harder to be knocked off your horse."}

name: Greatswords
description: Greatswords are a type of Weapon in Elden Ring. Greatswords are capable of inflicting a massive amount of damage, but sacrifice mobility, making the player vulnerable and open to enemy and boss attacks if they are not careful. High risk, high reward is the name of the game with these Weapons, but they can pancake many enemies, allowing you to finish them off unscathed.

name: HP
description: HP or Hit Points is one of the Stats in Elden Ring. Stats refer to various properties that govern your character's strengths and weaknesses, as well as how they are affected by interactions in and out of combat. HP is a measure of your health and how much damage you can take before falling in combat. It is one of the Base Stats which are directly affected by a player's Main Attribute distribution. Stats such as HP are an important aspect of character progression in Elden Ring.
metadata: {"Type": "Base Stat", "Effect": "Determines your current and total health.", "Influenced by": "Vigor"}

description: Halberds are a type of Weapon in Elden Ring. Halberds strike a balance between moderate damage and long reach, combining straight thrusting attacks and wide swinging strikes.

name: Hand-to-Hand Arts
description: Hand-to-Hand Arts are a type of Weapon in Elden Ring. Hand-to-Hand Arts are similar or a variant of the Fist Weapons, adding multiple quick moves that the player will be able to perform by using only their body as a weapon.

name: Heavy Thrusting Swords
description: Heavy Thrusting Swords are a type of Weapon in Elden Ring. Heavy Thrusting Swords focus on piercing attacks and are best used to counter or follow-up an enemy's attack. Their extra weight packs some extra physical attack power and still allows players to use this weapon with a Shield.

name: Intelligence
description: Intelligence is one of the Stats in Elden Ring. Stats refer to various properties that govern your character's strengths and weaknesses, as well as how they are affected by interactions in and out of combat. Intelligence primarily affects a player's ability to cast Sorceries, as well as equipping the weapons required to cast them. It is one of the 8 Main Attributes that players can spend Runes on to level up, increasing the Stat's effectiveness and influencing their relative secondary stats. Stats such as Intelligence are an important aspect of character progression in Elden Ring.
metadata: {"Type": "Main Attribute", "Effect": "Attribute required to perform sorceries. Also boosts magic power of intelligence-scaling Sorceries and improves Magic Resistance."}

name: Katanas
description: Katanas are a type of Weapon in Elden Ring. Katanas specialize in mid-range combat and are capable of inflicting slash and thrust attacks, as well as the Hemorrhage Status Effect in many cases, which can deal significant damage. Many players choose this weapon type for its unique moveset.

name: Light Bows
description: Light Bows are a type of Weapon in Elden Ring. Light Bows are two-handed ranged weapons that can be used to inflict damage on enemies from afar. Similar to other ranged weapons, they grant no guard protection. However, Light Bows are unique in their ability to quickly notch and fire an arrow immediately after rolling, sprinting, or landing from a jump, allowing a more aggressive and mobile playstyle. Light Bows require Arrows as ammunition.

name: Light Greatswords
description: Light Greatswords are a type of Weapon in Elden Ring. Light Greatswords are as long as greatswords but far lighter allowing the wielder to have quicker attacks capable of flowing into each other at the cost of damage.

Perfume Bottles consist of glass bottles filled with potent mixtures that can deal various types of elemental damage when released into the air. name: Player Trade
description: Player Trade for Elden Ring, also simply known as Trading, is an online mechanic where players can exchange various items and equipment between players. There may be limitations to which items and equipment can be traded. Guidelines, various mechanics and any other information regarding trading can be found on this page. Please note that this wiki page is made solely for that purpose. Leaving a comment on the page to have people help you with trading is discouraged, because of the implied risks. Try using the Official Discord link of the Fextralife Wiki and enter the Elden Ring channel instead.

name: Shields
description: Shields in Elden Ring are pieces of protective equipment which provide defense against the world's Enemies and Bosses. Typically wielded in the off-hand, Shields are capable of guarding, parrying, bashing, or even something unique with their respective Ashes of War. They can be two-handed for increased stability against incoming attacks. Most Builds can benefit from having a Shield equipped, even with infrequent use, so long as the stat requirements of the shield are met.

name: Sites of Grace
description: Sites of Grace are the Checkpoints of Elden Ring. These special locations feature a luminous remnant of Grace, enshrined by a small stump of roots, and allow a moment of respite in The Lands Between. Sites of Grace function pretty adjacent to how Bonfires worked in FromSoftware's previous titles, the Dark Souls series.

name: Skills
description: Skills in Elden Ring are armament abilities that allow the player to execute various and unique offensive attacks from the Weapon or Shield that is currently wielded. Skills can often be changed using Ashes of War, though there are some armaments with unique skills that cannot be exchanged.

name: Spears
description: Spears are a type of Weapon in Elden Ring. Spears allow the user to engage in melee combat from a safe distance, keeping them out of harms way. They are also some of the most useful melee Weapons on horseback due to their superior range.

Straight Swords are some of the easiest Weapons to use in Elden Ring, and work well when combined with a Shield, allows for quick follow up attacks after blocking.

name: Strength
description: Strength is one of the Stats in Elden Ring. Stats refer to various properties that govern your character's strengths and weaknesses, as well as how they are affected by interactions in and out of combat. Strength primarily affects a player's ability to wield Strength-based Armaments, as well as the damage dealt by such weapons. It is one of the 8 Main Attributes that players can spend Runes on to level up, increasing the Stat's effectiveness and influencing their relative secondary stats. Stats such as Strength are an important aspect of character progression in Elden Ring.
metadata: {"Type": "Main Attribute", "Effects": "Attribute required to wield heavy armaments.Also boosts attacks power of strength-scaling armaments and affects your Physical Defense."}

The Swift Spear scales primarily with Dexterity and is a good Weapon for builds that like to attack rapidly with decent range. This weapon is good for its high attack speed and can be paired with a shield. This also comes with the Impaling Thrust which goes through an enemy guarding.

name: Whetblades
description: Whetblades in Elden Ring are Key Items which allow the use of Ashes of War at Sites of Grace to bestow Skills and Affinities. This page covers their names, affinities they unlock, and Locations.
metadata: {"Name": "Usage", "Whetstone Knife": "Unlocks ability to use Ashes of War to grant Skills and Affinities to armaments", "Iron Whetblade": "Unlocks affinity upgrades: Heavy, Keen, and Quality", "Glintstone Whetblade": "Unlocks affinity upgrades: Magic and Cold", "Red-Hot Whetblade": "Unlocks affinity upgrades: Fire and Flame Art", "Sanctified Whetblade": "Unlocks affinity upgrades: Lightning and Sacred", "Black Whetblade": "Unlocks affinity upgrades: Poison, Blood, and Occult"}

name: Whips
description: Whips are a type of Weapon in Elden Ring. Whips usually inflict moderate damage, and perform poorly against heavily armored enemies, but do have long reach. Most of them deal Strike Damage that is useful against certain types of enemies. They can serve as a good offhand option or powerstanced for continuous attacks.
metadata: {"Name": "Phy Damage Type", "Tooth Whip": "Strike", "Whip": "Strike", "Thorned Whip": "Strike", "Urumi": "Slash", "Hoslow's Petal Whip": "Strike", "Magma Whip Candlestick": "Strike", "Giant's Red Braid": "Strike"}
